title: bean soup
directions: Rinse beans and cold water.
Bring to boil and simmer two minutes.
Remove from heat and cover.
Let stand one hour or add water and let stand overnight.
Drain.
Add ham bone, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 3 1/2 hours.
Add onion the last 1/2 hour.
Remove ham from bone.
Mash beans slightly with potato masher and add ham to soup.

title: grandma's cheese log
directions: Mix together cream cheese and horseradish and roll into a ball.
Place chopped dried beef on wax paper and roll cheese ball in beef to coat.
Wrap cheese ball in wax paper and chill for several hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: burrito dip
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Remove from heat and drain well.
Add chilies and refried beans.
Mix well.
Spread mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour taco sauce over the whole mixture and cover with cheese.
Bake at 375° until cheese is melted.
When you take the dish out of the oven, spoon sour cream on top of the melted cheese.
Serve warm with Tostitos.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Stir in taco seasoning, tomatoes and beans.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Place 1/2 the tortilla strips in a 2-quart casserole.
Top with half the meat mixture and half the cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes in microwave.
Spread with sour cream and garnish with avocado strips and chopped tomatoes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease and flour two 8-inch cake pans.
Combine cake mix and cocoa in bowl.
Add 1/2 cup milk and beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Add remaining 1/2 cup milk, eggs and butter; beat 2 minutes more.
Pour into pans.
Bake 25 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on rack.
Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: tomato salad
directions: Crumble crackers and mix with tomatoes.
Add other ingredients.

title: frozen peach salad
directions: Add enough water to pineapple juice to make 2 cups.
Boil. Dissolve jello in juice and water.
Chill until almost firm.
Add fruits, nuts, mayonnaise and Cool Whip (slightly softened).
Pour into pan that makes mixture at least 1 1/2 inches thick.
Freeze. Cut in squares.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Wonderful spring and summer salad!

title: stir fried spinach
directions: Trim the spinach and wash well. Cut into 2 to 3 inch slices. Heat oil in a large frying pan or wok. Add garlic, salt and shallots. Stir fry them in the hot oil for 20 seconds. Add the Tofu. Mash in the oil over medium heat. Add the spinach. Mix everything together well. Sprinkle evenly with soya sauce and cook gently for 1 1/2 minutes. Turn and stir once more.

title: company rice
directions: Bake one hour at 350°.
This recipe may be prepared in advance by not adding the rice until time for baking.

title: cran-raspberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce and stir to melt.
Add pineapple.
Pour 1/2 mixture in bowl and chill until firm.
Spread 1/2 sour cream over this and gently pour remaining Jell-O mixture.
Chill and spread sour cream on top. Garnish with green grapes.

title: italian potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Cool and peel or may be used with skin on.
Add remaining ingredients.
May be used warm or cold.

title: cranapple crisp
directions: Mix together like you would a pie crust.
Sprinkle over fruit. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In a saucepan, gently boil together, for 1 or 2 minutes, over medium heat, butter, sugar, cocoa and milk.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir in oats.
Drop on wax paper the size desired.

title: party potato casserole
directions: *Eight cups of cubed potatoes (about 8 medium) can be substituted for the frozen potatoes.

title: microwave rocky road fudge
directions: Butter 8-inch square pan.
Set aside.
Place chips, butter and shortening in large micro bowl.
Put on Medium (50%) for 5 minutes or until melted and smooth when stirred.
Add marshmallows and nuts; blend well.
Spread evenly in pan.
Cover; chill until firm. Cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 16.

title: olive nut spread
directions: Mash the cream cheese with a fork and add mayonnaise.
Blend well. Stir in chopped pecans and salad olives. Don't skimp on measurements.
Now add olive juice and pepper.
Stir well.
Put in covered container and refrigerate for several hours. Great on crackers and keeps very well if you can keep it.

title: southern biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into flour until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk, mixing just until dry ingredients are moistened.
(If necessary, add additional milk to make soft dough.)
Turn out onto lightly floured surface; knead gently a few times.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick; cut with floured 2-inch biscuit cutter.
For soft, high biscuits, place close together on ungreased cookie sheet; for crusty biscuits place about 1 inch apart.
Bake in preheated very hot oven (425°) for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: cream of celery soup
directions: In pan, melt butter. Add flour and blend on medium heat.
Add salt.
Pour in milk and stir to keep from sticking.
Yields 3 cups of white sauce.

title: dixie relish
directions: Mix vegetables together.
Cover with the salt; let stand overnight in a crock or enameled pan.
Drain.
Add spices, sugar and vinegar; pack into clean jars.
Seal.
Process in water bath for 15 minutes.

title: english pea and asparagus casserole
directions: Drain peas and asparagus.
Drain pimientos.
Make two layers of peas, asparagus and soup in a buttered casserole dish.
Put the chopped pimientos and onion between the layers.
Cover with buttered saltine cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: winterspice potpourri(not edible)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in airtight container. Shake before using.
To scent your home, simmer 2 heaping tablespoons in 4 to 6 cups water for 30 to 60 minutes.
Blend can be refrigerated and used again.

title: enchilada rice
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Add enchilada mix and tomato sauce.
Add to already cooked rice.
Sprinkle cheese over rice, then add lettuce and tomatoes over rice.
Enjoy.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Chop tomatoes, onion and peppers; place in a large stainless steel or porcelain bowl.
Sprinkle with salt and mix well.
Cover loosely with a towel and let stand overnight.
Drain well and discard liquid.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Add sour cream and whisk together until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into a dish of your choice.
Refrigerate until firm. Serves 8-10.

title: chocolate covered grapes
directions: Wash grapes and dry thoroughly on paper towels for several hours (one drop of moisture will cause failure). Line a cookie sheet with waxed paper; set aside. In a small saucepan, combine chocolate pieces and shortening. Heat and stir over low heat until chocolate is moistened. Hole grape bunch by stem and dip partially into melted chocolate. If necessary, spoon chocolate over grapes to coat. Let excess chocolate drip off. Place grapes, stem side up, on prepared cookie sheet. Chill until chocolate is firm, about 30 minutes or up to 6 hours.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Grease 9 x 9-inch pan. Mix ingredients. Pour 1/2 mixture in the pan. Put cheese on top.
Add remainder of mixture.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pickled squash
directions: Soak the first 4 ingredients in 3 quarts water with salt for 1 hour.
Pour off brine.

title: creamed spinach
directions: In a skillet, heat butter until melted. Add shallots and garlic; saute until soft. Add confit; heat through and add spinach. Saute until hot. Add cream and season with salt and pepper.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Cook celery and onions in butter until tender.
Mix all ingredients.
Place in baking dish and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple cheese bake
directions: Melt butter with flour and sugar.
Pat in bottom of Pyrex dish.
Pour in pineapple and cheese.
Add enough cracker crumbs to cover top.
May dot with butter.
Bake at 400° until it bubbles.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut a slice from stem end of each tomato and scoop out the pulp.
Place pulp in mixing bowl and add the rest of the ingredients except butter.
Mix thoroughly and fill each tomato shell.
Arrange stuffed tomatoes in baking dish.
Add 1/2 tablespoon butter to each tomato.
Add 1/4 cup hot water to baking dish and bake in moderate oven at 350°
for 25 minutes.
Serve at once.
Serves 6.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast and 2 tablespoons warm water and set aside. Combine dry ingredients. Cut in cup shortening. Add yeast and buttermilk. Shape into desired size biscuits. Place in greased pan and freeze or bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lu's dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in the one cup warm water and let stand a few minutes.
Add rest of ingredients together and add to yeast mixture.
Beat until dough is elastic.
Cover and put in warm place to rise, about one hour or until doubled.
Divide dough, form rolls and brush with melted butter.
I make butterhorns by dividing dough in half and rolling out into a circle.
Cut into eighths.
Brush with butter and start rolling from large end. Curve into a half circle shape.
Let rise and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Dough may be used as cinnamon rolls.

title: great grandma bee's white dinner rolls(plainville, wisconsin 1920)
directions: Put yeast into warm water and dissolve.
Bring milk to a boil and let cool.
Mix together sugar, salt, shortening, egg and yeast mixture.
Add cooled milk.
Add bread flour.
Put into a greased bowl and refrigerate overnight.

title: grilled scallops
directions: Wrap scallops in Prosciutto or bacon; fasten with a toothpick. Marinate overnight in red wine.
Drain and cook on a grill until bacon is done.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Cook zucchini in broth with onion, butter, lemon slices, curry powder, salt and pepper by bringing to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 8 to 12 minutes.
When cooked, put in blender until smooth. Stir in lime juice.
Serve warm or cold, garnished with sour cream.

title: fruit cocktail pie
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie shells, then sprinkle pecans on top.
Chill overnight.

title: banana punch
directions: Blend in blender. Freeze until ready to use, then add Sprite.

title: whiskey pound cake
directions: Use tube pan and spray with Baker's Joy or grease and flour.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add unbeaten eggs, bananas and nuts.
Mix well. Add flour and soda last.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: pineapple and banana punch(shared by mrs. clyde hill)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Combine sugar and hot water. Stir until dissolved and add to first mixture.
Pour into container and freeze about 2 hours before serving.
Set out to thaw.
Place in punch bowl and add 7-Up to equal liquid in punch. This is 2 large 7-Ups and 1 small.

title: 4th of july salad
directions: Prepare Honey-Sour Cream Dressing.
Mix strawberries, grapes, peaches and bananas.
Spoon fruit into lettuce cups.
Serve with Honey-Sour Cream Dressing.
Makes 5 servings.

title: almond brickle dessert
directions: Prepare topping.
Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Blend well.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour batter into greased 12 x 8-inch pan.
Spread with topping.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: creamy tomato soup
directions: Wash tomatoes well; core and quarter.
Cook on medium-low until almost done.
Add onion and celery soups, parsley and bay leaves.
Cook, stirring frequently so mixture will not stick, until tomatoes are very done (the skins will be loose).
Run through food mill.
Return to stove and add mixture of sugar, salt and pepper (adjust sugar and salt to the amount of tomatoes you have).
Bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
Fill hot jars and seal.
Process under 10 pounds of pressure for five minutes or in water bath for 40 minutes.
Makes 14 pints.
Recipe can be halved.

title: mary louise's buttermilk party muffins
directions: Dissolve dry yeast in 2 tablespoons very warm water and set aside.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and shortening.
Add buttermilk to yeast and mix with dry ingredients.
Roll to 3/8 to 1/2-inch thick, cut and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Heat milk to boiling.
Mix remaining ingredients up good and add to hot milk.
Last add beaten egg whites.
Makes 5 pies.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Blend with 1 egg.
Add gradually to dry ingredients.
Stir in corn and drop from tablespoon into deep hot fat.
Fry until golden brown 4 to 8 minutes.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken in 2 to 3-quart baking dish and season with salt and pepper.
Place one slice of cheese on each piece of chicken.
Mix can of soup with a little water and spoon evenly over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing mix on top.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, 1 hour or until tender.
Serves 8.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat jello and boiling water together with wire whisk.
Fold in cool whip and yogurt.
Stir with wooden spoon.
Pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate.

title: prune cake
directions: Beat oil and sugar until smooth; add eggs and continue to beat. Mix in flour and buttermilk alternately. Add all other ingredients and mix well. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Brown onions and beef in oil.
Add other ingredients.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese; stir in drained pineapple, 1 cup pecans and remainder of ingredients.
Form into a ball and roll in 1 cup nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: watergate salad
directions: Sprinkle dry pudding mix over Cool Whip and mix.
Add all other ingredients.
Fold and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: cheese balls
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Shape into ball and roll in 1/2 to 3/4 cup more chopped pecans.

title: dizzy pineapple bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9x5-inch loaf pan.
Combine ingredients and stir until mixed.
Do not over-mix!!
Pour batter into pan and bake for one hour or until bread tests done.

title: low calorie spaghetti
directions: Brown beef lightly in oil.
Sprinkle sauce mix over beef.
Add tomato puree and 2 puree cans of water.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Serve sauce with spaghetti.
Yields 4 servings.

title: rolls
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add oil and water.
Put batter in muffin tins.
Bake at 450°.
Makes 24 rolls.

title: frozen grape wine
directions: Mix all ingredients in gallon glass jug.
When mixed well, add water almost to the top.
Cover with a cloth held on with a rubber band.
Let stand 30 days.
Chill and serve or bottle for later use.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix fruit punch with water. Add other ingredients.
Serve in punch bowl.
When ready, add ice and 3 or 4 round slices of orange.
Makes a little more than 1 gallon.
If desired, add more punch or water to taste.

title: italian broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli until barely tender (5 to 7 minutes); drain well.

title: egg-sausage souffle
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour in casserole dish 9 x 13.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 12 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: taffy pull
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan with 1/2 cup water. Boil to hard crack stage.
Add vanilla and baking soda.
Pour into shallow dishes.
Cool.
Fold in edges.
Start pulling until white.

title: cheerio treats
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows.
Mix in peanut butter until all melted together.
Remove from burner and mix in cheerios
Mix in M & M's.
Spray a 9 x 13 inch cake pan with cooking spray.
Spread out mixture in the cake pan.
Wait approximately 5 minutes then cut into squares.
(If you wait too long to cut it is hard to cut.)

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Mix tart and sweet apples.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pare eggplant, if desired, and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Dip each slice into eggs, then into crumbs. Saute in hot olive oil until golden brown on both sides.
Place a layer of eggplant in a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with part of Parmesan and oregano.
Layer with some Mozzarella slices.
Cover well with part of tomato sauce.
Repeat layers until all eggplant is used, ending with a layer of sauce and several slices of Mozzarella.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until sauce is bubbly and cheese is melted.

title: sweet and sour franks
directions: Combine jelly and mustard in a double boiler until mixed.
Put cut franks in sauce.
Serve warm.

title: egg custard(club member: terah smith)
directions: Beat eggs. Add warm milk and sugar. Add vanilla and oleo.
May sprinkle nutmeg on top if desired. (I like mine better without it.) Bake at 350° to 375° until set. Be careful not to overbake.

title: stuffed pickles
directions: Core pickles with apple corer.
Let drain a bit.
Mix softened cream cheese, nuts and allspice; stuff the pickles and chill. Slice about 1/4 to 1/2-inch pieces and enjoy.

title: sourdough flapjacks
directions: Dissolve yeast in very warm water; stir well.
Add enough flour to make batter as stiff as waffle batter.
Cover; let stand overnight in warm place.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix together all ingredients, adding bread crumbs last.
Cut peppers lengthwise in half and clean.
Poke holes in each one to allow juices from filling to run off.
Fill each pepper generously.
Place in baking pan, 9 x 13 x 2-inch, and cover with your favorite spaghetti sauce. Serve with linguini or your favorite pasta.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift flour once; measure. Add baking powder, salt, soda and sugar and sift again. Add corn meal. Combine milk and eggs. Add to dry ingredients, mixing well. Bake in greased shallow pan in hot oven (425°) 40 minutes or until done.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: oat pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into pastry shell and top with 2/3 cup of pecans.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool before serving.

title: buttered pound cake
directions: Leave eggs and butter out overnight at room temperature.
Mix baking powder, salt and 3 cups flour (set aside).
Mix creamed butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Pour baking powder, salt and 3 cups of flour into the other bowl.
Pour milk slowly into it.
Add vanilla.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: vegetable stuffed sole
directions: Put butter, breadcrumbs, red pepper, carrot, celery, parsley, cayenne pepper, paprika, salt and lemon juice together.
Attach bowl and flat beater.
On stir speed, mix 45 seconds until combined.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Note:
Instant or long cooked rice can be used.
Long cook rice needs to be cooked 1/2 of required time.
Instant can be put together and baked by recipe.

title: chicken cacciatori
directions: In hot oil in large skillet, cook chickens until evenly browned.
Add onions, green peppers and garlic; brown lightly. Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Makes 8 servings.
Sauce is delicious when served over cooked thin spaghetti.

title: funnel cake
directions: Beat the first two ingredients together.

Blend the dry ingredients and gradually add to milk mixture, beat until smooth. Fill a skillet about 1/2 full of oil and heat for frying (375°). Place your finger over the bottom of a funnel with 3/8 inch opening and fill with 1/4 cup of mix.

title: salisbury steak bake
directions: Mix 1/4 cup soup with remaining ingredients.
Shape into 6 patties.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Spoon off fat.
Mix remaining soup with 1/3 cup water.
Pour over meat.
Bake 10 more minutes.

title: no-crust apple pie
directions: Mix apple slices with 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and water in saucepan.
Cook about 10 minutes or until apples are partially cooked.
Turn into 9-inch pie pan.
Cream butter; gradually cream in brown sugar.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture and mix thoroughly with spoon.
Sprinkle over the apples.
(Add enough flour to make a crumbly mix.)

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix baking mix, milk, cheese and parsley flakes until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds. Drop dough by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Mix margarine and garlic powder. Brush or pour over warm biscuits before removing from pan.
Serve warm.
Should make 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: ricotta cheese cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat Ricotta cheese, eggs, vanilla and sugar until blended. Add drained pineapple and pour over cake batter. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: chewy honey peanut butter(treats on a stick)
directions: You will also need 10 wooden sticks (optional).

title: snowball cake
directions: Soften gelatine in cold water 5 minutes.
Add hot water and stir until gelatine dissolves.
Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple.	Stir well.
Chill until mixture begins to thicken.

title: almond crescents
directions: Cream margarine and add sugar; blend in almond extract.
Add flour and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts; chill.
Shape rounded teaspoonfuls of dough into crescents; place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar or colored sugar.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Beat eggs slightly, mix with oleo.
Dissolve yeast in water, add to eggs.
Add milk, sugar and salt.
Blend in flour, one cup at a time. Store in covered dish in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out 1/3 of dough at a time, cut into pie slice shape and roll up from large end to small.
Let rise 4 hours.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: peachy fruit salad
directions: Pour cool vinegar mixture over vegetables. Refrigerate overnight.

title: recipe for a mother
directions: Stir well and let it age for a lifetime.
Serves many.
Yield: One mom.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Saute onion, sliced celery and garlic in 2 tbsp butter.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs together, then add bananas. Add self-rising flour.
Mix real well.
Grease loaf pan and cook at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: herbed cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients except chives in blender or food processor.
Blend until smooth.
Chill and sprinkle with chives. Serve with crackers or veggies.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add water and stir until thick. Knead same as you would for bread.
Let rise until about double in bulk.
Roll out as you would any cinnamon rolls.
Cut and put on pan and let rise.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: caritas texas hash
directions: *If too dry, add more tomatoes.
Rice will absorb liquid.

title: southwestern chicken soup
directions: Cover chicken with 6 cups water.
Add bay leaf, peppercorns and salt.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes or until chicken is tender. Discard bay leaves and peppercorns.
Cut meat into 1-inch pieces. Return to broth.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix sour cream and cream of chicken soup together.
Add thawed potatoes and onion.
Mix well.
Add Velveeta and mix again.
Pour into well greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top evenly with corn flakes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves lots!
Can be prepared ahead of time.

title: steak and green peppercorn sauce
directions: Heat butter and oil in a wide nonstick frying pan; add steak and cook until well browned on both sides and cooked to desired doneness, 3 to 5 minutes per side for rare.
Add brandy and set aflame, shaking pan until flame dies.
Remove meat and keep warm. Add shallots to pan; cook, stirring, until soft, 2 to 3 minutes. Add peppercorns, cream, mustard, tarragon and any accumulated steak juices.
Boil, stirring, until shiny bubbles form, 3 to 4 minutes.
Spoon sauce over meat and noodles.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: In large bowl, combine 3 cups all-purpose flour and yeast. In pan, heat milk, margarine, sugar and salt until warm and margarine is almost melted, stirring constantly.
Add to flour mixture.
Add eggs and beat with mixer on low for 30 seconds.
Use spoon and mix in whole wheat flour and as much of white all-purpose flour as you can.
Knead dough on floured surface until moderately stiff dough that's elastic.
Shape into ball; turn into greased bowl and let rise for 1 hour.
Punch down.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Layer wafers and bananas, sliced, then pudding.
Repeat as many layers as you desire.

title: mystery muffins
directions: Place flour in bowl; add mayonnaise and milk.
Stir.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 16 to 20 minutes.

title: summer spaghetti
directions: Cut onion and tomatoes.
Mix all spices with tomatoes, onion and garlic.
Add olive oil to mixture.
Let sit in fridge for 6 hours to marinate.
Cook spaghetti.
Pour cold mixture over spaghetti (hot) and mix well.
Enjoy!

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add flour and eggs.
Beat well and add buttermilk.
Pour into unbaked pie shell (9-inch).
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 1 pie.

title: imitation pink champagne
directions: Combine sugar and water.
Simmer until sugar is dissolved. Cool.
Mix with chilled fruit juice and syrup.
Just before serving, add ginger ale, pouring slowly down side of punch.
Serve over ice.
Makes 6 cups.

title: chocolate marshmallow icing
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together over hot water.
Pour hot milk over sugar and salt until sugar is dissolved.
Add chocolate mixture and beat until perfectly smooth.
If icing must be thinned, add 1 tablespoon hot milk.
Cut marshmallows into thinnest possible pieces.
Cover bottom layer with chocolate icing, then marshmallows, then more icing.
Put top layers on and carefully press two layers together.
Cover top and sides with chocolate.
Cut marshmallows thinly as before and place on chocolate, then remaining icing.

title: miss iris mae's pound cake
directions: Have margarine at room temperature and put in
a mixing bowl. Add sugar and eggs (slightly beaten); add milk and 1 tablespoon shortening.
Beat until well blended.
Add flour, baking powder and flavoring.
Blend well.
Bake in oven at 335° for 1 hour.

title: angela's strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: chinese almond cookies
directions: Soften margarine and combine with remaining ingredients. Dough will be short.
Make into small balls and flatten with chopped nuts and part of a maraschino cherry in center.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: celebration punch
directions: Thaw pine-orange-banana juice.
Pour all liquids together in punch bowl; stir to mix well.
When ready to serve, add all sliced fruits.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend all together; mix well. Form into 1 in size balls, about 3in apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with a fork. Bake at 350 degrees for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Place raw meatballs (I buy frozen) with the rest of the ingredients and cook on low until meatballs are done.
You can put in crock-pot and will be done for later that day.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Mix all together except cheese.
Season well with Worcestershire sauce, chili powder, Tabasco and salt to taste. Put in a greased casserole and bake 1/2 hour or until it bubbles all the way through.
Top with grated cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Drain cooked broccoli; place in the bottom of a greased pan or casserole dish.
Place chicken on top of the broccoli.
Combine the soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Pour over the chicken and top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: ok beef dip
directions: Brown meat in skillet, drain any fat.
Add onion, cheese, soup and sauce.
Cook over medium heat until cheese is melted.
Serve with chips or vegetables.

title: salmon mold
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Set in mold and refrigerate for 15 minutes.
Garnish with watercress.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients, except sugar.
Stir juice into bananas.
Cream together the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs to sugar until light and fluffy.
Alternately add dry ingredients and milk.
Beat after each addition.
Fold in bananas.
Pour into 2 greased 5 x 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Cool in pans for 10 minutes, then put on racks to cool completely.

title: spaetzle german noodles
directions: Mix eggs, milk, flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and the pepper. (Batter will be thick.)
Heat water and 1 teaspoon salt to boiling in Dutch oven.
Press batter through colander (preferably one with large holes), a few tablespoons at a time, into boiling water. Stir once or twice to prevent sticking.
Cook until noodles rise to surface and are tender, about 5 minutes.
Drain.
Pour margarine over noodles.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Take 1 cup of faith and spread generously through each lovely day God has given you.
Add 1 package of Hope to every good deed. And thank God for giving you graces you need.
Take 2 cups of charity; sift all around to your friends, neighbors, anyone you've found.
Bake for a lifetime and ice with love.
You have the recipe for Heaven above.

title: party meatballs
directions: Combine beef and 2 tablespoons of soup mix.
Shape into about 50 small meatballs.
Brown, then drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat 20 minutes.
Stir now and then.
Uncover for last 5 minutes to thicken sauce.
Serve on toothpicks.

title: pineapple bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish (11 x 7-inch shallow baking dish).
In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix in pineapple with its juice and then fold in the bread pieces.
Pour into the prepared baking dish.
Bake until the pudding gets lightly brown on top and firm, about 1 hour.
Can be served hot or cold.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix and place in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° until browned and cheese is melted.

title: 9 egg pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add baking powder to flour.
Add flour mixture alternately with eggs, beginning and ending with flour. Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until a cake tester comes out clean.

title: sweet dollies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Remove from oven and spread the melted butter over bottom of pan. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over butter.
Spread coconut over graham cracker crumbs, then add layer of chocolate chips, then a layer of chopped nuts.
Drizzle sweetened condensed milk evenly over top. Return to oven and bake for about 25 minutes, until lightly brown on top.
Cut into small squares when completely cooled.
Makes 36 small bars.

title: christmas salad
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and sugar.
In another bowl, fold together the mayonnaise, lemon juice, pineapple, pecans and bananas. Add cream cheese mixture and fold.
Fold the cranberry sauce into the whipped cream. Add to other mixture and fold. Freeze.
Keeps well for several weeks.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in a round pan.
Pack brown sugar firmly into pan and around the sides.
Place pineapple around the pan.
Place a cherry in the middle of the pineapple.
Mix cake mix according to the package directions.
(Tip:
Replace 1/2 of the water required with pineapple juice.)
Pour cake mix over pineapple and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: 7 layer taco dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and seasoning mix together.
Layer all ingredients in order in a 9 x 13-inch pan .
Top with jalapeno or green chili.
Better if made 1 day ahead.
Serve with chips.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake until golden brown.
Bake at 350°.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix soups, chicken broth, Cheddar cheese, chicken, mushrooms and spaghetti together.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10. Turkey can be used instead of chicken.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Saute onions in oil for 10 minutes. Drain. Add celery, mushrooms and chicken broth. Cook 5 minutes over low heat.
Stir in bean sprouts, water chestnuts, bamboo shoots and chicken.
Make a paste of soy sauce and cornstarch. Stir in. Continue cooking over very low heat until thickened.
Sprinkle with fried chow mein noodles or de-Shredded Wheat biscuit, 1/2 c. Rice Krispies or 1/2 c. crushed Life cereal.
Serves 6.

title: coconut balls
directions: Heat corn syrup.
Add coconut and mix well. Let set until cool.
Roll into small balls (you may need to wet hands because candy is very sticky).
Freeze balls.

title: soda biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to very hot (450°).
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and blend lightly.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
Knead gently about 30 seconds.
Roll or pat to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with floured 2-inch cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in a very hot oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 14 (2-inch) biscuits.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter, and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Put into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat margarine in rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches, in oven until melted.
Sprinkle with brown sugar. Spoon pineapple over brown sugar; spread evenly.

title: cabbage-onion slaw
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat to cool.
Pour over other ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: unstuffed cabbage
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown ground beef and onions for 5 to 6 minutes, stirring to break up ground beef.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Put sugar and Karo all in a boiler. Stir together and boil until forms soft ball in cold water.
Pour in platter that has been buttered and let cool.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop on greased sheet.
Flatten with fork and bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: saucepan peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa; add butter and milk.
Bring to boil and boil approximately 2 minutes, while stirring.
Remove from heat; add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well and drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool.

title: lefse
directions: Cook and rice potatoes.
While they are still warm, add butter and sugar; stir.
Add cream and salt, then lastly the flour.
Work with your hands and make small balls the size of golf balls.
Place on cookie sheet lined with wax paper.
Put in refrigerator until chilled.
Take out and roll in round pieces, almost like a pie crust.
Use lefse stick to slide under it and move it to lefse griddle to bake.
Be sure to bake both sides.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together dry cake mix, salt, soda and oil until blended.
Spread evenly into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes or until crust is golden brown around edges. Prepare pie filling as directed on can.
Pour over baked crust. Bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until center is firm.
Cool.
Spread Cool Whip over pumpkin mixture and store in refrigerator.
May garnish with nuts if you wish.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil breasts.
Cool and bone.
Pull or cut in small pieces. Place in the bottom of casserole dish.
Mix sour cream and soup together.
Spread over top of chicken.
Crumble crackers on top of mixture.
Melt butter and pour on top of crackers.
Bake at 350° until crackers are light brown and mixture bubbles (approximately 30 minutes).

title: better than sex cake(almost)
directions: Bake cake mix in a 9 x 2-inch pan according to the directions on the box.
Boil pineapple and sugar for 2 minutes.
When cake is done, punch holes in cake with a round wooden spoon.
While cake is still hot, pour pineapple mixture over cake and let cool.
Mix pudding according to directions and spread over cake.
Spread Cool Whip over top of pudding and sprinkle coconut over whipped topping. Cover and refrigerate.
Real rich and gooey.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt butter slowly.
Add sugar and eggs; beat lightly.
Add salt, nuts and milk.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: power pretzels
directions: Spread the top half of each pretzel with cream cheese or peanut butter.
On waxed paper, mix together cereal and chocolate morsels.
Roll pretzels in cereal mixture.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: devil food cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chunky guacamole
directions: Place the jalapeno, half the chopped onion and the salt in the work bowl of a food processor.
Process until it becomes a paste. Stir in half the tomato and half the cilantro and continue to process to a paste.

title: dave's wienies
directions: Over medium heat in a medium saucepan, combine jelly, mustard and brown sugar until jelly is melted and mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Add hot dogs and simmer 5 minutes, coating the hot dogs completely.
Serve warm.

title: heavenly strawberry pie
directions: Take 3 cups of strawberries and cut in half. Add powdered sugar.
Let stand 1 hour. Drain.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Put all together in a round mixing bowl (thin bowl works best). Do not need to butter dish.
Microwave for 2 minutes on High.
(If microwave is 600 watts, cook 3 minutes.)
Take out.
Stir together and beat.

title: easy russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients in an airtight container.
Use 1 or 2 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix in a medium bowl, marshmallow cream, cream cheese, orange peel and dash of ginger, then refrigerate until serving.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Make a golden brown roux with water and flour.
Add onion, green pepper and celery.
Simmer until tender.
Add tomatoes and water; simmer about 20 minutes.
Add shrimp, salt and pepper. Cook on low until shrimp turn pink.
Add parsley and onion tops. Add additional water if needed.
Cook 10 more minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: vegetable bake
directions: If using fresh veggies, prepare as usual.
Prepare frozen veggies until crisp-tender.
Add mushrooms.
Transfer to casserole.
Combine cream-style corn, cheese and soup.
Stir into veggie mix.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Sift
together flour, baking powder, soda and salt; set aside. In
a
large mixing bowl combine sugar, oil and mashed bananas; beat together.
Then add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk	and nuts.
Bake in a tube pan or 3 cake pans at 350° until done.

title: corn bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together flour, corn meal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, beat together eggs, milk and oil or melted shortening.
Add to flour mixture and stir just until batter is smooth (do not overbeat).
Pour into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 425° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 8 or 9 servings.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat well.
Stir in 1 to 2 tablespoons milk or half and half to make it creamier. Refrigerate.
Cut up Granny Smith apples for dispensing.

title: karen's famous cookie sheet cake
directions: Put the flour, sugar and soda in mixing bowl.
In a saucepan, add 1 cup water, cocoa and margarine.
Bring to boil.
Add to the sugar and flour mixture; mix well.
Add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk; stir well.

title: lemon squares
directions: Reserve 1 cup dry cake mix.
Combine remaining cake mix, 1 egg and oil (mixture will be crumbly).
Press into bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2 cake pan.
Beat remaining ingredients until light and fluffy, 3 minutes.
Pour into crust and bake about 20 minutes (until no imprint when touched lightly in center).
Cool and cut into squares.

title: brownies
directions: Mix together; mixture will be very stiff.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain well.
Stir in McCormick Salad seasoning.
Set in refrigerator to cool.
Dice all other ingredients.
Add these to spaghetti.
Stir in real well.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add milk slowly and cook in double boiler over hot water until thick and smooth.
Cool; add vanilla and pour into 9-inch baked pie shell.
Top with meringue made with 2 egg whites and 2 tablespoons sugar.

title: chicken delight
directions: Wrap each breast half with bacon.
Line baking dish with dried beef.
Place chicken on top.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour
over chicken. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cover with foil the first hour.
Good with rice.

title: spinach risotto
directions: Cook the chopped spinach in 3 tablespoons of olive oil with 1/4 cup of the onion until completely defrosted.
Add the garlic and cook until almost dry; set aside.
In a large, heavy pot, soften the remaining onion in the rest of the olive oil.
Add the rice and toss with oil.
Add the white wine and, stirring with wooden spoon, cook over moderate heat until the wine has been absorbed.
Add the chicken broth to the rice, 1/2 cup at a time, the same way that the wine was added, until the rice is al dente and a creamy sauce has developed throughout the rice.
This will take about 30 minutes.
Add the spinach with the last addition of stock.
Stir in the Parmesan cheese and butter.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: maudies mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into greased muffin tins. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel and thinly slice potatoes; boil for 5 minutes in salted water.
Heat soup and milk.
Add cheese and onion.
Layer drained potatoes and soup mixture alternately in a casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese and paprika.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.

title: cornbread salad
directions: In bowl, pour 1/2 cornbread mix.
Mix corn, beans, onions, pepper, tomatoes and cucumber together.
Put 1/2 over cornbread mix.
Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise and dressings.
Put 1/2 over vegetables.
Mix top with 1/2 cup cheese and repeat the steps again.

title: green vegetable salad
directions: Pull lettuce from head; slice cucumber and onions.
Cut tomato in wedges, and cut up peppers.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Toss for approximately one minute.
Spoon into small salad dish.
Add dressing and sprinkle with raisins.
Serve.

title: congealed salad
directions: In small bowl, dissolve strawberry jello in 1 cup hot water. In large bowl, mash cream cheese.
Gradually add jello to cream cheese.
Add pineapple, coconut and chopped nuts.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Pour into large serving dish.
Store in refrigerator and allow to congeal.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: double chocolate muffins
directions: Grease standard 12-muffin pan or line with paper cups. Preheat oven to 350°.
Ingredients should be at room temperature. Bake muffins on oven center rack.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat sugar, syrup and butter.
Then add other ingredients. Cook at 300° until brown.

title: creamy beef, macaroni and vegetables
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, macaroni, squashes and mayonnaise.
Heat through.
Let it cook for 1/2 hour or more. Sprinkle with cheese and serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Remove seeds from oranges and grind with cranberries. Add sugar and pineapple. Mix well. Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add to mixture. Mix well and congeal. Good with ham or turkey.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat eggs and other ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased pie pans.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.
Put margarine in 3-quart oblong Pyrex baking dish, melt in oven.
Sprinkle rice over bottom of dish. Add
chicken, salted to taste.
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix
over chicken.
Pour water over mixture.
Spread cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake for 1 hour to 1 1/2 hours.

title: swedish slaw
directions: Layer cabbage and onions in large bowl.
Heat to boiling:
sugar, vinegar, oil and spices.
Pour over cabbage and onions, covering all of top.
Cover, chill overnight or several hours.

title: amish yum-a-setta
directions: Brown hamburger with salt, pepper, brown sugar and onion. Add tomato soup.
Cook egg noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Layer hamburger mixture & noodle mixture in a 13 X 9 inch casserole with cheese between layers.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: thyme carrot soup
directions: Combine chicken stock, carrots and onions.
Bring to a boil. Simmer 20 minutes.
Puree along with 1/2 cup heavy cream.
Add thyme, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 5 minutes.
Garnish with fresh thyme.
Serves six.

title: lively lemon roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt margarine.
Add lemon juice, salt and pepper.
In bowl combine rice, broccoli, cheese and 1/4 cup lemon sauce; mix well.
Divide broccoli mixture equally among fillets.
Roll up and place, seam side down, in shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over roll-ups.
Bake 25 minutes or until fish flakes with fork.
Spoon sauce over individual servings.
Garnish with paprika.

title: unstuffed cabbage
directions: Crumble beef into a 4 to 5-quart Dutch oven; add onion and cook over medium heat for 5 to 6 minutes.
Stir often until meat is browned.
Quarter and core cabbage.
Cut crosswise in 1-inch wide strips.
You should have about 8 cups.
Add to meat mixture, cover and cook over medium heat, about 5 to 7 minutes until cabbage wilts.
Stir in tomatoes, sugar, vinegar and salt.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Serves 4.
(Serve over rice or noodles.)

title: turkey dressing
directions: Cut up pepper, onion, celery and eggs.
Mix all together with remaining ingredients and stuff turkey.
Cover turkey.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° or until lightly browned.

title: orange icebox cake
directions: Boil 2 cups water, sugar and marshmallows 20 minutes.
Soak gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water for 5 minutes.
Add to boiling syrup.
Add lemon and orange juice and pulp and chill.
When nearly set, fold in whipped cream.
Line a souffle dish or spring-form pan with oiled paper.
Separate ladyfingers and place around edge.
Pour in mixture and place remaining ladyfingers on top.
Chill thoroughly.
Turn out on serving dish and garnish with whipped cream and mandarin oranges.

title: jezebel
directions: Combine all ingredients; blend well.
Put in jelly jars and refrigerate.
Will keep indefinitely.
It can be poured over cream cheese and eaten on crackers.
Or as a meat sauce.

title: cavettelli and broccoli
directions: Boil cavettelli as per package; do same with broccoli.
In large skillet, heat oil.
Saute chopped scallions and garlic.
Add chicken broth and simmer.
Sprinkle with basil, parsley, oregano, salt and pepper.
Add cavettelli and broccoli to skillet; mix all together.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: super shrimp dip
directions: Blend shrimp and cream cheese in a bowl with a fork (if mixture is too thick, add small amounts of milk until creamy).
Add small amounts of lemon juice, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce to taste.
Heavy style chips, like Ruffles are best.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients by beating with rotary beater.
Beat or shake well, just before serving.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and egg.
Sift flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt into creamed mixture.
Roll into small balls.
In a dish, mix 1 tablespoon sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg. Roll the balls around in sugar mixture.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: microwave apple crisp
directions: Butter 8-inch microwave dish and fill with apples, cinnamon and water.
Mix sugar, flour and butter.
Spread over apples in dish.
Bake 9 minutes on High in microwave.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg and cinnamon for a "browned" look.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together first 2 ingredients and put in 9 x 13-inch dish. Mix together 10x sugar, margarine, cream cheese and vanilla and put on first layer. Add rest of ingredients in layers. Refrigerate. When serving, you can top with cherries.

title: shrimp salad
directions: In a saucepan, bring water to a boil; add peas, cover and cook for 2 minutes. Drain.

Place peas in ice water; drain and pat dry. In a large bowl, combine shrimp, rice, onion, red pepper, parsley and snow peas. In a small jar, combine lemon juice, soy sauce, canola oil, sesame oil, ginger and garlic. Shake well and pour over shrimp mixture. Toss to coat.

title: meat loaf
directions: Put all in mixing bowl and mix with your hands until the ingredients are well blended. Shape into loaf. Cover with sauce.

title: fruit roll
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Divide into 3 equal portions.
Roll each into an 11-inch log.
Roll each log in powdered sugar until firm.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices, reshaping slices if necessary.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Combine Eagle Brand and water.
Add pudding mix; beat well. Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Cover bottom of 2 1/2-quart glass serving dish with vanilla wafers.
Top with sliced bananas.
Top with 1/3 of pudding mix.
Repeat layering 2 times ending with pudding.
Cover.
Chill in refrigerator.
Serve.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in margarine until tender.
Stir in flour.
Remove from heat and add the rest of the ingredients saving 1/2 cup cheese.
Pour into a greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Top with remaining cheese and let stand five minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 good servings.

title: instant cheeseburgers
directions: Brown ground beef in pan.
Add onions to beef during last 5 minutes to allow them to cook somewhat.
Drain in sieve, pressing with paper towels to remove all fat.
Cool very well and mix in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.
When ready to eat, spread on buns, or bread and heat well.
Can also put between buns, wrap and freeze to eat for a quick meal.
Good to take to work and pop in microwave.

title: black iron kettle old-fashion beef stew
directions: Put oil in bottom of kettle, enough so the beef cubes, onions and potatoes won't burn.
Brown beef, onions and potatoes.
Add carrots, peas, celery and a little water and cook slowly for 1 hour or until done.
Season with blend of herbs.
Then add soups.

title: twenty-four hour salad
directions: Shred the lettuce into the bottom of a clear deep glass bowl. Add the vegetables in layers, as listed.
Mix the sour cream and mayonnaise and add as top layer, covering everything.
Seal top of bowl with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Top generously with Bac*Os before serving.
For color, carrot curls may be added with the Bac*Os.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar, baking soda and sour cream. Then add the lemon extract, vanilla, eggs and flour.

title: beef, cheese and noodle casserole
directions: Heat oil;
add onion.
Cook until golden.
Add meat and brown. Add
spaghetti
sauce,
salt
and
pepper to taste and heat.
Use 2
quart buttered casserole and put in half of the noodles, half of the sauce, half of the cheese.
Repeat.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This is very good!

title: cheese danish
directions: Press 1 package crescent rolls to the bottom of an ungreased pan.
Push together at perforations.
Mix ingredients and spread on crescent rolls.
Lay 1 package of crescent rolls on top. Do not push perforations together.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; add broth to Stove Top and margarine.
Let set until broth is absorbed.
Layer broccoli and chicken.
Mix gravy, mushrooms and wine or apple juice.
Pour over casserole.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix 3/4 cup sugar, flour, salt and cocoa well.
Add milk, egg yolks and vanilla.
Mix well.
Cook on medium heat until thick. Beat 2 egg whites with 2 tablespoons sugar until stiff.
Pour chocolate mixture into baked pie shell.
Put stiffened egg whites on top.
Brown in a 325° oven.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; let cool.
Add drained pineapple and pie filling.
Add enough water to reserved pineapple juice to make 3/4 cup and add to mixture.
Chill until set.

title: cape cod fish chowder
directions: Saute onion until tender in butter.
Add potatoes, salt, pepper, basil and water.
Cover.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Place fish cut in chunks over mixture and simmer 15 minutes or unit fish flakes.
Add 1 can (12 ounce) whole kernel corn and 12 ounce can evaporated milk or little cream.
Heat just to boil.
Serve in soup bowls with chowder crackers.
Add parsley for color.

title: 5 day coconut cake
directions: *Two layers baked and each layer sliced in half, making 4 thin layers (cooled).

title: hoppin' john
directions: Cook peas until 2/3 done.
Add other ingredients.
Stir often and add water as necessary, to make pot liquor.

title: cheesecake
directions: Soak raisins in hot water for 15 minutes.
Pat dry and coat with 2 tablespoons of flour.
Set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°. Beat the egg whites and salt until stiff.
Place the egg white mixture in the freezer for 5 minutes.
Combine the cheese, sugar, egg yolks and remaining flour; beat until smooth.
Stir in the raisins and lemon peel.
Carefully fold in the egg whites.
Pour the mixture into a greased and floured 9-inch spring-form pan. Bake for 45 minutes, then turn the oven off and leave the cake in the oven until it cools.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and pat in the bottom and up the sides of a long Pyrex dish.

title: crust for no bake pies
directions: Melt margarine; mix in all ingredients.
Press into pie pan. Bake until lightly browned for 20 minutes at 325°.
Let cool. Great for pudding pies.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In saucepan, put 3 teaspoons margarine and saute onion and celery.
Add small can of evaporated milk, 1 can cream of chicken soup and 1/2 cup Minute rice.
Cook 1 minute and then add 2/3 jar of Cheez Whiz.
Break broccoli apart and pour mixture over broccoli.
Put mushrooms on top and add almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Mix and spread on top of party rye or pumpernickel bread.
Top with a thin slice of cucumber.
Sprinkle with dill weed.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large bowl, mix together the ground beef, egg, water, bread crumbs and minced onion. Roll into small meatballs. Bake in preheated oven for 20 to 25 minutes, turning once. In a slow cooker or large saucepan over low heat, blend the cranberry sauce, chili sauce, brown sugar and lemon juice. Add meatballs and simmer for 1 hour before serving.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and cut in shortening.
Add milk to make a soft dough.
Place on floured board and knead lightly a few seconds.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick and cut with floured biscuit cutter.
Rolled on greased baking pan and bake in very hot oven (450°) about 12 minutes.
Makes 14 biscuits.

title: quick one-dish meal
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Drain green beans.
Place beans in casserole; top with meat.
Pour mushroom soup over meat.
Place biscuits on top; bake at 350° until biscuits are brown.
Serves 4.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and roll portions in cabbage leaves, fasten with toothpicks.
In bottom of large cooker place 2 cans kraut and then cabbage rolls on top.
Add 2 cans of tomato juice and enough water to cover.
Cook 4 hours.

title: salmon-rice pie
directions: Bring rice to boil in salted water; cover and simmer 14 minutes.
Mix with fork and stir in margarine and 1 beaten egg. Place in 9-inch pie pan sprayed with vegetable pan spray.
Press against sides and bottom of pan to make crust.
Spread salmon evenly over rice.
Heat milk and peas to simmer.
Add seasonings. Beat remaining egg.
Gradually stir in milk mixture.
Pour over salmon.
Layer slices of cheese over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: chautauqua chicken lush
directions: Thoroughly mix the first 5 ingredients and spread evenly in a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Scatter chips over the chicken mixture.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika and top with almonds. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pudding salad
directions: Mix pudding and 1 cup milk and let stand.
Drain pineapple and add Cool Whip, pecans and pineapple to pudding.
Stir in marshmallows.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix together and cook until thick.
Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and cooked custard.
Repeat layers again.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Boil together first 3 ingredients until broccoli changes color.
Add evaporated milk.
Melt oleo; add flour.
Mix well. Add to soup.
Cook to desired thickness.

title: applesauce-oat muffins
directions: Mix cereal, flour, brown sugar and cinnamon in a large bowl. Stir in remaining ingredients just until moistened.
Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms only of 12 medium muffin cups.
Bake until golden brown, 18 to 22 minutes.

title: rocky mountain blueberry muffins
directions: Stir milk and oil into egg.
Add dry ingredients; stir until just moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Batter should be lumpy. Fill greased muffins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 12 muffins.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate in top of a double boiler.
Cool. Combine eggs and sugar, beating thoroughly.
Add to chocolate mixture.
Stir in flour, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: stripe-it-rich cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, baking in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Remove from oven.
Poke holes quickly down through the cake with a round handle of a wooden spoon or plastic drinking straw, using a turning motion to make large holes.
Holes should be at 1-inch intervals.

title: brunch potatoes
directions: Cook, peel and chop potatoes and stir together soup, sour cream, cream cheese and butter buds.
Add 1/2 of shredded cheese and scallions.
Add milk, parsley, garlic and pepper.
Stir to combine.
Stir all together with potatoes.
Put mixture in an 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Spread the remaining ingredients over top and bake 5 minutes more.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: harvey's bean casserole
directions: Brown and drain fat from beef, bacon and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
For less sauce, drain some of the juice off canned beans.
Place in large covered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes and onions alternately in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Combine melted butter, salt, pepper, celery seed, paprika and garlic; pour over potatoes and onions in casserole.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Remove cover; continue baking 20 minutes more to brown.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: In large bowl, combine eggs and sugar, beating well.
Add pumpkin and lemon juice; mix until blended.
In separate bowl, combine flour, baking powder, spices and salt.
Add to egg mixture, mixing well.
Spread batter into greased and waxed paper lined 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.

title: french pancakes
directions: Sift the first 4 ingredients. Beat the eggs, milk and vanilla or lemon rind.
Make a well in the sifted ingredients.
Pour in liquid ingredients. Combine with a few swift strokes.
Ignore lumps. Cook over moderate heat (350°) in frypan with a few drops of oil, turning only once.

title: italian sausage heros
directions: In 10-inch skillet, over medium heat, heat sausages and water to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes.
Uncover; cook about 15 minutes, until water is evaporated and sausages are browned, turning occasionally.
Remove and keep warm.

title: red tomato relish
directions: Cook for 1 hour after it comes to a boil.
Seal in hot jars.

title: overnight brunch casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish with Pam cooking spray. Sprinkle 3 cups of shredded cheese evenly into dish. Melt margarine in medium skillet over medium heat. Saute onions, bell pepper and mushrooms in margarine until tender. Arrange vegetables over cheese in baking dish. Top vegetables with ham strips and sprinkle remaining cheese over ham strips. Beat eggs in separate large bowl. Beat in flour, parsley and milk. Blend well and pour over mixture in baking dish. Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cream butter, sugar and beaten eggs. Fold in pineapple and bread crumbs. Add cream; mix carefully. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: beef sticks
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and refrigerate for 24 hours. Shape into rolls and bake in 300° oven on broiler pan.
Grease drips through to bottom of broiler pan.

title: sweet and sour cabbage with tomatoes
directions: Shred cabbage as for cole slaw.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Pour off all but about 4 tablespoons of bacon drippings.
Mix all ingredients together and simmer 1 1/2 hours on low heat.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Stew 2 chicken breasts.
Make filling as for stuffed fowl.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions.
Cool.
Tear half of cake into pieces in large bowl (use punch bowl).
Prepare pudding using the 3 1/2 cups milk.
Pour 1/4 cup Kahlua over cake pieces, then spread half the pudding over cake.
Then spread half the Cool Whip over pudding and then sprinkle half the candy over Cool Whip.
Layer remaining cake, Kahlua, pudding and Cool Whip. Top with remaining candy.

title: soupe a la biere douce
directions: Simmer beer, lemon rind, cinnamon and ginger.
Mix corn flour and cold water to a smooth paste.
Add a few spoonfuls of the hot beer and then add the corn flour mixture to the beer in the saucepan.
Cook soup gently.
Mix egg yolks and milk together and away from heat, add to the soup in the pan.
Heat thoroughly without boiling.
Serve with slices of fried bread.

title: kookie bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Press cookie dough into ungreased 9 x 13 pan.
Press 1/2 cup of pecans into dough.
Pour caramel topping over crust.
In medium bowl, combine flour, peanut butter, sugar, egg and vanilla; stir with fork until well blended and coarsely crumbled.
Sprinkle over caramel topping and press down.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove pan from oven and cool 5 minutes. Spread with frosting; sprinkle with 1/2 cup pecans.
Freeze for 30 minutes; cut into bars.

title: reese's cup squares
directions: Melt margarine, add peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Spread chocolate in double boiler.
Spread over peanut butter mixture. Chill at least 30 minutes.
Allow to rest a few minutes after removing from refrigerator before cutting into small squares. Store in refrigerator.

title: chocolate fudge sauce
directions: Blend in saucepan the chocolate, milk, sugar and flour.
Cook until mixture is thick, then add butter and vanilla.
Serve hot.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Store in an airtight container.
Use 2 heaping teaspoonfuls (more or less to taste) for each cup of boiling water.
Simmer.
Makes about 30 servings.

title: oven roasted vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a plastic bag or bowl, shake or toss all ingredients until vegetables are coated.
Empty into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Discard bag.
Bake, stirring once, 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 4 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: fisherman's scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Peel potatoes and cut into 1/4's.
Fine chop garlic.
Place 1/2 of potatoes in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Add onion, salt, pepper and thyme on top.
Add remaining potatoes. Pour oil on top.
Bake, covered, 1 hour.

title: frosted pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add pumpkin and egg. Mix flour, soda, cinnamon and salt and mix this into the creamed mixture.
Stir in the butterscotch bits, nuts and raisins.
Spoon the cookie dough onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: 3 cheese ball
directions: Leave cheese at room temperature for about 2 hours.
Place all ingredients, except nuts, in a mixing bowl.
Beat with mixer until all ingredients are thoroughly combined.
Shape into a ball; roll in chopped nuts.
Wrap in waxed paper or plastic wrap; refrigerate.

title: david's bouillabaisse
directions: In Dutch oven, pour olive oil and cook over moderate heat. When hot, add garlic and cook 15 seconds.
Add 1/2 of fish mixture, the clams, wine, tomatoes, oregano, salt and pepper. Cook over high heat; simmer for 1 minute.
Lower heat; cover and cook 2 minutes.
Add remaining fish; stir gently for 2 more minutes.
Stir in parsley.
Serve with garlic bread.
Serves 4.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine melted butter or margarine with brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Continue boiling, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in baking soda.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in refrigerator until chilled.
Drop by teaspoonful in deep hot grease.

title: corn bread
directions: Stir water into ingredients quickly.
Add the eggs, butter and milk.
Bake in greased baking pan or casserole 1 hour at 400°.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Press shredded zucchini dry between paper towels.
Put into large mixing bowl.
Stir in flour, cheese, oregano, basil and pepper.
Add mayonnaise and eggs.
Mix well.
Pour a thin layer of oil in skillet to cover base.
Heat over medium heat.
When oil is hot, spoon 2 tablespoons batter into a 2-inch diameter in skillet. Fry until golden brown on both sides, approximately 3 minutes a side.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Steam vegetables until just tender in the following groups: cauliflower, broccoli, carrots, mushrooms and zucchini, bell pepper.
Meanwhile, combine olive oil, garlic, salt, pepper and herbs in a large bowl.
Add the steamed vegetables (okay if still hot).
Mix well.
Stir in vinegar within 30 minutes of serving to retain bright vegetable colors.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: reception salad
directions: Strain pineapple, heat the juice and mix with jello.
When partially firm, add other ingredients and allow to stand until firm.
Serve on lettuce.

title: spicy kielbasa
directions: Place ingredients (except kielbasa) in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes, then simmer for 10 minutes.
Place sauce in crock-pot and add kielbasa.
Slow cook for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Cook onion and hamburger; drain.
Put hamburger in an 8 x 10-inch casserole dish.
Pour 2 cans of tomato paste over hamburger.
Place cooked macaroni on top of tomato paste. Sprinkle grated cheese over macaroni.
Pour pinto beans over top of cheese mixture.
Mix up enough cornbread batter to cover this and pour over this and bake at 375° until bread is done.
You can use the size of dish that you want.

title: microwave brown sugar pecan coffee cake
directions: Place margarine in 6-cup ring dish.
Microwave, uncovered, on High, about 45 seconds or until melted.
Sprinkle brown sugar and pecans evenly over margarine.
Microwave, uncovered, 45 seconds to 1 minute, or until hot and bubbly.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Cook apples in water until soft and all the water has cooked away.
Mash and add sugar.

title: no-meat stuffed green peppers
directions: Wash peppers.
Cut slice from stem end and remove seeds.
Cover with boiling salted water.
Boil, uncovered, 3 to 5 minutes; drain. Halve lengthwise.
Brown onion in butter; add poultry seasoning, rice, salt and pepper.
Fill peppers with rice mixture.
Place in baking dish with a small amount of water.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: italian american casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper in a large skillet.
Boil macaroni in a large pot.
To the ground meat, add tomato sauce, tomatoes, corn, parsley, oregano, chili powder, garlic powder, salt, pepper and jalapeno, if desired.
Let mixture simmer on low about 30 minutes, so that it is fairly thick.
Drain macaroni. Mix macaroni with the meat mixture.
Stir well.
Arrange cheese on top, so that it covers all the meat.
Cover and let cheese melt.

title: hot spice tea for diabetics
directions: Mix 6 ounces boiling water with 1 1/2 teaspoons mixture.
Can keep dry mixture in sealed container and use as needed.
Should yield approximately 50 servings.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Combine sugar, eggs and flour.
Add butter and milk; pour into prepared pie shell.
Put 1/2 cup coconut on each pie.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes and 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: beer bread(to be made in a bread oven)
directions: To flatten beer, bring to room temperature.
Pour from glass to glass until bubbles disappear.
Put all the ingredients in, in order listed.
Use the Basic Bake setting.

title: mini-cheesecake
directions: Line
muffin
tin with liners.	Place one vanilla wafer in each
liner.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla and sugar on medium speed until
well
blended.
Add	eggs.
Mix well.
Pour over wafers, filling 3/4 full.
Bake
minutes at 325°.
Add any kind of fruit filling as topping.

title: fudge cake
directions: Spray and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Test with toothpick.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Use 2 cups salt for 3 gallons of cucumbers.
Let stay 9 days. Wash and slice. Cover with alum water (a 10 cent can).
Let stay 24 hours. Wash and cover with vinegar.
Let stay 24 hours. Drain and put a layer of cucumbers and a layer of sugar.
Use gallon jug to pack pickles in.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Dip chicken in sour cream and coat well with cracker crumbs. Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: noodles alfredo al dente
directions: Add egg to butter and cream.
Pour over noodles.
Toss with cheese.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Mix thoroughly in bowl first 4 ingredients.
Stir together in another bowl the dry ingredients.
Mix dry ingredients into shortening mixture.
Chill dough in refrigerator for 2 hours or overnight.

title: no shortening pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together flour and sugar in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour mixture into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in the middle comes out clean.
Cool completely before topping.

title: nannie mae brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 450° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: Melt margarine; add peanut butter, then add 10x sugar and Rice Krispies.
Form eggs.
Refrigerate overnight or couple of hours. Melt in double boiler the chocolate and paraffin.
Dip the eggs into chocolate.
Lay eggs on waxed paper until chocolate is hard.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Grease 9x13 baking dish. In a bowl beat butter and sugar. Then beat in one egg at a time. Blend in corn, chilies and both cheeses. In another bowl stir flour, cornmeal, baking powder, salt and pepper. Mix both mixes together; pour in dish and bake 1 hour.

title: kansas chowder
directions: Slightly brown hamburger; pour off fat.
In another pot, cook vegetables until soft in as little water as you can; don't drain water from vegetables.
Add meat and Cheddar cheese soup; cover and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: orange fluff
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender and chill for several hours in the refrigerator before using.
Excellent with all types of cut-up fruits.

title: poppy seed cake with caramel topping
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: pineapple refrigerator dessert
directions: Cream sugar and butter at medium speed for 5 minutes.
Add egg yolks, blend well.
Add pineapple and cream to mixture.
Cook over hot water until thick.
Cool.
Add nuts and cherries.
Place a thin layer in bottom of 12 x 2-inch pan.
Fill pan with alternate third layers; fruit mixture and crushed wafers.
Refrigerate overnight. Serve with whipped cream.
Serves 50.

title: chess cake
directions: Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Do not grease pan.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Soak crumbs in cream, then add rest of ingredients; mix thoroughly until smooth.
Shape into small balls about 1 inch. Fry in butter or olive oil until evenly brown or bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain oil from meatballs, then cover, about half, with a good dry white wine, simmering at a low heat until most of the wine is boiled away.
Serve hot or cold.

title: baked chicken loaf
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Combine with rest of ingredients.
Bake in buttered loaf pan set in hot water for 1 hour.
Serve with Pimento Mushroom Sauce.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix well.
Bake in loaf pans at 350° until done, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, and cinnamon.
fold into creamed mixture.
Add coconut, nuts, apples, and vanilla.
Mix and pour into 9 x 13 pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: seven seas casserole
directions: In saucepan, combine soup, water, onion, salt and pepper. Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix in uncooked Minute rice, peas and tuna. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheese appetizer
directions: Beat egg whites stiff; add cheese, cayenne and bread crumbs. Pat into small balls and fry in hot deep fat (375°) until light brown.
Makes about 16 balls.

title: chocolate caramels
directions: Put all in saucepan and when it comes to a boil, time it and let it boil just 8 minutes.
Take from fire; add 1/4 pound of butter and 2 tablespoons vanilla.
Beat until quite stiff. Pour into buttered tins and cut in squares.

title: jalapeno sauce
directions: Mix together.
Great as a dip or on a sandwich.

title: ruby's chicken pot pie
directions: Cook potato and carrot about 15 minutes in boiling water to cover.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Add potato and carrot and mix well.
Pour into pie shells and bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
In a saucepan, combine juice with sugar, cranberries, raisins and spices.
Cook 15 minutes or until boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 25 to 30 minutes until cranberries are tender.
Add pineapple and nuts; mix well. Refrigerate for at least 4 hours, until chilled.

title: white jello
directions: Mix sugar, gelatine, salt and water over medium heat, stirring constantly, until dissolved.
Put in large bowl until partially set.
Add beaten egg whites (should be stiff) and lemon juice and beat until fluffy.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in sour cream and whipped whip cream.
Put in mold and set.
Serve with strawberries or other fresh fruit.

title: golden cheddar turkey bake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix lightly.
Spoon into 8 x 10-inch baking dish.
Toss corn flake mixture over casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 35 minutes.
Add additional cheese if desired.
May be used
as a salad instead; omit the corn flakes. Add green grapes and refrigerate.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and noodles separately.
Mix cheese, cooked noodles, meat and sauce together in a casserole dish.
Top with pepperoni and cheese.
Bake
at 350° until bubbly.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet; add salt to taste.
Place chops on top of rice in deep casserole.
Put a thick slice of onion and a slice of raw tomato or 1/3 cup canned tomatoes on each chop. Add a ring of green pepper.
Add tomato juice or bouillon to skillet in which chops have been browned.
Add thyme and marjoram to liquid.
Pour liquid to casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter crunch pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and syrup until thoroughly combined.
Add cereal; stir until well coated.
With the back of a tablespoon, press mixture evenly and firmly in bottom and around sides of lightly buttered 9-inch pie pan forming crust.
Chill until firm. Spread ice cream evenly in cooled crust; freeze until firm.

title: chocolate and butterscotch fudge(microwave)
directions: Line an 8-inch square pan with foil.
In small microwave-safe bowl, place butterscotch chips and 1/3 cup sweetened condensed milk.
Set aside.

title: skillet chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in ovenproof skillet.
Stir in flour.
Cook 1 minute until smooth and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir in chicken broth.
Cook until mixture thickens and boils, stirring constantly.
Stir in pepper and sour cream.
Stir in vegetables, chicken and onion.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Place biscuits on top of hot chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until biscuits are brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: franks and sauerkraut
directions: Put in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake, covered, at 350°, for 20 minutes until heated thoroughly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together and bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and mix until everything is combined.
If electric beaters are used, beat about 10 minutes. Refrigerate for flavors to blend.
Shake before using.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: venison chuck roast
directions: Butter a casserole dish.
Place onion slices in bottom of dish.
Place roast on onions.
Add cloves, bay leaf and rosemary and place around meat.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour beer over roast.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake in 325° oven for 2 1/2 hours or longer, until tender.

title: molded salad
directions: Put 2 cups hot water in Jell-O.
Let set and cool.
Mix rest of the ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Stir occasionally.
Put in refrigerator.
Let set like Jell-O.

title: homespun-meat pie
directions: Combine meat, mushrooms, egg, onion, bread crumbs and seasonings; mix lightly.
Press meat mixture onto bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Remove meat shell from oven.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Drain excess fat from meat shell.
Mash hot potatoes with milk.
Stir in process cheese, parsley and salt.
Fill hot meat shell with potato mixture.
Bake for 10 minutes.
