Makes 6 servings.

title: brown rice and mushrooms
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, melt butter, then add rice, soups and mushrooms.
Cover and cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts.
Shape into ball and roll in finely chopped nuts.
Wrap in waxed paper and store in refrigerator.
Serve with crackers.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add eggs. Mix well. Add milk and vanilla. Combine with flour, then nuts and fruits. Divide mixture into 2 parts. Cook first half parts in 2 round cake pans. While the layers are cooking, mix other half mixture with the cocoa and pumpkin spice. Pour this mixture into 2 cake pans and bake. Best let to set for a couple of days before adding topping mixture. Bring to a boil and let boil for 4 minutes the coconut, sugar and water. Start with a chocolate layer and spread some of topping. Then top with white layer and top with topping until all 4 layers have been used and topping spread. This makes a tall cake. Decorate with pecan halves and red and green cherries. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes per layer or until done.

title: taffy apple pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Roll dough out flat onto a stone or rectangular baking dish.
Bake 16 to 18 minutes or until brown. Cool 10 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, brown sugar, peanut butter and vanilla.
Spread mixture evenly over cookie.
Peel, core and slice apples into small pieces.
Arrange apples over mixture. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Heat caramel sauce and drizzle over apples.
Sprinkle chopped peanuts over the top.
Cut and serve.

title: california cheese soup
directions: In a large kettle, bring water to a boil.
Add all vegetables and bouillon cubes.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Add soup and cheese.
Stir until blended.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Prepare jello according to directions and chill until thickened.
Mix the remaining ingredients together and stir them into the thickened jello.
Chill until set.

title: carbanara ala carolyn
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain.
Cook Canadian bacon until hot; drain.
Toss hot spaghetti with enough hot bacon grease to keep spaghetti from sticking.
Toss in bacon, eggs and onions, half cheese and salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with remaining cheese on the side and French bread.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water.
Blend in flour.
Add cinnamon, nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: aunt annie oates sugar cookies(heritage)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, salt, baking powder, flour and vanilla.
Work into several balls.
Chill in refrigerator for one hour.
Roll on well floured board.
Cut into desired shapes. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mrs. shaw's cheese rice krispies
directions: Have cheese and oleo at room temperature.
Mix in mixer until fluffy.
Add flour, Rice Krispies, sauce and seasoning.
Mix well. Pick up small amount with hands and roll into ball.
Mash flat with fork.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Watch carefully.

title: miss elly's bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers thin.
Put into pot.
Sprinkle with salt.
Let stand overnight.
Drain.
Mix vinegar and all other ingredients in same pot.
Mix and add cucumbers and onions.
Stir with wooden spoon until it comes to a boil (do not boil).
Ladle into 4 or 5 pint size jars.
Seal securely.

title: all occasion punch
directions: In
large
chilled
punch bowl, combine punch, lemon 'n lime and
orange
juice	concentrates.
Mix well.
Slowly add 7-Up. Add
ice cubes. Float orange slices on top. Makes about 5 gallons.

title: chicken cordon bleu casserole
directions: Prepare Stove Top stuffing according to package and set aside. Line pan with raw chicken breasts.
Cover with ham slices.
Top with cheese (use lots).
Cover with soup, then cover with stuffing. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and chill.

title: crab casserole
directions: Melt butter in top part of double boiler; add flour, salt and pepper.
Cook until bubbly.
Slowly add milk; stir briskly.
Cook over hot water until thick and smooth, stirring occasionally. Continue cooking for about 5 minutes.
Add egg yolks, then onion, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir in crabmeat.
Pour mixture into 1-quart casserole dish.
Cover with buttered breadcrumbs. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: southern biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix softened butter with flour mixture. Add buttermilk. Knead dough on floured surface 4 or 5 times.
Roll dough out and cut biscuits.
Put on buttered tray and cook in oven, preheated at 450°, until brown.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Saute meat and onion; drain.
Add chilies, taco sauce and soup to meat mixture.
Tear tortillas in half in 9 x 11-inch baking dish.
Pour 1/2 meat mixture over tortillas.
Repeat layers and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine butter, sugar, syrup, eggs, vanilla and salt.
Add pecans.
Put in pie shell.
Cook at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Let cool before serving.

title: pink party punch
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in punch bowl.
Add raspberry sherbet. Have all ingredients cold.
Serves 50.

title: three cheese ball
directions: Leave cheese at room temperature for approximately 2 hrs. Place all ingredients except nuts in a mixing bowl.
Whip with mixer until all ingredients are thoroughly combined.
Shape into a ball and roll in chopped nuts.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate until completely chilled.

title: hardy tuna salad
directions: Cook beans according to directions, drain and cool.
Combine beans, tuna and celery.
Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice, soy sauce and garlic powder; add to salad, toss well and chill.
Before serving, add noodles and mix well.

title: candied nuts
directions: Mix the sugar, cinnamon and milk mixture. Boil to a soft ball stage.
Add the nuts.
Be very careful, will scorch easily.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix as for cornbread.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until coarse crumbs.
Add milk, stir until flour is moist.
On lightly floured surface roll into 18 x 12-inch rectangle.
Place apples on dough. Sprinkle apples with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Roll and cut as for cinnamon rolls.
Place one inch apart on ungreased baking pan. Pour syrup over dumplings.
Bake at 375 for one hour or until apples are done.
Serve warm with cream or ice cream.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, including 1/4 cup reserved liquid.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugars, shortening and eggs until light.
Add applesauce, mixing well.
Spoon flour measured with the soda, baking powder, salt and spices to flour, not sifted, stir well to blend.
Add blended dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with water, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Stir in fruit and nuts, blend well.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Dust with powdered sugar to serve, or frost with Penuche Frosting.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; gradually add eggs, then banana and vanilla.
Fold in dry ingredients that have been sifted together. Add nuts.
Bake in a buttered loaf pan at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes; turn out of pan to cool completely.
Serve sliced and spread with butter.

title: lemon cake
directions: Beat together for a full 4 minutes in mixer.
Grease and flour a large 13 x 10-inch pan.
Bake as directed on cake mix box at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
When baked, while hot, poke holes in cake with cooking fork, ice pick or toothpick and pour the following (mixed) over the cake:

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken in 2 quarts water with 1 teaspoon salt until it leaves bone (approximately 2 hours).
Save broth.
Pick from bone and skin and layer on bottom of pans.
Chicken can be prepared and refrigerated a day ahead.
Saute onion, mushrooms and celery in butter until celery is transparent.
Add this mixture and enough broth to remaining ingredients until well mixed.
Pour over chicken and add broth until soupy.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Baste during baking if dressing gets dry.
Two 8-inch square pans or equivalent.
Dry bread cubes in pan if unsure of size.
This casserole is better the second day.

title: spinach with sour cream
directions: Cook spinach in small amount of water with onion until spinach is thawed.
Beat eggs and mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased casserole for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients well in small bowl.
Cook potatoes in boiling water for 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain, cool, peel and chop potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients; add dressing and toss gently.
Chill in covered bowl.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: dennis' fried chicken
directions: Heat oil and oleo until hot.
Put dry ingredients in bag and shake well.
Add chicken and shake again.
Place in hot skillet and brown on both sides, then lower heat and cook until done. Just before taking off, turn heat up high for 3 to 5 minutes. Serve hot or cold.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix together and pour into 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: curried chicken
directions: Boil or bake chicken.
Skin and debone.
Dice chicken.
Saute onion, garlic and apple in oleo.
Add soup.
Season with curry powder, white pepper and cayenne.
Serve on a bed of white rice, saffron or yellow rice.
You may also season with "7 box condiments" (coconut, raisins, peanuts, green onions, chutney, toasted almonds or crumbled bacon).

title: snicker bars
directions: Mix and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: There is an old story about a man who lived a long and worthy life.
When he died, the Lord said to him, "Come, I will show you Hell."

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add applesauce, then sifted dry ingredients.
Beat smooth and fold in raisins, if desired.
Bake at 350° in a tube pan for 1 hour or until done.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix and boil together sugar, cocoa, stick of butter and milk. Boil for 2 minutes; may use microwave.
Cover bowl with cling wrap if microwaved.
Add and stir well into boiled mixture the peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Drop by spoonfuls onto foil to cool.

title: chocolate nut - butter bars
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and one of the eggs in a large mixing bowl.
Beat until mixture is crumbly.
Press evenly into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Beat remaining egg with the sweetened condensed milk in a small bowl until well blended.
Pour over crumb mixture crust.
Sprinkle chocolate pieces and nuts on top. Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.

title: wiener boats
directions: Preheat oven at 400°.
Cut wieners in half lengthwise, but not all the way through.
Press open to make "boat".
Spoon mashed potatoes into boats equally.
Cover tops with shredded cheese. Put in oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: almond joy candy
directions: Combine sugar, Karo and water.
Cook over medium heat until forms a soft ball in water, stirring constantly until dissolved. When forms soft ball, remove from heat.
Add coconut and almonds or nuts.
Let cool.
When cool, shape into balls.
Lay on cookie sheet.
Refrigerate for cooling, then dip into chocolate.

title: potatoes in foil(shared by sandy and john connor)
directions: You will also need heavy-duty aluminum foil (2).

title: frosted potato salad
directions: Cube potatoes
and slice eggs into a bowl.
Combine all other ingredients
and
add to mixture.
Add enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Chill.
This salad is very attractive when packed into a mold and served on greens.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: Combine
in
deep
narrow
bowl Dream Whip, pudding and cold milk.
Blend then beat at high speed to soft peaks 4 to 6 minutes. Makes 3
cups
or
enough
for
a 2-layer cake. Store frosted cake in refrigerator.

title: mexican bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Pour half of mixture into greased 10-inch square container.
Spread half of cheese on top. Spread remaining mixture on top, ending with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until done.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: salami wrap-ups
directions: You will need fancy toothpicks.

title: quick and easy peach pie
directions: Whip cream cheese; add sugar, sour cream, and vanilla. When smooth, fold in Cool Whip. Put into crust. Chill.

title: scrumptious breakfast burrito
directions: Scramble eggs. When almost done, add chopped up chicken. Mix well.

title: kentucky pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add syrup and beat well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla, melted butter and then pecans last.
Pour into 2 deep pie shells.
Bake at 325° until solid.
Yields 12 servings.
Preparation time is 45 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix together and put in baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: fresh peach ice cream
directions: Use blender to mix the ingredients and pour mixture into freezer.
Put 1 quart fresh peaches into blender and blend.
Pour these into freezer and add additional milk to the fill line on your freezer.
Freeze and enjoy.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Mix egg yolks, sugar and butter together.
Mix candy in (save some to go on top).
Mix in Cool Whip.
Pinch cake up in bottom of pan.
Pour rest of candy on top.

title: peach melba pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Mix peaches, raspberries, sugar, tapioca and lemon juice in large bowl. Let sit 15 minutes. Roll one-half of the pastry to an 11-inch circle (about 2 inches larger than pie plate) on lightly floured surface. Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry, allowing a 1/2-inch overhang. Fill with fruit mixture. Dot with margarine. Roll remaining pastry to 12-inch circle. Cover pie with pastry; seal and flute edge. Cut slits on top to let steam escape. Bake 55 minutes or until juices form bubbles that burst slowly. Cool. Makes 8 servings.

title: french custard ice cream
directions: Scald the milk.
Add the beaten egg yolks to which the sugar has been added.
Cook over hot water like custard, stirring constantly, until the mixture coats a wooden spoon.
Chill; add the cream and vanilla and freeze in hand or electric freezer, using 4 parts ice to 1 part ice cream salt.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Simmer broccoli in water with seasoned salt for 30 minutes. Saute onion in butter, then add soup, Pet milk and cheeses.
Heat until cheese is melted.

title: rib-sticking chicken pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine chicken, vegetables, broth, onions and soups.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 pan.
Combine flour, buttermilk and margarine in a bowl, blending well.
Spoon over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until crust is golden brown.

title: beer batter for fish
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and lemon pepper together.
Add beer and stir.
Beat eggs and mix into flour mixture.
Allow fish to set in batter for 10 minutes.
Fry in deep fryer in hot oil.

title: kool-aid play doh
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil and water. Stir quickly, mixing well.
When cool, mix with your hands. Store in sealed container or plastic bag.

title: cheese and sausage muffins
directions: Mix biscuit mix and pepper. Add milk and stir slightly. Add sausage and cheese. Mixture will be thick. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: chocolate marshmallow brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add other ingredients and mix well. Bake until done.
Lay marshmallows on top and put back in oven until browned.
When cool, ice with chocolate frosting.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender and pour into two or three unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to an hour. Serves 6.

title: cold spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti into quarters, cook according to package directions. While still warm, add
remaining ingredients. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together with mixer on low speed, then on medium about 4 minutes until fluffy.
Stir in pecans.
Wrap dough in wax paper; refrigerate 2 hours or overnight.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix and form ball and then roll in crushed pecans.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 glass baking dish. Spread the dried beef in the bottom. Wrap a strip of bacon around each piece of chicken and place over beef. Mix together soup and sour cream and pour over all. Bake, covered, at 300° for 2 hours. Bake, uncovered, for the last 30 minutes.

title: squash and carrot casserole
directions: Place crumbs in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Mix all other ingredients and spoon over bread crumbs.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Cook in a 350° oven for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: cracker dessert
directions: Beat egg whites to medium consistency.
Add sugar, then add crushed crackers.
Add nuts, baking powder and vanilla.
Mix and bake 30 minutes at 350° in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch greased pan.
Cool. Over this, put Dream Whip (prepared as directed on package), cream cheese and drained pineapple.

title: cilantro corn pancakes
directions: In a large bowl, sift together the flour, baking soda, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Stir in cornmeal.
In another bowl, lightly beat eggs.
Add buttermilk, oil, corn, chiles, cilantro and scallions.
Add to dry ingredients and stir until combined. Place a griddle or skillet over medium high heat.
When hot, brush with oil, then drop batter by large tablespoonfuls onto griddle. Cook until tiny holes form on each pancake.
Turn pancakes and brown on other side.

title: french onion casserole
directions: Cook onions in 3 tablespoons margarine until tender.
Blend in flour and pepper.
Add bouillon and sherry.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Turn into casserole dish.
Toss croutons in melted butter; spoon atop onion mixture.
Sprinkle with Swiss and Parmesan cheeses.
Place under broiler until cheese melts (about 1 minute).
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6 people as a side dish.

title: date and nut cookies
directions: Cook dates, sugar and water 10 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Divide mixture (4 or 5 balls).
Roll out approximately 1/4-inch thick.
Spread date filling and roll up like jelly roll.
Put each in separate wax paper and chill overnight.

title: taco soupmidland, texas
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat.

title: pickled beets
directions: Use young tender beets.
Wash, leave 2 end of stem and boil 15 minutes in water to cover.
Dip in cold water; rub off skins.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Remove leaves from cabbage.
Dip in boiling water until wilted.
Dry leaves.
Combine the other ingredients except water and brown sugar.
Place spoonful of mixture on each leaf; roll up and tie with twine.
Brown cabbage rolls lightly in shortening. Place in casserole; sprinkle with brown sugar.
Add water and cover.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until cabbage is very tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together soup, mayonnaise, onions, almonds and chestnuts. Add rice, chicken and celery.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with buttered bread disks.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix all ingredients.
Spoon out into bottom crust.
Top with leftover crust.
Brush water over top crust and sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes. Makes 1 pie.

title: taco spread
directions: Soften cream cheese and pat on serving plate.
Layer lettuce, tomatoes, onions, celery, taco sauce and grated cheese.
Serve on chips.

title: beef stew
directions: This is for a big pot.
Cook on low heat all day.

title: original hobo bread
directions: You will need three 1 pound empty coffee cans.

title: toll house cookies
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, vanilla, water and egg.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate morsels.

title: broccoli bacon quiche
directions: Fry bacon until crisp (6 slices per quiche).
Blot real well. Crumble.
Blot broccoli real well to get out moisture.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix well.
Let
stand out of refrigerator all day after feeding (approximately 8 to
hours).
This
does not rise, only makes bubbles.
Return
to
refrigerator for 3 to 5 days. The Starter must be fed even
if
bread is not made.
Store in quart jar with holes punched in lid.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Add 1 cup of the flour to chopped fruits and mix well.
Cream butter and sugar at medium on mixer.
Add unbeaten eggs one at a time until well blended.
Add the 1 1/2 cups flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Add cake mixture to chopped fruits and nuts and mix well.

title: custard cornbread
directions: Set oven at 400°.
Place butter in a heavy 9-inch skillet and heat it in the warming oven.
Do not allow the butter to brown. Sift the dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Add the eggs and break them up with a fork, then stir in 1 cup of the milk and the buttermilk; mix with a spoon.
Pour into the skillet over the butter, do not mix.
Pour the last cup of milk over the top of the batter.
Do not stir in.
Sprinkle paprika over the top.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes until golden.
Serve warm with butter.

title: gorp
directions: In a bowl, combine oats, peanuts, nuts and wheat germ. Combine honey and oil.
Stir into oat mixture.
Spread in a jelly roll pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until light brown, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from the oven.
Let cool. Break into pieces.
Stir in candy, dried fruit and raisins.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: creamy hot corned beef dip
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large baking dish.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.
Serve hot with veggies, crackers or chips.
If you need to keep hot, place in a chafing dish over heat.

title: party punch
directions: Mix together all ingredients in punch bowl.

title: golden cheese bake
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream butter in bowl
until
light and fluffy.	Beat in sugar; beat in eggs one
at
a time.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in sour cream.
Mix
in
flour, baking soda, salt and vanilla. Beat until smooth
and
well
blended.
Fold
in
blueberries. Spread half of the batter	into
a
x
13-inch	oblong pan, greased.
In bowl mix
brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over batter; spread
remaining
batter
over nut mixture. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool in pan and cut into squares; sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: spaghetti with meat sauce
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper.
Stir in remaining ingredients except spaghetti and cheese.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Stir sauce occasionally.
Serve over spaghetti noodles and sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 8 servings.

title: prune nut cake
directions: Combine the cake mix, pie filling, eggs and oil.
Mix well. The mixture will be stiff.
Add the brandied fruit and the nuts. Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 60 minutes.
Let the cake cool in the pan for 20 or 25 minutes.

title: creamy apple dip
directions: Mix together until creamy.
Great with Granny Smith apples!

title: cake that won't last
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix by hand until well blended. Pour into large greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.
This cake recipe does not use any eggs.

title: grace gerlach-brenneman's baked beans
directions: Cook beans soft.
Drain and save water.
Blend all ingredients with 2 cups bean water.
Add drained beans.
Stir gently to mix.
Bake at 325° for 3 to 4 hours.
If beans get too dry, add more bean water or ketchup.

title: low-fat scalloped potatoes
directions: Wash and slice potatoes thinly; do not peel.
Slice onions thinly.
Spray 2-quart casserole with cooking spray.
Layer potatoes (sprayed with cooking spray), onions, cheese and undiluted soup.
Repeat layers, adding salt and pepper to taste. After layers are in dish, mix remaining soup with milk and pour over mixture. Top with more cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hamburger with corn and rice
directions: Brown onion with hamburger and seasonings.
Drain off fat. Add corn and rice and cook, covered, over medium heat until rice is done.

title: microwave pumpkin cheesecake
directions: In 9-inch pie plate, place margarine.
Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Add cracker crumbs and 2 tablespoons sugar to melted margarine.
Combine ingredients and press firmly to form a crust. Microwave on High for 2 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork
chops on both sides.
Put rice in bottom of buttered casserole.
Pour soups over rice.	Place chops on top of rice and soup mixture.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lieb's chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts for 20 minutes.
Debone.
Cook broccoli according to directions.
Put broccoli in greased casserole; lay chicken on top of broccoli and add soup mixture.
Put cheese on top of soup mixture and then sprinkle bread crumbs on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 30 minutes.

title: boneless beef chuck or pikes peak
directions: Season
the
roast
with
the
salt,
pepper and garlic powder at
least 4 hours before baking and keep refrigerated. Preheat oven.
Dust
the roast several times over with flour. Put oil or shortening in roaster and brown on all sides, being careful
not to
puncture the roast (I use turkey grabbers to turn roast
on all sides to brown).
Add the hot water, onion and celery.
Bake at 400° for one hour and then reduce heat to 350° and
bake
hours longer.
If you need to add more water, you may do so at this time.
Makes its own gravy.

title: baked apple pies
directions: Quarter apples and remove core.
Bake apples in baking dish with sugar sprinkled over them on 300° to 350° until tender. Remove from oven, sprinkle with cinnamon.
Mash by hand or use an electric mixer, until smooth.

I use biscuits. I roll each biscuit out flat and spoon apples into each, then I fold each one over and pinch together the edges and poke holes in the dough with a fork. These are fried in melted butter until brown.

title: yam and apple scallop
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water 20 to 25 minutes or until tender; let cool to touch.
Peel.
Cut potatoes into 1/4-inch slices and arrange in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Core unpeeled apples and slice into 1/4-inch rings.
Cut apple rings in half.
Arrange in rows over potatoes.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine brown sugar and next 4 ingredients; sprinkle over casserole.
Dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes or until apples are tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: canned okra
directions: Put in kettle; cover with water.
Cook for about 15 minutes. Put in jars and seal.
When ready to eat, drain and rinse, drain, roll in meal and fry.

title: beef stew
directions: Heat drippings in 2-quart utility dish with microwave 20 to 30 seconds.
Add onion.
Cook 3 minutes or until onion is limp.
Add remaining ingredients.
Combine thoroughly.
Cover and cook 8 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika before serving.
Recipe yields 4 servings.

title: angel crisp tea cakes
directions: Cream
together:
sugar, margarine and shortening.
Add 1 egg. Stir
in flour, salt, soda, cream of tartar and vanilla.
Pinch off pieces about the size of a pecan.
Roll lightly in palm
of hands.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Dip fork in water and mash
little ball out as flat as you like.
Bake at 350°
for
10 minutes
or
until
lightly
browned.
Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples in buttered 1 quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with sugar and spices.
(If raw apples are used bake 375 degrees for 30 minutes or until apples are soft).
Cream butter, add sugar gradually and beat until fluffy.
Add egg and beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk and flavoring. Spread over cooked apples.
Bake 30 minutes longer.

title: maraschino cherry bars
directions: Mix in large bowl until crumbly, press into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes until lightly browned at 350°.

title: nacho dip(for large party; half ingredients for smaller party)
directions: Whip cream cheese and sour cream together.
Mold on tray and let chill in refrigerator for at least 1 hour.
Remove from refrigerator.
Cover top of mold with shredded lettuce, then diced tomatoes, diced onions and chopped peppers.
Cover generously with taco sauce and finish off with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Use large nachos for dipping.
Keep chilled until served.

title: crescent yeast rolls
directions: In large mixing bowl mix yeast and sugar.
Pour warm milk over yeast and sugar.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
In small bowl beat eggs and add melted margarine.
In sifter add flour and salt.
Mix yeast mixture and egg mixture, then add flour mix.
Cover and let sit out overnight.
Divide in three sections.
Roll out like pie dough, cut in eighths.
Roll up in crescent shape; let rise.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together; top with Cool Whip.
Serve with cake or as a salad.
Make the day before for better flavor.
Keeps well, covered, in refrigerator.

title: pudding dessert
directions: Mix the cake as directed on package.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake.
Mix milk and cream cheese. Add vanilla pudding. Beat for 2 minutes. Spread on cooled cake.
Drain the pineapple well. Spread over the pudding mix.
Spread Cool Whip over the pineapple. Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Prepare pastry from your favorite recipe or from a package mix according to directions except substitute a dry white wine for 1/2 of the liquid.
Place in a 10-inch quiche or pie pan;
flute edges and prick all over with a fork.
Bake at 350°F. for 10 minutes or until set but not browned.

title: chocolate-hershey-bar-pie
directions: Bake crust with almonds pressed in it.
Cool.
Grate Hershey bars (reserve 1 tablespoon).
Melt marshmallows and 1/2 cup of milk.
Add grated Hershey bars to marshmallow mixture and cool. Pour into crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle reserved 1 tablespoon of grated Hershey bar on top of the pie.

title: better than almost anything cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Make and bake cake as directed on package for 13 x 9 inch pan.
Cool 15 minutes.
Poke top of warm cake every 1/2 inch with handle of wooden spoon.
Drizzle milk evenly over top of cake; let stand until milk has been absorbed into cake.
Drizzle with topping.
Run knife around sides of pan to loosen cake.
Cover and refrigerate about 2 hours or until chilled.
Spread whipped topping over top of cake.
Sprinkle with toffee.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: pork and beans ala victor
directions: Mix all ingredients together in baking dish; place bacon strips on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until done.

title: hot bean salad
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Brown first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake for 2 hours.

title: molded crab meat salad
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in the hot water.
Add the salt.
Combine the crab meat, olives and sweet pickles with gelatin.
Chill in mold.
Garnish with chicory, radishes, olives or pickles.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry pie
directions: For Pie, separate eggs. Mix 4 stiffly beaten egg whites with one cup sugar, added slowly; beat until stiff. Combine baking powder, crackers, and nuts to egg mixture. Place in a well-buttered 9-inch pie tin and bake for 40 minutes in a 325° oven. Cool.
For the filling, mix strawberries with Cool Whip and place on top of pie shell.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and rub with lemon juice.
Place in baking dish. Mix butter, sugar and water.
Pour over potatoes.
Cover and cook 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Combine mustard, sugar, cream, vinegar and salt. Beat until light and fluffy. Cut hard-cooked eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks; mash with fork. Add enough of the mustard mixture to make a smooth paste.
Refill egg whites. Garnish with paprika.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Beat pudding and milk together until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer unbroken graham crackers on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Put on 1/2 of pudding mixture.
Add another layer of graham crackers and remaining pudding.
Cover with last layer of graham crackers and carefully frost the top.
Refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours before serving.
The graham crackers will soften and this will be easily cut and served.

title: pudding cake
directions: Mix butter, flour and nuts and pat down in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut clusters
directions: Put these items in crock pot in order listed.
Cook on low heat.
Do not bother for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not even stir.
After it has cooked for 1 1/2 hours, stir until mixed well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let harden.
Makes about 90-100 clusters.

title: mulligatawny soup
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add apples and cook 10 minutes. Combine flour and curry.
Add to onion mixture.
Stir in chicken stock slowly.
Cook until smooth and thick.
Add rice and boil for 20 minutes.
Add chicken, cream and seasonings.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into a pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Add remaining Pace on top and your choice of shredded cheese (optional).

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix together in ice cream freezer and freeze as usual.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Dice and drain all fruit except strawberries.
Combine in a 2-quart casserole.
Boil water; add sugar.
Boil until clear. Pour over fruit mixture.
Freeze overnight.
Set out 20 to 30 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken and chickpea salad in a pita
directions: Toast the pitas.
In a mixing bowl, toss all ingredients (except pitas and stuffings, or course), until everything is well combined.
Stuff pitas.
Serve immediately.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix together and freeze in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, oil and yeast mixture.
Roll out by hand.
Let rise 10 minutes.
Cook in oven 400° until golden brown.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chickens and debone.
Place cut up chicken in bottom of large pan.
Pour the following ingredients over the chicken; english peas, Veg-All, chopped onion, and boiled eggs.
After those ingredients have been added, then cover with cream of chicken and cream of celery soups.
Mix topping and spread over top of the pie.

title: banana salad dressing
directions: Beat eggs well with a fork; stir sugar into eggs.
Add vinegar and water.
Place egg mixture in saucepan.
Place saucepan in pan of hot water or double boiler and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Cool.
Spread over sliced and quartered bananas and sprinkle with crushed peanuts.

title: arkansas dump cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add eggs, cooking oil, pineapple and juice, vanilla and bananas or applesauce.
Mix up like cornbread (not in a mixer).
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: rice consomme
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Cover with foil and bake in casserole dish on 350° for 1 hour.
(Can bake 45 minutes, turn off and leave in oven for 15 minutes.)
Fluff with fork when ready to serve.

title: salami wedges
directions: Spread cream cheese over 9 slices of salami.
Stack spread slices and top with a plain slice of salami.
Cover and chill. Before serving, cut into 12 wedges and arrange on platter.
Makes 12 appetizers.

title: date cake
directions: Soak dates in hot water and let stand until all is ready. Cream together sugar and butter or margarine.
Sift together soda, flour, baking powder and salt.
Alternate dry ingredients with dates and water.
Add nutmeats and egg.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake in almost cold oven for 1 hour at 250°.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Make two 8-inch layers following package directions.
Mix pudding substituting 1/2 cup of milk with 1/2 cup of Kahlua. Place one layer of cake in a large salad bowl.
Cover with half of the pudding.
Layer with half of the Cool Whip.
Add the second cake, the rest of the pudding and the rest of the Cool Whip. Shave some chocolate over the top.
Serve with a spoon.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend together well.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: squash or eggplant casserole
directions: Cook bacon and butter.
Cook onion and pepper a little.
Add everything together.
Pour in casserole dish; top with 1/2 cup each crackers and cheese (paprika on top, optional).
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until tender.
Peel and mash.
Heat oven to 350°.
Combine butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar, salt and nutmeg in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until creamy.
Beat in sweet potatoes until well mixed.
Beat in eggs, milk and vanilla slowly.
Spoon into 3 unbaked pie shells using about 4 cups of filling per shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until set.
Cool to room temperature before serving. Store in refrigerator.

title: prime ribs and fried ice cream
directions: Kill a cow, cut its rib out and take it to the restaurants. They cook the rib and eat!!!!!
Take the ice cream, then cook it for 10 minutes, then eat!!!!

title: batter for fish
directions: Dip fish in batter and deep fry in hot oil.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake layers
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Alternate with milk and flour, then add vanilla.
Pour into 3 cake pans (9-inch), greased.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: idiot's chicken
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Pour 1/2 into 9 x 13-inch pan to coat.
Wrap cheese around chicken.
Put into pan, seam sides down. Pour soup over all.
Sprinkle stuffing over top.
Pour remaining butter over stuffing.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Drain strawberries; save juice.
Mix juice with cake mix.
Add 4 eggs, 1 at a time; add 3/4 cup vegetable oil.
Mix well; add 1/2 cup sweet milk and few drops of red food coloring.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° until done.
Frost with icing.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix last 7 ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Cover and marinate at least 12 hours.
Drain to serve (optional).
Will keep for 2 weeks.

title: creamed corn muffins
directions: Mix flour, corn meal, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Cut in butter until mix resembles crumbs.
Mix buttermilk, egg and corn and stir into flour mixture until moist.
Grease 12 muffin tins and fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 5 minutes before removing.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes with peelings until tender.
Refrigerate overnight or until cold.
Peel and grate potatoes.
Add cheese and sour cream to potatoes.
Mix well with hands and put in casserole. Dot in margarine and bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: rachel's pizza burgers
directions: Mix together.
Put on open hamburger rolls or English muffins. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 425°.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Make teaspoon size balls; press down with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Do not grease pan. Let cool before lifting off.
Makes approximately 24.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil water; add sugar and Karo.
Stir until dissolved and spins a thread.
Add peanuts; cook slowly over low heat until it turns golden brown.
Remove from heat; add butter, vanilla and soda.
Stir quickly; pour onto greased cookie sheet.

title: ohio lemon pie
directions: Peel the lemons and slice very thin.
Cover with the sugar. Let stand at room temperature for 2 hours. Add the eggs and pour into pastry lined pie plate.
Dot with butter on pastry before adding filling and again after adding filling.
Cover with top crust with steam vents. Brush top crust with remaining filling left in bowl. Bake in very hot oven at 450° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 40 minutes longer.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Dice all ingredients.
Mix together; add diced tomatoes, if desired.

title: cheese meat loaf
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients and 1/4 cup of the cheese. Mix thoroughly.
Bake in a 1-quart baking dish at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and bake until melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: val's easy potato salad
directions: In a saucepan, put water on with a touch of salt, turn heat to med-hi.
Peel and cut your potatoes and cook until the potatoes are soft.
While the potatoes are cooking, slice your cooked eggs, pickles and onion.
When the potatoes are done, rinse with cold water and let drain.
Add the potatoes to egg mixture and then add enough mayo to make creamy, add the mustard and season to taste with salt, pepper, onion and garlic salt.

title: steak diane
directions: Pound meat to 1/2-inch thickness.
Mix crushed garlic with oil and salt.
Rub into steak; cover and let stand for at least 1 hour. Seal steak in buttered pan; turn and smear sealed side with mustard.
Reduce heat when both sides are sealed.
Remove meat; add wine and sauces to pan and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and stir in cream; do not boil.
Serve over steak.

title: ono chocolate cake
directions: Combine the cake mix, pudding, oil, 4 eggs, vanilla and hot water and mix for 2 minutes.
Add nuts and chocolate chips. Hand mix a couple of times and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: holiday fruitcake
directions: Generously grease and flour tube pan.
In a large bowl, combine eggs and water.
Add remaining ingredients by hand.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 80 minutes.
Cool completely.
To store, wrap tightly in foil or plastic wrap.
Can glaze with warm corn syrup.
Decorate with candied fruits and nuts or cherries.

title: mary's quick doughnut balls
directions: Measure flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into bowl. Add milk,
egg	and
vanilla;	beat until
smooth.
Drop
by teaspoonfuls into hot fat.	Fry for 3 minutes
or until golden brown.
Drain.
Stir together 1/2 cup sugar
and
teaspoon cinnamon.
Roll doughnut in mixture.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all together and store.
Use 3 to 4 tablespoons per cup of hot water.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake mix.
Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Crumble 1/2 of cake in a punch bowl, then pour 1/2 of pudding on top of cake.
Layer 1 1/2 bananas, 1/2 of the crushed pineapple and 1 box strawberries.
Spread 1/2 carton Cool Whip. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup coconut and 1/2 cup nuts over Cool Whip. Repeat layers, starting with cake and ending with Cool Whip, coconut and nuts.
Make 12 to 24 hours before serving.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Line base of 9 x 13-inch dish with chipped beef.
Wrap each chicken breast with a bacon slice.
Combine sour cream and soup. Pour over chicken.
Bake at 300° for about 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: chocolate oreo pie
directions: Mix together crushed Oreos and melted butter.
Press mixture into 8-inch pie plate; chill.
Melt chocolate in 3 tablespoons water over low heat, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add vanilla to cooled chocolate; mix.
Whip 1 cup whipping cream and add chocolate mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into chilled pie crust and refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: no cook frosting
directions: Place butter and sugar in mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Stir in vanilla and milk until smooth and creamy.
Use just enough milk to make frosting of good spreading consistency.
Makes enough for 24 cupcakes or 1 (9 x 13-inch) cake.

title: cheese dip
directions: Put one can of Ro-Tel in cheese. While melting, brown sausage. Drain and combine with remaining can of Ro-Tel. Eat and enjoy.

title: three pepper beef kabobs
directions: Whisk together oil, lemon juice, water, mustard, honey, oregano and pepper in large bowl.
Add other pieces and stir to coat.
Alternately thread onto skewers.
Broil in pan 9 to 12 minutes, turning occasionally.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water with salt; let cool, then add pineapple and mix well.
Let stand in refrigerator until partly congealed; mix milk, salad dressing and cottage cheese and blend well.
Add mixture to jello mixture and blend well and let chill in refrigerator until firm.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pat firmly. Beat eggs, sugar and 1 1/3 sticks butter with mixer at least 15 minutes.
Spread mixture over crust.
Cover with sliced bananas and crushed pineapple (well drained).
Top with Cool Whip and then sprinkle chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together very well and shape into the size of a robin egg.
Roll in hands.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add egg yolks; dissolve soda in 1 teaspoon warm water.
Mix in 1 cup buttermilk.
Add 3 cups plain flour alternately with milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in cake batter.
Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours until done at 300°.

title: southern oatmeal pie(tastes like pecan pie)
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie shell (9-inch pie tin).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve plain or with whipped topping or whipping cream.

title: bernice heugatter's corn flakes peanut butter bars
directions: Mix syrup and sugar together.
Let come to boil; add peanut butter and mix well.
Pour over corn flakes and mix until combined.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press down to stick together.

title: ground meat barbecue
directions: Brown the meat. Add the rest of the ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.

title: scalloped onions
directions: Wash and peel onions; slice 1/4-inch thick.
Heat oleo in saucepan; add onions.
Cover and cook until golden brown, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Place onions in 6 to 8-inch baking dish; add seasoning and white sauce.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs and cheese; bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes.

title: onion ring batter
directions: Mix all ingredients, except onions, beating well.
Slice onions into rings.
Dip in batter; drain for a second.
Fry in hot oil; drain.
Serve hot.
Batter is also good for okra, shrimp, clams and other vegetables.

title: party turnovers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine soup mix and hamburger.
Brown well. Drain and add cheese. Separate crescent dough into triangles.
Place 1 tablespoon of mixture on each.
Fold over and seal.
(Can be refrigerated at this point and baked at time of party.)
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet and bake for 15 minutes or until golden brown. Serve hot.
Makes 48.

title: cherry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water and cherry pie filling.
Chill until firm.
Mix cream cheese and crushed pineapple and spread over top.
Sprinkle with nuts and let set (preferably overnight).

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg whites and salt until very stiff.
This takes a long time.
When stiff, add the sugar gradually to the egg whites and salt.
Fold chocolate chips into meringue.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Place in oven and turn off heat.
Leave in oven until oven is cool; basically forget about them.
Do not open to peek.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: lo-cal salad
directions: Mix dry jello in cottage cheese.
Add drained fruit.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Let stand in refrigerator for at least 4 hours.

title: maxine's chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift dry ingredients together. Alternate dry and liquid ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 325° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: spinach cheese squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
In
9 x 13-inch pan grease well.

title: strawberry glaze pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan.
Stir in water. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick and clear. Remove from heat; stir in Jell-O.
Cool.
Place strawberries in baked pie shell.
Pour glaze over berries.
Refrigerate.
Top with whipped cream.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Serve on Ritz or Club crackers.

title: bev's key lime pie
directions: Mix milk and Cool Whip.
Add lime juice and lime peel.
Mix and pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with grated lime peel. Refrigerate.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all these ingredients together.
Pour half into each pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Yields 2 pies.

title: finger paints
directions: Mix cornstarch and water.
Boil until thick.
Color with food colorings.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Combine
beef,	tomato	sauce
and
salt. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Mix
onion,
sour cream and cream cheese.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Cook
noodles
and drain.
Layer noodles, cheese mixture and
meat	in casserole dish. Top with grated Cheddar cheese. Bake
at
325° to 350° or until bubbly. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheerio treats
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Microwave margarine in a large microwave-safe bowl on High 45 seconds or until melted.
Add marshmallows; toss to coat with margarine.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth when stirred, stirring after 45 seconds.
Stir in peanut butter.
Immediately add cereal; mix lightly until well coated.
Using greased spatula or wax paper, press mixture into prepared pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: pork chops casserole
directions: Brown pork chops and onion lightly.
Place pork chops in baking dish.
Slice potatoes and put on top of pork chops.
Add soup and rinse out the can with a little water.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bouquet garni
directions: Wrap dried herbs, still on the stem, or coarsely crumbled, in a 4-inch square of cheesecloth.
Tie in a bag.
This makes 12 bags.

title: beans in a bundle
directions: Drain beans.
Separate beans into bundles.
Wrap the bundles with 1/2 slice of bacon each, line them in a casserole dish.
Pour Italian dressing over the top of bean bundles and bake at 425 until bacon is crisp.

title: million's house beverage
directions: Fill a large glass 3/4 full of ice.
Pour in 3/4 full of Dr. Pepper, then fill rest of the way with Pepsi.

title: baked clams
directions: Split and clean fresh clams.
In saucepan, mix butter, bread crumbs, oregano, oil and cheese. Spoon over clams.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add enough milk to make a stiff dough. Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until browned.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Melt margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add Parmesan cheese and mix.
Layer half of spaghetti, 1/3 of cheese and 1/3 of pepperoni 2 times.
Spaghetti sauce is next layer.
Top with layer of cheese and pepperoni again.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, fry bacon and onion until onion is tender, about 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and cook, stirring occasionally, until cabbage is tender, about 10 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate crepes
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Beat well with a whisk or electric mixer until well blended.
Or place ingredients in a blender jar and blend until well mixed.
Let batter rest 2 hours if possible. Cook in crepe pan or frying pan.

title: cheddar tuna casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine; add soup and milk.
Stir in remaining ingredients except cheese.
Pour in a 1-quart Pyrex dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Take out of oven and sprinkle with cheese on top.
Put back into oven until cheese melts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: angel food cake
directions: Break up cake and put in bottom of long pan.
Mix vanilla pudding and cream cheese together and pour over cake.
Take pineapple (drained) and spread over pudding.
Take your strawberries and put on pineapple.
Then put Cool Whip over that. Spread coconut over cake.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy; add milk and vanilla.
Beat and pour into crust.
Chill about 3 hours.
Top with pie filling.

title: yummy tummy brownie mix
directions: For gifts:
Layer cocoa, flour, sugars, salt, nuts, and chips in quart jars.
Attach a card reading: When you are ready to enjoy your brownies, just pour the mixture in a bowl and add vanilla eggs and oil.
Bake at 350 degrees in a 7x11 pan for 30 minutes.

title: cheddar potato strips
directions: In a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish, arrange potatoes in a single layer. Pour milk over the potatoes. Dot with butter; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cover and bake at 425 degrees for 30 minutes or until the potatoes are tender. Sprinkle with cheese and parsley. Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer or until cheese is completely melted.

title: bar cookies
directions: Mix margarine and graham cracker crumbs together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and pat down good.
Top with coconut and Eagle Brand milk.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Mix together peanut butter and melted chocolate chips.
Put on baked layer.
Cool. Cut into bars.

title: blackberry dumpling
directions: In large pot, mix blackberries in their own juice, water and sugar together.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Cover pot.
Cut biscuits into 4 parts.
Add to blackberry mixture.
Stir occasionally. Cook for 12 minutes or until it is tender.
Serve hot or cold.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk, then mix in sour cream and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Layer vanilla wafers and bananas.
Top with pudding each time.
Spread remaining half of Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with wafer crumbs.

title: * pineapple-rice salad *
directions: Make jello using pineapple juice.
Let jello almost set; add pineapple and rice.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: cowboy sourdough flapjacks
directions: Mix starter, water,
and flour in bowl; keep overnight. Stir in remaining ingredients the next day.
Let mixture bubble 10 minutes.
bake on griddle, using 1/4 c. batter for each cake. Makes 2 dozen 5-in. flapjacks.

title: beans and rice
directions: Add ingredients (except rice) all at once to a large pot. Cook for 3 hours at medium heat until beans are very soft and 1/2 the liquid remains.
Serve over rice.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well.
Fold in Cool Whip and chill.

title: estelle templeton's tea cakes(old timey tea cakes)
directions: Use enough flour to make a medium stiff dough and beat well. Roll out on a floured board to about 1/4 inch thick.
Cut out and bake in a 350° oven until edge turns golden.
Remove from oven and cool.
Can eat plain or frost.

title: raspberry and sour cream coffee cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat sour cream and butter with electric mixer on medium-high speed until combined.
Add about half the flour to mixture.
Blend.
Add sugar, eggs, milk, baking powder and soda, and vanilla.
Beat on low speed until thoroughly combined. Scrape sides.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Go back to low speed and add remaining flour just until combined.
Spread batter evenly in pan.
Dollop jam in small spoonfuls on top of batter. Use a knife and swirl jam into batter to create a marble effect. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes.
Sift confectioners sugar over top.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Yields 12 servings.

title: crock-pot barbecue beef
directions: Place roast, onions and water in crock-pot.
Turn on high for 6 to 8 hours.
Roast should be very tender.
Drain off broth; shred beef.
Add catsup, mustard, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Put back in crock-pot.
Add broth, if needed, to moisten. Leave about 1/2 hour.
Serve on buns.

title: crabmeat dip (salad)
directions: Soften the cream cheese. Chop up crabmeat and shred with a fork.
Mix all the ingredients. You can shape it like an oval or leave as is in a bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill. Cover crab dip with cocktail sauce and serve.
Enjoy!

title: string bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans and pour into casserole dish. Combine mushroom soup and milk. Pour over string beans. Sprinkle grated cheese over top. Sprinkle onions over grated cheese. Bake in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage and crumble it up.
Grease a 9 x 11-inch baking dish.
Unroll the crescent rolls.
Place in baking dish and pinch the seams so that there are no holes.
Sprinkle the sausage over the rolls.
In any order, sprinkle the cheeses over sausage.
Mix eggs, milk, salt, pepper and oregano in a bowl and mix well.
Pour on top of cheeses.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, eggs, pecans, pickles, pineapple tidbits, salt and pepper. Blend with enough mayonnaise to moisten, not too much. Seedless grapes may be substituted for the pineapple. Serves 8.

title: dieter's delight
directions: Prepare pudding mix with milk as directed on package.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping and 1/2 of the crushed cookies.
Place a thin layer of cookie crumbs in the bottom of a 2-quart bowl.
Fill with pudding mixture.
Top with remaining crushed cookies.
Chill until set, about 1 hour.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, pour into a greased and floured 9 by 13 in. cake pan.
Combine cream cheese and margarine with pwd. sugar and vanilla in bowl and mix well.
Spoon over batter.
Bake 45-50 min. at 350°.
Do not over bake and do not frost.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers, veggies or toasted pita bread. (It tastes better than it sounds!)

title: billy goats
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add egg yolks and vanilla. Sift together flour, soda, salt and all spices. Add dry ingredients to egg mixture with sour milk. Add nuts and dates. Drop on greased cookie sheet. Bake for 20 minutes at 325°.

title: asparagus potato soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine chicken broth, potatoes, onion, salt and nutmeg.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 5 to 8 minutes, until potatoes are barely tender. Add asparagus, return to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes more, until vegetables are tender.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Place meat in 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Slice onion. Diagonally slice celery.
Pare carrots and cut into chunks.
Add vegetables to baking pan.
Blend salt, sugar and cornstarch. Sprinkle over ingredients in baking dish.
Add tomato juice. Cover pan with sheet of heavy-duty aluminum foil and crimp edges to seal lightly.
Bake stew (do not stir) in slow oven (250°) for 4 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: country cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: oven pot roast
directions: Put meat in Dutch oven.
In a bowl, stir dry meat marinade into the cup of buttermilk.
Pour mixture over meat.
With a fork, pierce meat and allow to stand at room temperature for 15 minutes, turning several times.
Add toasted rye bread crumbs to marinade. Cover and bake in 325° oven until meat is tender, 2 to 3 hours. Remove meat.
Skim any fat from liquid in pan.
Add drained mushrooms and additional buttermilk to flour to make a thickened gravy.
Serve gravy with sliced meat.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Pour milk over poppy seed and let stand 2 to 3 hours.
Cream sugar and shortening; add poppy seed and milk alternately with sifted mixture of flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold carefully into batter.
Pour into oiled 10 x 14-inch cake pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
When cool, cut cake in two and put together as a layer cake with filling.

title: butterscotch torte
directions: Mix flour, nuts and softened butter; spread in pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
After crust cools, mix together 1 small carton Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Whip until smooth and spread over top of crust.

title: sweet muffins
directions: Grease muffin cups or use baking cups.
Mix liquid ingredients in separate bowl as dry.
Add dry to liquid mixture and stir just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: aunt b's no bake cheese cake
directions: Mix jello and water; cool.
Cream the cheese, sugar and vanilla together.
Add the cooled jello and fold in the Cool Whip. Pour into graham cracker crusts.
May add a little yellow food coloring to mixture before pouring it into pie crusts.
May also top finished cheese cake with fruit topping.

title: caramel raisin pudding
directions: Mix all together and put into a greased pan or baking dish.

title: glazed carrots and onions
directions: Place carrots in 2-quart casserole dish along with butter. Microwave for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients; stir and microwave for another 2 to 4 minutes until vegetables are glazed.

title: creamed cod plus
directions: Cook vegetables in saucepan or microwave in small amount of water.
Lay fish on top so all cook about same time until tender.

title: old testament cake
directions: Follow the direction of Solomon in Proverbs. Makes 4 average bread pans or two loaf pans lightly greased.
Bake at 350° for 50-60 minutes.
Slices best when cold.

title: stir fry chicken
directions: In Wok or large skillet heat olive oil. Saute vegtables for about 2 min. Remove from pan, keep covered. Add chicken to pan saute until done 3-4 min. Add vegetables to chicken.
Coat with peanut sauce, heat.
Serve over white rice.
Keep frozen chicken in the freezer and for a quick meal, just cook the chicken and rice. Serve with a cucumber or apple.

title: hickory nut pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add beaten eggs.
Mix water with syrup and combine with egg mixture.
Add the nuts and butter last.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then reduce temperature to 350° and bake 35 minutes longer. Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: karo pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients for filling together, adding pecans last. Pour into pie shell.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes longer.
When pie is done, outer edges of filling should be set.

title: pasta in a pot
directions: Brown first 5 ingredients; add tomatoes and sauce and simmer 20 minutes.
Boil macaroni.
Mix the sour cream and cheeses. Layer in 4-quart covered casserole: half sauce-meat mix; half macaroni; all cheese mixture; remaining noodles and remaining sauce.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: autumn fruit cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add cracker crumbs, coconut, pineapple and baking powder; mix well.
Add nuts and mix well.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for approximately 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: best peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine Crisco, margarine, peanut butter, sugars and egg.
Add flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add peanuts.
Chill batter. Shape into one-inch balls.
Make crisscross pattern with fork to flatten.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup, milk and pepper.
Alternate potatoes, onion and soup.
Dot	with
butter.
Cover
and bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes more to brown.

title: southern chess pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugars and flour.
Beat in eggs, milk, vanilla and butter.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Steam cabbage leaves in steamer just enough to fold.
Mix all ingredients together and simmer in pan for 10 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Open cabbage leaf, put in enough of mixture for 1 serving.
Fold over sides, then ends.
Use toothpick to hold. Fill all 7 leaves the same.
Place in baking dish.
Cook for about 15 minutes in covered dish at 325°.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine ingredients in large salad bowl; add dressing.

title: cinnamon sticks
directions: Mix together the butter, sugar, flour, egg yolk, cinnamon and vanilla. Pat down on large cookie sheet.
Beat the egg white until it's broken up and spread over dough with pastry brush.
Sprinkle the cup of chopped pecans over the dough and press in with spatula or hands. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Cut into strips or squares while warm.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Break tomatoes. Layer ingredients in 1-quart casserole dish. Put juice of tomatoes all over. Bake about 1/2 hour at 350°. Serves 4.

title: fruit cocktail dessert
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, soda and salt and add egg, slightly beaten, one can fruit cocktail, undrained, vanilla and 1/2 of the nuts.
Pour into buttered pan, 9 x 9-inch or round 9-inch pie pan. Mix remaining nuts into brown sugar and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream; good warm. Serves 8.

title: ravioli soup
directions: In a large sauce pan combine water, tomato juice, beef broth, carrot, potato, onion, sugar, and salt. Boil. Reduce heat, simmer; covered until vegetables are tender (12 to 15 minutes). Gently stir in Ravioli and snipped spinach.

title: brisket with onion gravy
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Bring 2 cups of water and the soup mix to a boil.
Place half the onion in the bottom of baking dish or Dutch oven.
Place meat on top with remaining onions on top of meat.
Pour soup mixture in.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: flank steak fix-up
directions: Rub steak with garlic.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt and the pepper.
Cut the meat crosswise into 4 to 6 serving pieces.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Boil diced eggplant 30 minutes or until tender in salty water. Mix together eggplant, soup, mushrooms, cheese and 1/4 cup grated onion.
Top with buttered Town House cracker crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chinese hash
directions: Cook beef, onion, celery and green pepper together until tender.
Add soups, water, soy sauce and rice.
Combine and bake covered for 45 minutes at 350 degrees.
Sprinkle Chinese noodles on top.
Bake uncovered another 15 minutes.

title: soy shrimp and pickled onions
directions: Marinate the cooked shrimp in soy sauce for 1 hour.
Drain and alternate shrimp and pickled onions on skewers.
Chill and serve.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Dice cauliflower and lettuce (medium to fine).
Dice onion. Fry bacon until crispy.
Crumble bacon up.
Layer cauliflower, lettuce, onion and bacon.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar.
Pour over layered ingredients.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Put into refrigerator.
Mix up well when ready to serve.

title: chinese noodle cookies
directions: Melt butterscotch bit over double boiler. Stir in noodles and peanuts. Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper. Let harden.
Enjoy.

title: buffalo enchiladas
directions: Mix ground bison with Worcestershire sauce, onion, garlic, bell pepper and jalapeno peppers.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Brown in frying pan over medium-high heat until mixture is gray. Lightly cover meat with chili powder while browning.
Once browned, transfer meat into chili pot/Dutch oven.
Add tomatoes and tomato paste.
Mix thoroughly.
Add cumin sparingly (pinch or two). Sprinkle paprika across meat and add water until meat is covered with 1/4 to 1/2-inch.
Bring to a boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer over medium heat for 30 to 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally and add water, if needed.
A sprinkle of flour or masa can be added at the end to thicken the sauce.

title: oriental salad
directions: You may combine the first 5 ingredients ahead of time.
Cut up celery cabbage and mix with the mixed ingredients just before serving.

title: chicketti
directions: Melt butter in	pan;
add
flour and stir until bubbly. Remove from heat.	Gradually stir in liquid from mushrooms and cook over low
heat
until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and gradually	stir
in
chicken broth, sour cream, salt, pepper and mushrooms.	Cook spaghetti and drain.
Place layers of spaghetti, chicken
mixture
and
cheese
until all used.
Cheese on top and sauce.
Bake in oven until bubbly.

title: baked rabbit with stuffing
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine.
Remove from heat and stir sesame seed, thyme and salt.
Pour mixture over bread crumbs. Toss and spread in bottom of greased dish.

title: pestro dip
directions: In blender or food processor, blend all ingredients until almost smooth.
Cover and chill.
Makes 2 cups.

title: lima bean-broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter; add curry powder and cereal biscuits.
Stir over low heat about 5 minutes to coat the cereal well.
Cook the vegetables separately.
Combine lima beans with the 2 soups (undiluted) and add 1 cup of the cereal mixture.
Stir in the broccoli.
Place in buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Top with remaining cereal mixture.
May sprinkle with paprika if desired. Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Can easily be doubled for a larger group.
Serves 8.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan pineapple, pie filling,
then
cake mix.
Be sure that cake mix and butter reach corners well.
Next, dot evenly with butter, then sprinkle with pecans.
Bake
for
minutes or until golden brown.

title: hamburger picnic bundles
directions: Place a well seasoned beef patty in the center of a 10-inch square of aluminum foil.
Top with a teaspoon of steak sauce or chili sauce.
Cover meat with thinly sliced potatoes, carrots and onions.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add 1 tablespoon water. Fold foil loosely around food.
Seal tightly.
Bake at 450° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Mix 1 stick of melted margarine with powdered sugar (sifted) and creme de menthe liqueur.
Follow instructions on brownie mix and bake in a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cool.
Spread over cooled brownie.
Mix sugar, margarine and creme de menthe liqueur.
Cool until firm.
Mix 6 tablespoons melted margarine with chocolate chips.
Spread over top of brownies.
Refrigerate to cool.
Cut into squares.

title: heavenly divinity salad
directions: Place Cool Whip in large bowl and stir well to fluff up.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving. Serve on lettuce leaves, if desired.
Yields 4 servings.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown and drain hamburger and bacon.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook in crock-pot or slow cooker a couple hours.

title: sweet-sour cole slaw
directions: Place shredded cabbage in a covered dish in refrigerator for several hours.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over cabbage 1/2 hour before serving.

title: fish almondine(microwave)
directions: Mix flour, paprika, salt and pepper.
Place on flat plate or waxed paper.
Coat fish fillets with mixture.
Preheat large browning skillet in microwave, 3 to 4 minutes.
During last 20 to 30 seconds of heating, melt 2 tablespoons of butter or margarine in skillet.
Place fillets in browning dish.
To brown on one side, place in microwave; cook on High for 1 minute.
Remove and turn fillets gently.
Return to microwave and cook 3 to 3 1/2 minutes on High or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Remove fish to a serving platter.
Heat browning skillet 2 minutes and add butter during last 20 seconds.
Add almonds and brown lightly in butter. (You may want to place in microwave 30 seconds.)
Add Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice and heat 30 seconds.
Remove mixture from pan and spread over fish fillets.
Garnish with paprika.
(You may want to heat total dish before serving 45 seconds to 1 minute.)

title: chicken a la king
directions: Brown mushrooms and pepper in margarine. Blend in flour and seasonings over low heat. Stir until smooth.
Blend in chicken broth and evaporated milk. Stir until mixture comes to a boil. Add chicken and pimientos.
Stir until correct thickness.
Serve over pastry, English muffins or biscuits.
To reheat mixture, add small amount of milk. Freezes well.

title: drop cookies
directions: Cook raisins in a small amount of water, until water is about gone; add oleo and set aside to cool.
Add all other ingredients together; mix with raisins and oleo mixture.
Then drop on a greased cookie sheet, 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° until done. These take a little longer than regular cookie dough.
Also, they must be refrigerated or they will mold.

title: cheese dainties
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.
Mix well.
Form into small balls size of olive.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not bake until brown.
Makes 8 to 9 dozen.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti; set aside.
Microwave butter, onion and mushrooms for 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in flour to a paste.
In a separate dish, combine broth and cream and cook 3 minutes and stir into flour mixture.
Stir in half of the Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Carefully stir in cooked spaghetti, chicken and remaining cheese.
Cover and cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: corn and shrimp soup
directions: Melt butter in deep saucepan.
Saute onions, green onions and bell peppers.
When limp, add tomatoes.
Stir well.
Slowly add flour.
Stir until smooth.
Add milk until blended.
Add corn and shrimp.
Cook until shrimp is pink.
Add salt and pepper.

title: rich pastry(yields one 9-inch pie)
directions: Combine flour and salt in a large bowl; cut in shortening and butter with a pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle with water, 1 tablespoon at a time; mix lightly with a fork just until pastry holds together and leaves side of bowl clean.
Roll out to a 12-inch round on a lightly floured pastry cloth or board; fit into a 9-inch pie plate.
Trim overhang to 1/2-inch; turn under and flush with rim.
Flute to make a stand-up edge.
Chill while making filling.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in Reynolds oven bag (large); place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce, mushrooms, onion, oregano and garlic powder to bag.
Squeeze bag to blend in flour.
Add chicken to bag.
Turn bag to coat chicken with sauce.
Arrange ingredients in an even layer.
Close bag with a nylon tie; cut 6-inch slits in top.
Bake until chicken is tender, 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve over pasta.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fried rice
directions: In skillet fry bacon that has been cut into 1 inch strips. When bacon is almost done, add chops (that have been cut into 1 inch cubes).
Season with salt, pepper, oregano and 1 teaspoon lemon juice.
When chops are almost done (about 25 minutes), add chopped green onions.
While meat mixture is simmering with a lid on, cook rice as directed on box.
When meat mixture is done, add it to rice.
Then in skillet meat was in scramble eggs.
Add these to rice and meat.
Serve and let each person add as much soy sauce as wanted.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 1-quart casserole dish.
Top with buttered Ritz crackers and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mother's southern fruitcake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; set aside.
Cream butter, sugars and egg yolks.
Sift 3 cups flour and baking soda, then add lemon. Mix fruit with the 4th cup of flour.
Hand mix flour with creamed butter, sugars and egg yolk.
Mix in fruit and nuts.
Fold egg whites.
Let stand in mixing bowl in refrigerator overnight.
Bake in large funnel pan or 2 loaf pans for 3 hours at 250°.
Check at 2 1/2 hours with toothpick since ovens vary.
Leave upside-down in pan 30 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, sprinkle pudding over fruit cocktail.
Stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple and oranges.
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: shoo-fly pie(amish recipe)
directions: Mix well.
Dissolve 2 teaspoons soda in 1/2 cup hot water and add to mixture.
Pour in 2 unbaked pie shells and top with reserved crumbs.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 375° and bake for 30 minutes or until top is dry and done.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together with sweet potatoes, eggs, sugar, milk, vanilla and 1/3 cup butter.
Spread in an 8-inch baking dish, butter and flour.
Crumble pecans and coconut on top of sweet potato mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: brownie pie
directions: Beat all ingredients, except nuts, until smooth (2 minutes in blender on high speed).
Pour into greased pie plate.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve with a scoop of ice cream.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Two days before, drain pineapple and mix with marshmallows. Refrigerate overnight.
Mix juice, flour, vinegar, sugar and egg. Stir over low heat until thickened.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cream pumpkin, eggs and shortening.
Add to dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: laura's pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and butter in a saucepan; place over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves and butter melts. Cool slightly. Add eggs, vanilla, salt and pecans. Stir well. Pour into prepared pie crust. Bake at 325° for 55 minutes or until set.

title: steak bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut round steak into serving pieces. Place in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over steak.
Spoon mushroom soup over top.
Cover tightly with foil. Bake for one hour.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil and dice chicken.
Combine soups, peppers, onion, milk and diced chicken in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Soften the flour tortillas in the chicken broth.
Line a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with softened tortillas and pour a layer of chicken mixture on top of this.
Top with grated cheese and repeat until casserole dish is full.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Roll in 1/2-inch balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: easy mexican soup
directions: Combine tomatoes, tomatoes with green chiles, corn, tomato soup, vegetable soup and chili
in large pot and mix well. Bring to a simmer over medium heat, stirring frequently. Layer cheese, sour cream and chips in individual bowls. Ladle hot soup over top. Makes 12 servings.

title: fruit punch
directions: Dissolve jello and add sugar.
Stir well.
Add lemonade and pineapple juice.
Freeze.
Set out 4 hours before serving (until slushy.)
Add ginger ale, mix well. Serve.

title: monkey bread
directions: Thaw bread.
Make mixture of brown sugar and cinnamon (1 cup sugar, add 2 teaspoons cinnamon or more, if desired).
Roll pieces of bread (walnut size) in butter and roll in sugar mixture.
Put balls in layer in Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Add ball-nuts layers until used up.
Let bread raise.
(Balls could be rolled in nuts before putting in pan.)
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes. Turn out on deep dish.

title: jacob's power ranger cookies
directions: Mix everything in big bowl.
