Cook in oven. Decorate with blue icing.

title: chocolate intrigue cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of a 10-inch tube pan. Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add vanilla to milk and alternately add flour mixture and milk to the creamed mixture, beating well after each addition.
Pour 2/3 of batter into prepared pan.
Mix chocolate syrup and baking soda together.
Add to remaining batter.

title: chili bean casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and butter.
Drain off fat. Mix the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: orange glazed chicken
directions: Brown chicken on both sides in hot oil using a large skillet. Move chicken to side of pan.
Add carrots and celery; cook and stir until tender.

title: cran-kraut meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients in large saucepan.
Simmer over medium heat for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: frozen strawberry delight
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar together.
Add strawberries and pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip and add pecans. Freeze in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cut in squares.

title: hot and spicy barbecued chicken
directions: Light a hot fire in a barbecue grill.
Chop the garlic.
In a shallow dish, combine the garlic, oil, Worcestershire sauce and hot pepper flakes.
Dip the chicken in the sauce to coat completely.
Grill the chicken a total of about 6 minutes, turning and brushing often with sauce, until it is nicely browned and white in the center.

title: granola
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine honey and oil; stir into the oat mixture.
Spread out evenly in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Remove from the oven; stir in the apricots and raisins.
Place in another pan and let cool, stirring often to prevent lumping.
Store in tightly covered jars or plastic bags for up to 2 weeks.
Makes 6 1/2 cups.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion and green pepper. Drain.
Put in casserole dish. Stir in soup. Cover completely with cheese, then with Tater Tots.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: gravy
directions: Brown butter and flour together.
Add broth.
Stir.
Bring to boil and, if too thick, add a little more broth.
Salt and pepper.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Pare the potatoes and onion; grate and let stand for about 10 minutes so moisture from the potatoes will rise to the top. Remove the liquid.
Beat egg until the yolk and white are thoroughly combined.
Pour into the grated potatoes and onion; stir with fork.
Add the other ingredients.
More flour may be needed.
Fry in hot fat.
When brown on one side, turn.
Excellent with meat.

title: back to school cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and molasses and beat well.
Stir and beat well.
Stir in sour cream and Pet milk, then mix in dry ingredients.
Mix all of this together.
Drop from tablespoon on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Makes about 6 dozen.

title: greek salad with fresh basil
directions: Toss lettuce and basil leaves together in salad bowl.
Mound gently.
Arrange remaining ingredients attractively on lettuce with anchovies crossed on top.
(Can be prepared to this point several hours in advance, wrapped airtight and refrigerated.) Garnish with basil leaves.
Serve vinaigrette on the side.
Makes 2 main course servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine.
Add soup and cheese. Mix and simmer slowly.
Add broccoli which has been slightly cooked.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Top with dried bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: friendship cake
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups starter juice and 2 1/2 cups sugar; add 1 large cup sliced peaches.
Stir once a day for 10 days.
Then add 2 1/2 cups sugar and 2 large cans of chunk pineapple.
Stir once a day for 10 days.
Then add 2 1/2 cups sugar and 1 large can fruit cocktail and one 10 ounce jar maraschino cherries.
Stir once a day for 10 days.
Then drain fruit.
Makes about 2 cups.
(Save juice for other starters.)

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix stuffing, milk, water, 1/4 cup of the salsa and margarine in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Arrange chicken over stuffing.
Pour remaining 1/2 cup salsa over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake 30 minutes or until chicken is done.
Remove foil.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into flowerets.
Peel stalks and slice thin. Cover raisins with hot water; soak 5 minutes and drain.
Cook bacon until crisp; crumble.

title: vodka tomato cream sauce for pasta
directions: *You can used canned tomatoes, either whole ones you chop or canned diced tomatoes, drained.
Crushed tomatoes do not work in this recipe.

title: chicken ball
directions: Mix all together.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: delicious slush(usa)
directions: Combine undrained pineapple and orange juice concentrate in blender container.
Process until smooth.
Add banana; mix well. Stir in ginger ale.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze for 30 minutes or until slushy.
Spoon into glasses.
Yields 4 servings.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll out biscuits.
Place apples in center.
Sprinkle cinnamon on apples; fold over and seal the edges of biscuits. Place in large glass dish.
Bring to boil the butter, 7-Up and sugar.
Pour over dumplings and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie cake
directions: Melt butter. Mix in 1 egg and cake mix.
Press in pan. Mix cream cheese, 3 eggs, vanilla and powdered sugar. Pour on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon mousse
directions: Chill milk in freezer until slivers of ice appear in it.
Turn into a chilled bowl and whip.
Add lemon peel.
Slowly add lemon juice, beating constantly.
Continue beating and add sugar slowly. Cover bottom of pan with half of crackers.
Pour whipped mixture into pan and cover with remaining crackers.
Wrap and freeze. (Will keep several weeks in freezer.)

title: cheese balls
directions: Blend onions and beef in food processor very fine.
Add bacon bits and cream cheese.
Make a ball and roll in chopped pecans or parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: antipasta
directions: Cook springs in 1/4
to 1/2 cup Italian dressing.
Cube cheese and meat; mix
with
the
springs.	Add
green peppers. Pour on the rest of the Italian dressing.
Sprinkle on oregano for taste. Add garlic salt to taste.

title: crazy cake
directions: Put in sifter flour, soda, sugar, salt and cocoa.
Sift into ungreased pan and add vanilla, vinegar, shortening and water.
Mix well.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: savory eggs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle cheese in 9-inch square pan.
Dot with butter.
Mix cream, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour half over cheese.
Pour eggs over top, then remaining cream mixture.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Serve at once.
Makes 6 servings.

title: angel food cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugars until creamy.
Add egg, then sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in flavorings and coconut.
Roll dough into small balls.
Bake on a greased baking sheet 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: inez's hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all together and place in greased casserole dish.
Top with buttered cornflake crumbs, if desired. Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together oil, sugar, eggs and salt.
Whip with fork until creamy.
Add carrots, walnuts, flour, cinnamon, baking soda and baking powder.
Grease and flour 3 round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.
Don't overbake.

title: bundle beans
directions: Optional:
Boil bacon in water or partially cook to remove excess fat.

title: special macaroni cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, mix cooked macaroni, mushroom soup, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Top with cheese.
Bake until bubbly in a 425° oven.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Place cooked broccoli in bottom of pie crust.
Cover with cheese and cooked onions.
Mix milk and eggs with salt and pepper. Pour over ingredients in crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onions and mango in butter.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and cook macaroni.
Add to ground beef the onion, spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce and macaroni.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and very thin slices of pepperoni.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Put chicken in first, layer cheese on top. Combine soup, seasoning, parsley and wine and pour over chicken.
Mix butter and stuffing and put on top.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
tags: cream of celery soup or cream of chicken

title: microwave fudge
directions: Sift into a 2-quart glass bowl sugar and cocoa and put on top margarine and milk.
Do not mix.
Microwave 3 to 4 minutes.
Take out when margarine melts and stir.
Add vanilla and nuts (optional).
Pour into pot in freezer for 1/2 hour.

title: company casserole
directions: To the browned and drained ground beef, add the green pepper, onion, salt and pepper to taste and the tomato sauce. Simmer until it has cooked some.
Prepare the noodles according to directions. Rinse and drain. Blend together the cream cheese, cottage cheese and sour cream.
Grease a 2-quart
baking dish.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Make a layer of noodles, cheese and tomatoes and meat sauce.
Repeat until all is used.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes. Serve 6 to 8.

title: cracker salad
directions: Combine crackers and mix well just before serving.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Soak poppy seed in milk for 2 hours.
Cream butter.
Add sugar, a little at a time, creaming well.
Then add poppy seed and milk.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes.
Stir in chips, marshmallows, vanilla and 1 cup nuts.
Place in greased 8 x 10-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: coin salad
directions: Blend together ingredients and refrigerate 1/2 hour before serving.

title: squash and corn casserole
directions: Cook together the squash and onion until tender.
Drain.
Mix in beaten eggs and corn.
Mix in bread crumbs, saving some for topping.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven about 1 hour.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bread crumbs. Serves 10 to 12.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Mix flour, salt and milk; this forms a blob.
Beat oleo, sugar and vanilla; beat all ingredients until whipped cream.

title: easy pasta fagioli
directions: Brown bacon in 2 tablespoons oil slow in large pot, then add onion, celery and garlic.
Cook until tender on medium heat (not brown), then add salt, oregano, pepper and spaghetti sauce.
Stir and cook 10 minutes.
Add water (1 quart); bring to a boil.
Stir in noodles and boil 15 minutes or until tender, then add beans and parsley.
Heat through.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: venison meat loaf
directions: Beat egg.
Add milk and bread crumbs.
Mix thoroughly with meat and seasonings.
Put in a loaf pan. Mix the mustard, ketchup and brown sugar.
Spread over top of meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Pour off excess grease, if necessary.

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Remove and discard the wing tips and separate each wing into 2 pieces at the joint.
Trim excess fat and skin. On a plate, stir together the flour, salt and pepper.
Coat the wings with the flour mixture and shake off the excess.
Heat oil in a deep fryer or deep, heavy pot to 375°.
Heat over medium heat until a corner of a wing held in oil makes a lively sizzle.
Add as many wings as will fit in a single layer without crowding; fry, turning once, until golden brown and cooked through, about 10 minutes.
Drain on paper towels and keep warm on a baking sheet in the oven.
Repeat with remaining wings.
Heat butter in a small saucepan over low heat until foaming.
Remove from the heat and stir in red wine vinegar and hot red pepper sauce.
Transfer the wings to a large mixing bowl, pour the sauce over the wings and toss until evenly coated.
Taste and adjust the seasonings.
Serve hot with celery sticks and dressing of your choice.

title: rice krispies ice cream pie
directions: Put butter and marshmallow cream in saucepan over low heat. Stir until syrupy.
Add Rice Krispies and mix until well coated. Press into buttered 9-inch pie pan to form a crust.
Fill with ice cream.
Put in freezer.
Serve with fresh fruit or frozen strawberries.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Add chopped onions and 3/4 of the cheese.
Mix soup, milk and sour cream together. Toss lightly with potatoes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Combine cranberries, raisins, sugar, spices and water in a large saucepan.
Simmer 15 minutes or until berries pop and mixture thickens.
Stir in onion, apple and celery; simmer 15 minutes longer or until mixture is thick.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix salt, sugar, mustard, vinegar and onion in blender so that onion is liquified.
Slowly add oil until dressing is thickened. Stir in poppy seed.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
Yields 3 cups.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar; add eggs one at a time, sifted dry ingredients, plums and nuts.
Pour in greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: emily's fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash off tomatoes; slice.
Salt and pepper both sides.
Put in a skillet over medium to high heat, turning heat down so they don't burn.
Make sure skillet has enough oil to coat the tomatoes. Before frying, coat tomatoes in a mixture of corn meal.
(I put salt and pepper in corn meal in addition to seasoning the tomatoes.)
Fry until brown.
Remove from skillet.
Drain off grease.
Put fried tomatoes on paper towels.
Serve hot.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Refrigerate.

title: oatmeal peanut butter candy
directions: Set oats aside in a large bowl.
Place peanut butter in bowl with oats.
Lightly grease wax paper with margarine.
The piece should be approximately 15-inches long.
Cook sugar, margarine, evaporated milk and vanilla in large skillet.
Bring to a boil. Lower heat and let boil until mixture reaches soft ball stage, 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Spoon onto greased wax paper.
Let cool for about 10 minutes.

title: turkey enchiladas(good for leftover turkey)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan saute onion and garlic in butter until onion is tender.
Add 1/4 cup olives, sour cream, soup and green chiles; mix well.
Reserve 3/4 cup sauce and set aside.
Stir in turkey and 1/2 cup cheese to the remaining sauce.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cottage cheese in large bowl.
Add dry Jell-O, then fold in oranges and pineapple.
Place in refrigerator until firm.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet.
Add in chili seasoning and stir.
Once chili seasoning is thoroughly absorbed throughout the beef, add in beans and picante sauce.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Beat egg, sugar and cheese for a few minutes.
Add milk, salt and vanilla.
Add almost all melted fat.
Mix with noodles and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch (or oval) baking dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Add chopped nuts and/or fruit, i.e. raisins, pears, etc.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour. Serve warm or cold.
Serves at least 12 people.

title: crema caramella
directions: Melt sugar in large skillet over medium heat until it turns a nut brown color.
Pour immediately into 1-quart ring mold and coat all sides.
Set aside.

title: english toffee popcorn balls(family favorite)
directions: Over medium heat, simmer all (except popcorn), stirring constantly.
Should form hard ball when a few drops are dropped into a cup of cold water.
Stir in 1/2 to 3/4 cup butter; stir until mixed.
Pour over cooked popcorn, stirring until evenly coated.
Beware of hot toffee.
Allow to cool slightly.
Rub hands with butter and form into balls.
Cool and cover individual balls with Saran Wrap (colored wrap for the holidays).

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms and chop into small pieces.
Fry bacon until crisp and crumble (save grease).
Add stems to bacon and fry for a couple of minutes.
Add Herb-Ox.
Crumble bread in food processor or blender.
Add bacon mixture to bread and then add cheeses to this.
Add grease, if needed, to form ball type dough.
Form into balls and stuff into mushroom caps.
Bake in foil-lined and covered pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: glazed ham
directions: Use Hamilton E Z carve ham.

title: finger jello
directions: Dissolve sugar and Jell-O in 4 cups boiling water.
Then dissolve 3 packages unflavored gelatine in 1 cup cold water.
Mix together; chill.
Cut into squares.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Drain strawberries, reserving 1/2 cup juice. Mix together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar. Make a hole in the center of mixture. Pour strawberries, eggs, oil and pecans into the hole. Mix by hand until all ingredients are thoroughly combined. Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans. Bake for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix ingredients and top with cracker
crumbs;
dot with butter.
Bake at 350° in greased loaf pan
for approximately 1 hour.

title: corn fritters
directions: Fryer setting: 375°.
Beat eggs 1 minute; add milk.
Add flour and baking powder, then add shortening.
Beat until blended, then add cream-style corn and vanilla.
(If needed, add more flour so that you can drop by large tablespoonfuls into hot oil.)
Fry 2 to 4 minutes, until light brown.
Serve with warm syrup.
May also use fruit for Fruit Fritters.

title: fudge nut pie(no crust)
directions: Mix
with
a
fork
butter or margarine and sugar.
Add flour, salt, cocoa, eggs, vanilla.
Add nuts.
Pour into a Pam sprayed or greased pie plate.	Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400°F for 40-45 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: homemade mayonnaise
directions: Beat egg yolks in small bowl with electric mixer at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Combine and add dry ingredients.
Beat again. Add oil, drop by drop, beating constantly.
When mayonnaise begins to thicken, add lemon juice.
Add remaining oil in a very thin stream, continuing to beat.
Store in refrigerator.

title: venison steak
directions: Tenderize steak.
Salt and pepper.
Dip in buttermilk and roll in flour.
Fry in deep fat fryer until golden brown.

title: frozen pumpkin dessert
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, salt and spices.
Add nuts.
In chilled bowl, fold mixture into ice cream.
Line bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with half the gingersnaps; top with half of ice cream mixture.
Cover with another layer of gingersnaps and remaining ice cream.
Freeze until firm (15 hours).

title: mexican chicken with rice
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper;	brown
in
oil. Remove from pan.	Add onion, peppers,
tomatoes,	red
pepper flakes and garlic in skillet.	Stir in broth and
bring
to
a boil.
Add rice.
Place rice mixture in bottom of
9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with chicken pieces.
Bake covered 1
hour
or until done at 375°.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake(makes 10 to 12 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
In bowl combine graham cracker crumbs, cocoa, sugar and butter.
Press evenly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add sweetened condensed milk, beating until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
In small bowl, toss 1/2 cup mini chips with flour to coat.
Stir into cheese mixture. Pour into prepared pan.
Sprinkle remaining chips evenly over top. Bake 1 hour.
Turn oven off.
Allow to cool in oven 1 hour. Remove from oven; cool to room temperature.
Refrigerate.

title: herb seasoning mix (spicy)
directions: Crush or grind all together.
Cover tightly.
Let stand overnight before using.
For table use, store in shaker.
Be sure herbs are finely ground.

title: cranberry cake
directions: Bake in a greased tube pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Sprinkle top with powdered sugar or frost.

title: mock chicken legs
directions: Cut the meat into 1-inch squares and place alternately on 4-inch skewers.
Press the meat together.
Add salt and pepper. Mix an egg with 1 teaspoon of cold water in a bowl.
Dip the pressed meat in the egg mixture, then roll the pressed meat in flour or fine bread crumbs.
Fry the pressed meat.
Place in pot. Cook up drippings with a little water and pour over meat.
Add mixture of 2 tablespoons each of celery, onion and green pepper on top.
Cover and steam on low heat for 1 hour (or finish in oven at 325° for an hour).
Makes 6.

title: dilly dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with vegetables, crackers, potatoes or corn chips.

title: pork hot dish
directions: Brown cut up pork; salt and pepper.
Place in Dutch oven or casserole.
Add chopped onion, sliced carrots and sliced potatoes. Heat soups, adding enough Cheez Whiz to have an orange color. Pour over meat and vegetables. Bake in slow oven, 275°, for about 3 hours.

title: pizza dough
directions: Put dry ingredients in food processor.
Add liquid ingredients and process until ball forms on top of blade.
Knead lightly by hand on floured counter.
Let dough rest about 15 to 30 minutes. Roll out on floured counter.
Put in greased pizza pan. Top with sauce, meat, cheese, etc.
Bake at 400° for about 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Makes two pizzas.

title: great grandma's holiday bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Grease pans.
Shape into loaves and let rise.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: liver and mushrooms
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper; dredge liver and brown in shortening.
Pour off drippings; add mushrooms (including liquid), soy sauce, parsley flakes, coriander and water.
Cover tightly and cook slowly for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tex-mex chili
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, cook beef, onions, garlic, chili powder, cumin and pepper until beef is browned and onion is tender, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together; stir just until combined.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool on a wire rack.
Wrap and store overnight.

title: zappels
directions: Mix all ingredients until creamy.
Cover and let rise 1 hour. Heat oil until hot.
Drop strings of dough into hot oil.
Cook until light brown.
Roll in confectioners sugar when cooled.

title: christy's brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and blend.
Sift flour and cocoa and add to mixture.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Pour into greased pan and bake about 30 minutes.
This is a light cake-type brownie.

title: crock brim pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and dry.
Layer dill between cucumbers in 4-gallon crock. Boil the water and salt to a rolling boil.
Cool slightly, then pour over cucumbers; weigh down with a plate and jug of water.
Cover cucumbers with a towel and clear the towel when they start to ferment.

title: old fashioned potato salad
directions: Mix potatoes, eggs, onions, celery and parsley in large bowl. In small bowl, combine oil, vinegar, salt, sugar and paprika. Pour over potato mixture.
Toss lightly to combine.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Just before serving, toss lightly with mayonnaise.
Put in serving container.
Sprinkle with additional chopped parsley.
Place in cool place until ready to serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: honey bear honey drink
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and mix well.
Serve cold.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Blend butter and peanut butter together.
Sift in confectionary sugar.
Add one Tbsp. of milk at a time and mix on low until well blended.
This frosting is very good with chocolate cake or German chocolate cake but have been told it is very good with yellow cake too.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix sugar, brown sugar, butter, eggs, vanilla and almond for about 1 minute.
Mix flour, salt and soda together.
Add to sugar mixture.
Mix about 2 1/2 minutes.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff. Add cream of tartar and beat again. Fold egg whites into nuts, sugar and crackers. Mix and pour into 9 x 13 pan. Bake 25 minutes at 350° until light brown. Cool thoroughly. Spread Cool Whip over cooled pie. Add drained pineapple over Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut. Chill and serve.

title: green stuff
directions: Pour pineapple into large bowl.
Add pudding and mix well. Fold in Cool Whip; add marshmallows.
Refrigerate.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
In bottom of pastry shell, sprinkle cheese, ham and onion.
Combine eggs, sour cream and seasonings and pour over ingredients in pie shell.
May top with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: stuffed french toast strada
directions: Cube bread and layer half in greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cube cream cheese over bread; put remaining bread on top of cheese. Mix egg, milk, syrup and butter mixture.
Pour over bread and press down to soak up.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with Cider Syrup.

title: dr. bird cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients; stir to moisten.
Do not beat.
Turn into an 8-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: southwestern chicken soup
directions: In a large skillet, saute the chicken in oil until lightly browned. Transfer to a 5 quart slow cooker with a slotted spoon. Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on low for 7-8 hours.
Stir before serving.

title: country-style doves
directions: Salt and pepper doves to taste.
Flour them and place in oiled skillet at medium heat.
Turn to brown evenly.
Remove birds and place on paper towel to drain.
Pour excess oil from pan.
Add flour to remaining drippings to make gravy and stir.
After paste begins to brown, add water to desired thickness.
Add chicken bouillon cubes to gravy.
Put doves back in gravy and top with onions.
Add milk and stir.
Cover and cook on low heat for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: cranberry-apple crunch
directions: Put cranberries and sliced apples in long pan.
Sprinkle with white sugar.
In a bowl mix oatmeal, brown sugar, flour, nuts and melted butter.
Pat mixture over cranberries and apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(If glass dish, bake 45 minutes.)

title: stir-fried vegetables
directions: Chop vegetables.
Heat oil in a large skillet.
Pour vegetables in skillet; season with salt and pepper and stir briskly.
Lower heat, cover and steam gently 5 to 8 minutes.
Stir again.
Add soy sauce to taste.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: roast of beef
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Place roast in a shallow open pan, fat side up.
Rub in a little flour, salt and pepper.
Put roast in oven and roast 5 minutes per pound for rare, 6 minutes per pound for medium and 7 minutes per pound for well-done.
Time exactly to the minute.
When cooking time has finished, turn off oven.
Do not open oven door at any time!!
Allow roast to remain in oven for 2 hours and, again, do not open oven door!!

title: chicken stock
directions: In your largest pot, combine all ingredients; cover with water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove chicken and vegetables and save for another use. Refrigerate stock in pot overnight.
Skim off fat.
Freeze in storage containers.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix together and bake in unbaked pie shell in a 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornmeal, flour and cornstarch; stir in eggs. Add milk, lemon juice, butter and lemon rind; mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake for 30 minutes longer or until filling is firm and lightly browned.

title: dairy-farmer's eggnog
directions: In a large saucepan, heat 1 quart milk with sugar to simmering, stirring constantly to prevent burning.
This can be heated in the microwave in a glass bowl.

title: easy pumpkin swirl
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pumpkin roll pan.
Line top and sides with wax paper.
Grease wax paper.
Beat eggs and sugar until fluffy.
Stir in pumpkin.
Add buttermilk mix a little at a time.
Stir well after each addition.
Add spices and mix well.
Pour in pan.
Spread evenly and sprinkle with nuts. Bake for 13 to 15 minutes.
Invert on towel dusted with powdered sugar.
Roll up cake and towel.
Unroll cake when cool and spread with filling.

title: sauerkraut cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, mix well and then add vanilla, salt and cocoa.
Sift together flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Alternating, add flour mixture and water. Fold in kraut by hand.
Bake in greased and floured pan for 35 to 45 minutes at 375°.
Use either one 9 x 11-inch pan or two regular round pans for a layer cake.
Frost with mocha, sour cream or cream cheese icing.

title: pineapple chess pie(like k & w's)
directions: Combine sugar and margarine.
Cream well and add eggs and flour, beating well.
Stir in pineapple and vanilla.
Pour in pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool thoroughly before serving.

title: wintermelon chicken soup
directions: Put chicken, carrots, mustard cabbage and ginger slices in crock-pot.
Cover with water and slow cook for 6 hours.
Put in wintermelon for last 3 hours.
Salt, pepper and shoyu to taste.

title: special roast
directions: Wrap roast in foil and place in roasting pan.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Drain potatoes and reserve liquid.
Cut onions in slivers and place it in with the potatoes around the roast.
Mix reserved liquid with mushroom soup and A.1.
steak sauce.
Pour mixture over potatoes.
Seal roast tightly and bake at 400° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: salmon cheese pate
directions: Blend all ingredients with mixer.
Place in a small bowl lined with plastic wrap.
Chill. Unmold.
Best when made one day ahead.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown ground beef with Ortega taco seasoning, salt and pepper, then drain.
Layer in casserole dish:
1 package crescent rolls (lay out flat), hamburger, salsa, shredded cheese, dash of chili powder, sour cream and 1 package crescent rolls (lay out flat). Bake at 350° until browned.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Over medium heat, put water, sugar, salt and cornstarch; stir constantly until thickens.
Add extract and cool off of stove burner.
Put strawberries on bottom, then filling on top.
Let cool fully, then top with whipped cream for an added touch.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend all ingredients. Be careful, not too much milk, and do not overblend.

title: rich brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and chocolate syrup.
Mix in flour, nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in jelly roll pan.

title: filled cookies
directions: Cream the shortening.
Add sugar, beaten egg, milk and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and baking powder, which has been sifted together.
Roll out thin on slightly floured board and cut with cookie cutter.
Place 1 teaspoonful of filling on each cookie; cover with another cookie and press edges together.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in a separate bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients; blend the two until it forms a ball. Refrigerate for 15 to 20 minutes, then roll out.
Yields 4 crusts.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Saute mushrooms and green peppers in butter.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Let bubble.
Slowly stir in chicken broth and cream.
Bring to a boil over low heat stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute. Add chicken and pimiento and heat through.
Serve in toast cups or pastry shells.

title: sukiyaki
directions: Saute onion in hot oil.
Add beef.
Saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Add celery, mushrooms, bamboo shoots, sugar, soy sauce and water.
Stir to mix well.
Cover; simmer about 10 minutes.
Arrange spinach on top of meat and vegetables.
Cover, simmer for 5 minutes or until spinach wilts and veggies are crisp tender.
Serve with hot seasoned rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: breaded pork chops
directions: Pork Coating Mixture:
Mix all ingredients except ribs or loin chops and milk.
Shake ingredients in medium plastic or paper bag. Dip pork ribs or loin chops in milk.
Shake each in pork coating mixture, coating both sides. Cook on rack in shallow roasting pan in a 425° oven until done and brown, 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Mix onions and other ingredients except cheese.
Pour into a baking dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes.

title: old fashioned beef stew
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Coat meat with flour mixture.

title: technicolor casserole(aka chicken spectacular)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.
To freeze, do not cook prior to freezing.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together.
Makes 1 punch bowl full.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Add milk.
Gradually add rest of ingredients and cook until thick.
Add coconut and stir. Pour into baked pie shells. Top with favorite meringue and bake at 350 degrees until brown.

title: connie's chicken recipe
directions: Melt margarine, soup and water together.
Pour rice in bottom of 8 to 14-inch pan.
Pour half of the soup mixture over rice and stir.
Place raw chicken pieces on top.
Pour remainder of soup mixture over chicken.
Bake in a 275° oven for 2 hours.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and save juice.
Use juice (about 3 cups). Sprinkle pudding and cook until thick.
Let cool.
Chop bananas and put in bowl.
Add about 3 tablespoons lemon juice.
Mix. Spoon out bananas.
Add all other fruit and mix with pudding.
This is a fat-free salad.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Beat well. Add bananas, flour, baking soda, salt and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine ingredients in order listed.
Spray baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours, or until done.

title: pasta salad
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, prepare macaroni according to package directions.
In colander, rinse with cold water; drain well.
In large bowl, combine macaroni, zucchini, tomatoes, olives, basil and garlic powder.
Add vinaigrette; toss to coat.
Cover; refrigerate at least 30 minutes before serving.

title: cranberry mousse
directions: Puree the first 3 ingredients.
Add gelatine in center for 20 minutes.
Add lemon juice and orange juice to pureed mixture. Whip the cream, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Fold in puree with gelatine and juices and serve.
Can be frozen.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, margarine and vanilla together.
Gradually add powdered sugar.
Knead together and shape into walnut size balls.
Set aside.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift dry ingredients, cut in shortening, add yeast and buttermilk.
Knead just enough to hold together.
Roll out on floured board 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with a biscuit cutter; dip in melted butter.
Let rise one hour.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until brown.
(Dough may be stored in refrigerator for up to one week.)

title: citrus drink
directions: Squeeze lemons, limes and oranges. Add water and sugar. Mix well. Keep cold.

title: pudding delight
directions: Mix pudding, milk and ice cream well.
Add Cool Whip.
Spread pudding mixture on cracker crust.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip.

title: eggplant fritters
directions: Peel and cube eggplant.
Cook in salted water (to cover, until tender).
Drain thoroughly and mash.
Beat egg.
Blend in flour, sugar, baking powder and eggplant.
Drop by spoonful in oil on medium heat.
Brown, then turn and brown on the other side.
If dough seems too soft, add more flour.
Place on paper towel to cool.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: To Serve:
Use 2 or more rounded teaspoons mix per cup of hot water.
Add 3 to 4 red hots, if desired.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in brown sugar.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Let cool.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: beer-steamed clams and mussels
directions: Saute lemon grass, ginger, garlic, chilies, onions and red pepper in olive oil.
Add beer, clam juice and lime juice.
Add mussels and clams.
Cover saute pan and steam until clams and mussels are fully opened.
Season to taste.
Divide clams and mussels equally into bowls.
Pour vegetables and broth over. Garnish with cilantro.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: orange sherbet jello
directions: Mix 2 jellos together.
Add boiling water.
After dissolved, add pineapple juice, orange sherbet and sour cream.
Use beater to smooth out lumps.
When smooth, add drained pineapple, bananas and drained mandarin oranges.
Pour in mold and chill.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: red lentil pate
directions: Bring water to boil, add lentils and cook 10 minutes.
Add onion and mushrooms, lower heat and cook 10 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients, blend well and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve on rice cakes, pita bread, tortillas or dip into vegetables.
Add more water as needed and cooking time may vary.
Lentils should be soft enough to serve as dip.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store; cover tightly.
Use 3 teaspoons per cup.
Add water.

title: pepper onion relish
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Boil gently until mixture is thickened and reduced about 1/2 in volume (about 45 minutes), stirring occasionally.
Pack the relish into hot jars.
Seal.
Process in boiling water for 5 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Put broccoli spears in the bottom of pan (thawed or raw). Layer chicken breasts on top.
Mix soup, mayo, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour on top of chicken.
Cover with grated cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: une fratte a la veande(hamburger pie)
directions: Brown meat and chopped onions with salt and pepper.
Drain well; place in pie shells.
In a large bowl, mix eggs, cottage cheese and Swiss cheese.
Spread over meat mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4 or 5.
Freezes well.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix well.
Drop from a teaspoon.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
May refrigerate dough and cook later (3 or 4 days).

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Mix all ingredients in large iron pot except cornstarch and crawfish.
Saute over medium heat and then add cornstarch and 1 cup water and let simmer for 20 minutes, stirring often.
Add crawfish and enough water to make a gravy and let simmer for 20 minutes more covered.
Serve hot over rice.

title: jacqy's ambrosia
directions: Add sugar to cream and whip.
Combine remaining ingredients and fold into whipped cream.

title: breakfast bread
directions: Grease Bundt or tube pan.
Layer about half of the rolls on the bottom.
Sprinkle half of the dry pudding mix over bread.
Mix together the brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle half the brown sugar over rolls followed by half of the pecans and half of the butter.
Repeat layers.
Cover with Saran Wrap and foil.
Leave out overnight to rise.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: apple ugly cake
directions: In mixing bowl, mix sugar, flour and soda, then stir in oil, eggs (slightly beaten), vanilla, salt and cinnamon.
Last of all, add apples and raisins.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan in 325° oven for approximately 30 to 35 minutes.
Watch closely.
Frost, if desired, or serve with a dollop of whipped cream.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend Marshmallow Fluff, cream cheese and Cool Whip until creamy.
Then slice fresh apples, nectaries, strawberries or any other fresh fruit.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mash avocado with fork until creamy.
Chop onion and add to avocado.
Add mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt; mix well.
Serve with your favorite chip.

title: strawberry refrigerator jam
directions: Mix berries, sugar and salt.
Boil water and Sure-Jell for 1 minute.
Stir in berries; cover and let stand overnight.
Next day, put in sterilized jars.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Sprinkle pineapple over syrup in sheet pan.
Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Pour batter over pineapple in pan.
Bake at 300° in a convection oven about 50 to 60 minutes.
Invert each portion on serving dish and garnish with whipped cream.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cinnamon and butter.
Place on stove; bring to a boil.
Pour into a casserole; top with cinnamon and butter.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: vera's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender. Peel and mash or chunk in large bowl. Mix margarine with potatoes while they are hot.
Mix onion, pickles, vinegar, pimientos, chilies and mayonnaise with potatoes. Add salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Cut boiled eggs in fourth and place on top of salad.

title: mushroom chicken
directions: Sprinkle garlic powder, m.s.g. salt, Accent, thyme, poultry seasoning and seasoning salt on chicken.
Bake chicken in oven in about 2 tablespoons butter at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Pour on mushroom soup.
Cut up onion and add.
Cook 1 to 2 cups rice.
Add to chicken and bake for 30 minutes more.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Add Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
Refrigerate.

title: spinach and artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small saucepan over medium heat, saute onions, celery and garlic in butter until tender.
In a separate bowl, combine sauteed mixture, cooked spinach, sour cream, artichoke hearts, hot pepper sauce, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour into a greased 2-quart baking dish. Top with the other 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes. Serve hot with warmed tortilla chips.

title: wiener schnitzel
directions: If using veal round steak, cut into 4 pieces.
Mix flour, salt, paprika and pepper; coat meat with flour mixture.
Pound until 1/4 inch thick.
Beat egg and water until blended.
Dip meat into egg mixture, then coat with bread crumbs.
Melt shortening in a large skillet; brown meat quickly.
Reduce heat; cover and cook about 45 minutes or until tender.
Serve with lemon wedges.
Serves 4.

title: beef rice hot dish(serves 25)
directions: Brown celery and onions in butter, add meat and brown.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease bottom only of a 10 x 14-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: peaches 'n cream pie
directions: Beat cheese until smooth; blend in sugar and 2 tablespoons milk.
Fold in 2 cups of the whipped topping and spread in crust. Top with diced peaches, pressing down lightly.
Chill.

title: cranberry orange bread
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda.
In separate bowl, combine egg, grated orange peel, orange juice and oil; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Fold in cranberries and nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 60 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan.
Cool.
Wrap and store overnight.

title: ruth's caramel corn
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients together for four minutes. Remove from heat and add baking soda and vanilla.
Stir into the popped corn.
Put in a large pan in a 200° oven for one hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: frozen cream cheese salad
directions: Roll crackers to fine crumbs.
Add sugar and oleo.
Line salad bowl with 2/3 of crumbs.
Save the rest to sprinkle on top.
Cream egg yolks, cream cheese, salt, sugar and vanilla.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and Cool Whip.
Pour in salad bowl and top with crumbs.
Freeze overnight.

title: special cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well in a large mixing bowl.
Roll into small balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 350 degrees for 10-12 minutes.
Yield:
180 cookies.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Mix 1 cup hot water with Jell-O.
Add the pie filling.
Mix. Before Jell-O sets up completely, add 1 small carton Cool Whip.

title: turkey taco bake
directions: First Layer: diced onion and celery.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Mix together and pour in Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until done.

title: browned butter frosting
directions: Heat butter over medium heat until delicate brown; cool.
Mix melted butter with powdered sugar.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix until fluffy.
Frosts a 13 x 9-inch cake or fills and frosts two 8 or 9-inch cake layers.

title: watergate dessert
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and bake 15 minutes in 9 x 13 pan. Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip; put on cold crust. Mix instant pudding with milk. Spread on top of cream cheese mixture. Top off with Cool Whip. Spread over entire pan. Sprinkle with coconut, nuts or chocolate curls.

title: fruit cookie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into a roll or log.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Place on wax paper and chill.
Serve.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Batter pork chops and fry until brown on both sides.
In a large casserole dish, layer sliced potatoes and onions.
Pour mushroom soup mixture over potatoes and onions.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put pork chops on top and cook in oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: nick's cinnamon-raisin bars
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Stir in water and raisins.
Cook over medium heat until thickened and bubbly; cool. Cream butter and sugar.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; stir into creamed mixture.
Add oats and 1 tablespoon water; mix until crumbly.
Firmly pat half the mixture in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread with raisin filling.
Mix remaining crumbs and 1 tablespoon water, spoon over filling and pat smooth.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes; cool.
For cinnamon icing, mix confectioners sugar and cinnamon.
Stir in enough milk for drizzling consistency.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Peel potatoes.
Grate them and add sugar, molasses, eggs, sweet milk and butter flavor.
Bake slowly until done.

title: caramel pie
directions: Completely submerge in water, cans of Eagle Brand milk.
Bring to a slow boil for about 2 hours.
Turn off and set for 30 minutes.
Open carefully and put in pie shell.
After pie is cooled, top with whipped cream.

title: paella
directions: If you don't have a paella pan, the broiler pan with your oven is large enough to use.
In Dutch oven, heat oil.
Add peppers and onions.
Cook until tender.
Add garlic, tomatoes and peas.
Stir in rice, salt and saffron.
Coat rice well and remove from heat. Transfer to prepared pan (sprayed with Pam).

title: 3-d map dough(for school projects, etc.)
directions: Mix water and salt together.
Gradually add flour, 1/2 cup at a time.
Stir until sticky and gooey.
Allow little hands to apply to plywood board and allow to dry for several days until hard and white.
Poster paint can be used to color the landscape.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Measure flour and sift, then sift all dry ingredients together. Combine all ingredients.
Do not use a mixer.
Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
No icing is necessary.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt margarine.
Add flour and stir.
Add milk gradually, stirring with a wire whisk.
Thicken.
Add cheese and stir.

title: sausage bread
directions: Squeeze sausages from casing into frying pan, chop up and brown evenly.
Drain meat on paper towel-lined plate.
Cool.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, margarine and sugar.
Add flour; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time; add milk, coconut flavoring and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into floured and greased tube pan.
Bake in 300° oven for 2 1/2 hours.
Yes, 2 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix stuff together.
Pour in long cake pan.
Put in oven and bake for 30 minutes. Take out and put on chocolate icing.
Let cool, then eat.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in sugar, pecans and crackers.
Pour into greased 12-inch dish.
Bake 25 minutes.
Completely cool.

title: grape jelly(recipe for diabetics.)
directions: Soften gelatine in water.
Bring grape juice to boil.
Remove from heat. Add softened gelatine, stirring to dissolve. Add sweetener. Bring to a full rolling boil.
Ladle into clear 1/2 pint jars.
Makes 2 (1/2 pint) jars.
Keep
in refrigerator.

title: grated potato pudding
directions: Dice onion and bacon fine.
Saute onion and bacon with 1/2 cup water until onion is transparent and water has evaporated.
Stir melted butter into the mixture.
Soak slice of bread in evaporated milk until completely saturated, stirring to break it up.
Set aside.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix ingredients together with mixer until smooth.
Beer is used to smooth consistency.
Serve dip in a hollowed out round loaf of bread.
Use extra bread from round loaf, cubed, for dipping!

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix corn, onion, pepper, pimentos, milk, margarine, cracker crumbs, salt and pepper to taste.
Put into a 13 x 9-inch casserole; top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave for 15 minutes, until set and cheese is melted. Serves 10.

title: lemon-orange salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in the 2 cups hot water.
Blend in pie filling until smooth.
Add orange pieces and drained pineapple. Put in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Refrigerate.
Before serving, frost with the Cool Whip.
Use as dessert or salad.
Very tasty.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the blueberries.
Drain juice off of the blueberries and fold berries into batter.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full and bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: broiled scallops
directions: Spray pam in baking dish. Place all above ingredients. Broil 10-13 minutes until white. Single serving.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, butter, onion, soup, salt, pepper and sour cream in large bowl. Spread in a 9 X 13 pan. Sprinkle crushed corn flakes on top and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour or until hash browns are tender.

title: cherry or blueberry delight
directions: Butter a 9 x 15-inch pan.
Layer the pie filling, crushed pineapple and juice.
Layer the dry cake mix.
Pour melted margarine on top, then sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
If you use cherry pie filling, chop fine with chopper.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Boil spinach and drain.
Mix sour cream and onion soup mix with spinach.
Pour in baking dish and top with French fried onions.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Simmer chicken with celery until tender. Remove from broth and reserve 1/4 cup broth. Shred chicken. Saute onion in oil. Cool broccoli and drain. Combine chicken, onion, broccoli, sour cream, soup and 2 tablespoons chicken broth in saucepan. Simmer 5 minutes.

title: crunchy peanut butter pie
directions: Beat peanut butter, powdered sugar and cream cheese real good. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust; chill several hours before serving.

title: potato soup
directions: Place bacon, onion and celery in the bottom of a large boiler and cook until vegetables are tender.
Sprinkle in flour and cook 3 minutes.
Add water, chicken broth and potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are soft.

title: barbecued potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
With knife, cut potatoes crosswise into thin slices.
Spray baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Place potatoes on pan.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients until well blended.
Spread evenly over potatoes.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are fork-tender.
Makes 4 servings; 160 calories; 4 grams fat; 0 cholesterol; 70 milligrams sodium. Calories from fat 23.

title: gooey squares
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup Pet milk.
Set aside.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix, 1/3 cup Pet milk, melted margarine and pecans until moist.
Press 1/2 of mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over mixture.
Pour caramels over chocolate chips.
Crumble remaining mix over top and bake 15 minutes longer.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: frozen strawberry meringue
directions: In a large bowl with mixer, beat egg whites until fluffy.
Add sugar, one tablespoon at a time, beating constantly until meringue is thick and glossy. Add 1 cup crushed strawberries. Beat on medium speed just to blend.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt and set aside.
Cream margarine and gradually add 3/4 cup sugar, vanilla and egg.

title: microwave quickie fudge
directions: Blend sugar and cocoa in an 8 x 8-inch microwave dish.
Pour in milk and place butter on top.
Cook on High heat for 2 minutes. Remove and stir until well mixed.
Add vanilla and nuts; stir well.
Place in freezer for 20 minutes.
Cut and serve.

title: carrot-raisin salad
directions: Finely chop carrots; mix all ingredients well.

title: picnic scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Divide potato slices into 3 portions. Liberally grease the bottom and sides of a 9-inch by 13-inch casserole.
Put one portion of the sliced potatoes in the bottom of the casserole and dot with half of the butter.
Spread around 7 slices of ham, 5 slices of cheese and half the onions.
Then sprinkle 2 tablespoons flour over the layer, and salt and pepper to taste.

title: philly fruit bread
directions: Blend cream cheese, oleo, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs; beat. Add flour, leaving 1/4 cup to stir into fruit.
Fold in fruit and nuts.
Pour in loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour; in small pans for 45 minutes.
Makes 4 small pans.

title: frozen strawberry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Break a few vanilla wafers into a blender; grate until desired consistency is reached.
Pour crumbs into a measuring cup.
Continue processing until 1 1/2 cups of crumbs are made.
Blender chop nuts to make 1/2 cup finely chopped nuts.
Combine crumbs, nuts and butter and blend thoroughly.
Press mixture firmly on bottom and sides of 10-inch pie plate.
Bake 10 minutes; cool.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish. Spread pecans, then coconut over bottom of dish.
Mix cake mix as directed and pour over coconut and pecans.
Mix 1 stick butter and cream cheese. Add confectioners sugar. Drop spoonfuls all over top of cake.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit cocktail cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Dissolve baking soda in hot water; add molasses.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to molasses, then add creamed mixture.
Fold in raisins and nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls on sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
These cookies keep well.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Prepare your favorite pie shell. Let cool. Dilute frozen orange juice with water. Add sugar to taste. Add 4 tablespoons cornstarch. Cook until mixture thickens. Remove from heat. Add 1 tablespoon almond flavoring. Cool before pouring over peaches. Slice peaches into pie shell. Pour cooled glaze over peaches. Chill. At time of serving, may top with cream, Cool Whip, yogurt or ice cream.

title: green pea dumplings
directions: Roll each biscuit and cut in strips.
Mix the peas, milk and butter, and bring to a boil.
Drop the strips of biscuit dough into the pea mixture a few at a time.
Cook about 2 minutes.

title: jubilee sauce
directions: Melt butter; add sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, for 3 to 4 minutes (mixture will become slightly opaque).
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in evaporated milk.
Add the lemon juice and beat vigorously.
Serve hot or cold.
The sauce may separate while in refrigerator.
If this happens, beat vigorously until it resumes original appearance. Serve over fruit cake, bread, puddings, etc.

title: rolled fillet of sole casserole
directions: About 45 minutes before serving, in small bowl, mix Parmesan cheese, pepper and 1/4 cup chopped parsley.
Sprinkle fillets with salt.
Pat parsley mixture on one side of each fillet.
Roll fillets, with parsley side in, jelly roll fashion.
Place fillets, seam side down, in shallow 2-quart casserole or 11 x 7-inch glass or ceramic baking dish.

title: cucumber salad
directions: After slicing cucumbers very thin, sprinkle with salt; let set about 20 minutes.
Squeeze the cucumbers and discard juice.
Mix other ingredients with cucumbers.
Mix well and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: get together punch
directions: Day Before:
Pour 1 can Punch in a 1 1/2-quart ring mold; freeze.

title: meringue
directions: Beat whites, salt and water until stiff. Then add sugar. Beat until sugar dissolves. Beat until very thick and fluffy. Spread on pie and brown slowly.

title: sonya's lemon pie
directions: Mix ingredients together, pour into pie crust.
Put in freezer.

title: pineapple-coconut cake
directions: Mix everything in mixer and then beat.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan about 40 to 45 minutes or when toothpick is dry.
Bake at 325°.

title: mary kohr's baked stew
directions: Mix together in large casserole or pot.
Bake, covered, for 3 hours at 350°.
Serve over noodles.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans well and place in lightly greased casserole dish. Pour soup over beans.
Top with onion rings.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix in double boiler and cook 5 minutes after all is blended. Store in refrigerator.

title: banana pudding
directions: Add lemon juice and vanilla to pudding, milk and sour cream. Beat well and fold in 1 cup Cool Whip. Layer your vanilla wafers and bananas in a 9 x 13 glass baking dish. Put 1/2 pudding on that and then repeat another layer. Cool and then put the rest of the Cool Whip on the top.

title: lo-cal baked potatoes
directions: Mix onion soup mix and oil.
Add raw potatoes that have been washed and diced with or without peeling.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8. Exchanges:
1 bread and 1/2 to 1 fat.

title: beef and bean barbecue bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown meat; drain.
Add pork and beans, barbecue sauce, onions and salt.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in 1/4 pound Velveeta cheese (chop in cubes).
Pour in 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: raspberry vinegar
directions: Heat, but do not boil, the vinegar.
Add sugar.
Dissolve the sugar in hot vinegar.
Place berries in jar or bottle and pour warm vinegar over the berries.
Before capping, allow the liquid to cool to room temperature.
Fix top tightly and place in sunny window spot for 1 to 2 weeks.
Store in cool place.
As the berries soften and loose their shape, strain and rebottle the vinegar.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix well and press in 9 x 13 dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool completely.

title: easy sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all 3 ingredients together in large casserole.
Bake at 350° about 1/2 hour.
This is a good dish to take to a party. Looks appetizing with the various colors.

title: appetizer franks
directions: Grease shallow baking dish with cooking oil spray.
Cut franks into one-inch pieces.
Cut bacon strip in half.
Wrap 1/2 strip bacon around each frank piece and place (bacon end down) in baking dish.
Sprinkle light brown sugar evenly over top of all bacon wrapped frank pieces until covered.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until bacon is crisp.
Poke toothpick into each frank piece and place on serving platter.
Very tasty and easy to make.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, celery, olives, onions and mayonnaise together. Add cheese and put in casserole dish.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: avocado salad
directions: Mix jello in 1/2 cup hot water.
Cool, but not set.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill thoroughly before serving.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Combine chicken, soup and water in saucepan.
Heat.
Mix Bisquick and milk in separate bowl.
Pour chicken mixture into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Dip spoon in hot chicken mixture, then dip spoon into batter.
Put spoonful of batter on top of chicken mixture.
Repeat dipping until all dumpling batter is used.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet 'n sour chicken
directions: Roll chicken pieces in flour, salt and pepper.
Dip in buttermilk, then roll again in flour.
Fry until golden brown. Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix soup with liquid from 1 can of asparagus.
Drain balance of asparagus.
Alternate ingredients in casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 400° until bubbly.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend ingredients for about 30 seconds.

title: dorito bean dip
directions: In an 8 x 8-inch dish, spread cream cheese in bottom of dish. Spread finely chopped onion over cheese; next, spread chili with beans.
Grate Monterey Jack cheese; sprinkle over beans. Microwave until cheese melts, or put in oven.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, cocoa and milk together in saucepan; boil one minute and add remaining ingredients.
Blend.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: crab spread
directions: Drain crab and rinse with clear water.
Loosen with a fork and set aside.
Spread cream cheese and milk mixture onto pizza pan or platter.
Cover with sauce mixture.
Sprinkle loose crab meat on top.
Chill until time to serve.
Use a small knife to spread on crackers.

title: broccoli and rice and cheese casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Cook broccoli and rice separately.
Combine all ingredients and stir it all together. Bake in 2-quart casserole dish, slightly greased.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: pea salad
directions: Dissolve sugar in water. add oil and vinegar. Mix well and add first 6 ingredients and let set over night.

title: chopped apple cake with lemon sauce
directions: Combine first 11 ingredients and bake at 350° until done.

title: oven omelet
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In oven, melt butter in 13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Tilt dish to coat bottom with butter.
In large bowl, beat eggs, sour cream, milk, salt and garlic until blended.
Stir in onions and cheese.
Pour in buttered dish.
Bake until eggs are set, but still moist, about 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream first 6 ingredients.
Work in flour.
Dough will be very stiff.
Shape into 24 small balls.
Place on cookie sheets (12 per sheet).
Press lightly with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake 10 to 13 minutes at 350°.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: pizza porcupine patties
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Reserve 1 cup of the tomato sauce.
Mix remaining sauce, the ground beef, rice, chilies, salt, garlic salt and oregano.
Shape into 6 patties 1/2 inch thick.
Place in ungreased baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Bake uncovered 15 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time; beat after each addition.
Add milk; stir thoroughly.
Add coconut, nuts and crumbled wafers; mix.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Chop cranberries (can be put in a blender or food processor).
Peel and slice apples thin.
Add sugar to pineapple, cranberries and apples.
Mix well.
Let stand for 15 minutes. Fold in remaining ingredients.
Freeze in 2 loaf pans.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir in apples last.
Bake 1 hour or longer in Bundt pan at 325°.

title: gourmet dinner
directions: Begin with the 3 sniffs to select direction of meal.
Check the watch to be sure it is near mealtime.
Choose as the main course beef, pork, chicken, seafood or whatever the selected neighbor happens to be serving.
Knock on the door about 20 minutes before mealtime.
Be sure you have the hearty appetite.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes and onions until tender. Drain and put in large dish. Cook butter, flour, salt and milk until thick. Then add cheese. Stir until cheese is melted. Pour over potatoes and bake at 400° until bubbly and brown.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl and beat until blended. Pour into well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: applesauce raisin cake
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and eggs; beat.
Add flour, soda, baking powder, salt, allspice, applesauce and raisins.
Mix all together.
Bake in loaf pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mini calzones
directions: Flatten biscuits out on baking sheet.
Put some ham on each biscuit; top with cheese.
Shake on a little grated cheese and seasoning.
Fold biscuits over so ingredients are in middle.
Bake in preheated oven at 425°, approximately 15 minutes.

title: yeast dough
directions: Blend together milk, sugar, lard, salt and egg. In 1/4 cup warm water, dissolve yeast, then add to milk mixture. Add enough flour to make a soft dough. Let rise until double in bulk, then make into rolls, coffee cake, cinnamon rolls, whatever you desire.

title: lizzie juday's cranberry salad
directions: Grind or chop cranberries & fruit.
Add sugar.
Dissolve jello in hot water and cool a bit.
Then mix with the fruit.
You may add chopped nuts, celery or crushed pineapple, drained well.
I usually double this for holiday family gatherings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Cut apples in slices 1/2-inch thick. Put in buttered dish. Mix water and cinnamon. Pour over sliced apples. Mix flour, butter and sugar. Spread over apples. Bake about 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; add onion and mushrooms while browning.
Then add mushroom soup and stir.
Put frozen Tater Tots on top of casserole.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Use a casserole dish.

title: classic lemonade
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan, stirring over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Boil about 1 minute.
Strain; discard rind and cool.
Add lemon juice and ice water; pour over ice and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot turkey or chicken salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together, except potato chips.
Heap into individual baking dishes or a 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle the crushed potato chips on top.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli and sweet pepper stir-fry
directions: Peel tough broccoli stems.
Cut stems and flowerets into pieces 1 1/2-inches long.
Blanch in large pot of boiling water for 2 to 3 minutes, until bright green and tender-crisp.
Drain; cool under cold running water.
Dry on paper toweling.

title: italian garden salad
directions: In a large skillet, combine ingredients with 1/4 cup water. Bring to a boil; stir occasionally.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, 5 minutes.
Cool, then refrigerate at least 24 hours.
Drain well. Makes 6 antipasto servings.

title: saucepan brownies
directions: Melt oleo and chocolate in heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring often.
Beat in eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Blend well. Add flour and baking powder into chocolate mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Add nuts and blend again.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream well the oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each one.
Dissolve soda and buttermilk to mixture. Add flaked coconut.
In a paper sack or bowl, put your flour, dates, chopped pecans and orange slice candy (cut up).
Mix all this or shake in bag until coated with all the flour.
Add to creamed mixture; stir well.
Pour in a greased tube pan that has wax paper in the bottom.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Combine real orange juice (1 cup) and 2 cups powdered sugar.
Pour over cake.
Let set until cake is cold.

title: cowboy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy. Add dry ingredients and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen cookies.
Nuts can be omitted and coconut added.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Beat Eagle Brand milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Add Bisquick and vanilla.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 6 to 8 minutes at 325°.
Remove from oven and place a Hershey's Kiss in the center of each cookie.

title: chocolate brownie pie
directions: Mix in large bowl; pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 400° until knife inserted comes out clean.
Foil around pie crust edge may be used to keep it from becoming too done during baking.

title: jogging in a jug(vinegar health drink)
directions: Mix in large container.
Drink 3 ounces a day.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix shortening and sugar together.
Beat in one egg at a time. Mash up bananas and add to mixture.
Add nuts, flour and soda. Bake at 325° for approximately 55 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf pan. Double ingredients for full size cake pan or 2 loaves.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions, then drain. Return to stove on low heat and add margarine and Velveeta cheese. Stir until melted, then pour into casserole dish.
Crumble Ritz crackers on top to cover.
Lay 3 to 4 pats of butter on top of crackers.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350° or until crackers are golden brown.

title: mexican chicken rice
directions: Put chicken, oleo, olives, capers, onion, pepper and tomatoes in large pan.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook until chicken is done.
Remove chicken from bone.
Add rice and water. Cover pan and cook until rice is tender.
Serves 4.

title: smoked oyster dip
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, mixing well.
Stir in oysters.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Break up sausage; fry until almost done.
Add celery, bell pepper and onion; saute until limp.
Drain grease; add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(May uncover for last 15 minutes.)

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Topping: Mix the jello with 1 cup boiling water. Add the strawberries. Mix and cool in the refrigerator until thick.

title: waffle cookie
directions: Melt first two ingredients and blend.
Add remaining ingredients and drop on waffle iron.
Bakes in less than a minute.

title: chicken club sandwich
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Toast bread, then spread first slice with a little mayonnaise.
Cover with 1 or 2 lettuce leaves and slices of chicken.
Spread a little more mayonnaise on the chicken and cover with a second slice of toast.
Spread a very small amount of mustard on the toast, then a little mayonnaise.
Cover with bacon and tomato slices.
Place third slice of toast on top and press down firmly.
Serves 1.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix as listed.
Mix 1/2 cup grated cheese in mixture and the other 1/2 cup on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: summer rice salad
directions: Cook brown and Wehani rice in pot.
In skillet or wok, saute broccoli rabe, beans and parsley in olive oil.
When rice is done, pour over juice of two lemons and let cool.
Mix sauteed mixture with rice and chill.
Season to taste with black pepper.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix chicken broth, chicken soup and 3 cans water and bring to a boil.
Break flour tortillas into small pieces and add to hot liquid.
Add chicken.
Cook about 30 minutes at slow boil.
Stir occasionally.
Add small amounts of water at a time if mixture gets too thick.

title: frozen mocha cheesecake
directions: In small bowl, combine crumbs, sugar and margarine.
In buttered 9-inch spring-form pan or 13 x 9-inch baking dish, pat crumbs firmly on bottom and up sides of pan.
Chill.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Add Eagle Brand and chocolate syrup.
In small bowl, dissolve coffee in water.
Add to Eagle Brand mixture.
Mix well.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into prepared pan.
Cover.
Freeze 6 hours or until firm.
Garnish with additional chocolate crumbs (if desired).
Return leftovers to freezer.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: game time hamburger buns
directions: In saucepan, heat butter over low heat.
Add milk, salt and honey and heat mixture to 100° to 110°.
Remove from heat.
Combine yeast and warm water in mixing bowl, stirring until dissolved.
Add the milk mixture.
Stir in whole wheat flour and 1 cup white flour and stir until batter is smooth.
Gradually add enough white flour to make a soft, workable dough.
Turn out on a lightly floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Round into a ball and place dough in a warm, buttered bowl, turning to coat the top.
Cover loosely with plastic wrap and a towel.
Place in a pan of warm water, about 98°, and let rise for about 15 minutes.
Butter 2 large baking sheets.
Punch down dough and divide into 16 portions.
Cup in hands and rotate quickly to make smooth bun.
Place on sheets 1 inch apart and flatten each bun slightly.
Cover and let rise for 15 minutes.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake buns 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cauliflower-broccoli medley
directions: Separate cauliflower and broccoli into bite size pieces. Combine with onions in large bowl. Combine remaining ingredients, except bacon. Mix well and pour over vegetables and toss gently. Chill several hours or overnight. Garnish with bacon.

title: ding bat cookies(no bake)
directions: Mix together dates, margarine, egg and sugar and cook in a pan until thick, then let cool.
Add vanilla, nuts and Rice Krispies. Take a teaspoonful and roll in coconut.
Lay on wax paper to dry.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the shortening with the sugars.
Add eggs and beat well. Blend in cinnamon, baking soda and milk.
Add oats, flour and raisins.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: peach chutney
directions: Place brown sugar, onion, green pepper, raisins, ginger, garlic, chili peppers, vinegar, mustard seed and cayenne pepper and salt in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and cook over medium heat 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
While this is cooking, bring large saucepan of water to boil.
Add 3 or 4 peaches at a time.
Boil until skin loosens (1 minute).
Place in cold water to cool.
Peel, pit and slice into thin pieces.
Add peaches to cooked mixture and cook 1 hour and 30 minutes more over medium heat.
Stir to prevent sticking until mixture thickens. Pour into hot pint jars and process 10 minutes.
Makes 4 pints. Good with meats or can be used as appetizers with cream cheese and crackers.

title: squash pies
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, squash, coconut extract and lemon extract in medium bowl; mix well.
Stir in flour and butter.
Spoon into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese, pineapple, 1 cup pecans, peppers, onion and salt. Form into ball.
Press remaining cup of pecans to top and sides of cheese ball.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and butter.
Stir over medium heat, constantly.
Time for 3 or 4 minutes after it comes to a rolling boil.
Do not stir while it is boiling.
Remove from heat, add vanilla, marshmallow and peanut butter.
Stir quickly until blended well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into well-greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: judy's granny cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, soda and salt together.
Add eggs and pineapple.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread on brown sugar and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger with chopped onion.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: poppy seed bran muffins
directions: Beat eggs; stir in orange juice.
Add the other ingredients until blended.
Fill 2/3 full in muffin cups.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: broccoli-noodle casserole
directions: Boil together the first 3 ingredients.
Add the dry noodles. Cook until almost done. Drain, then add 1/2 stick butter.
Cook the broccoli until tender. Drain, then add 1/2 stick butter.
Mix the broccoli and noodles. Add the sour cream and cheese.
Put in casserole and sprinkle with the almonds.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet and drain off liquids.
Stir in salt, pork 'n beans, barbecue sauce, and brown sugar.
Heat until bubbly, then pour into oven-proof bowl.
Cut biscuits in half and put around edge of the bowl.
Sprinkle cheese over bread and bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: green banana fruit salad
directions: Chop apples.
Peel orange and pull sections apart and slice. Slice strawberries.
Peel and slice banana.
Measure the fruit. Put fruit into a big mixing bowl.
Mix Cool Whip with yogurt in small bowl.
Pour topping over fruit.
Eat!
Delicious!

title: pineapple cream dessert
directions: In a 9X13-inch pan, bake cake at 350 for 10-12 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese in a bowl.
Pile lightly in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° until heated through and cheese is melted, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: santa fe spaghetti bake
directions: You will need a 9 x 13-inch pan or any baking dish that will hold this amount of spaghetti.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease tube or Bundt pan.
Cut biscuits into quarters and shake in plastic bag with mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Place biscuits in pan and sprinkle with nuts and raisins, if desired. Combine remaining sugar mixture and margarine in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before removing.

title: heavenly hash salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip with nuts, coconut and fruit cocktail.
Cut apple and banana into small pieces.
Add to Cool Whip mixture and chill.

title: casserole for a crowd
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Cook until tender; add remaining ingredients except crumbs.
Put into 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned sugar cream pie
directions: Sift together sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in 1 cup cream to make a paste.
Stir paste until very smooth, then add the remaining cup cream.
Beat lightly.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell; sprinkle with cinnamon and dot with 1 tablespoon butter. Bake in 400° oven for 15 or 20 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 325° or 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
