title: pimento cheese
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler, then add rest of ingredients, except mayonnaise.
Cook 30 minutes in double boiler.
Take off stove.
Add mayonnaise.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into container and refrigerate.

title: white fruit salad
directions: Cook dressing (last 4 ingredients) in double boiler until as thick as it will get.
Cool.
Whip 1/2 pint whipping cream.
Fold in cold dressing.
Pour over fruit mixture and let stay in refrigerator overnight.

title: rhubarb freezer jam
directions: Mix all together in a 4-quart saucepan.
Let heat to boil; cook 20 minutes.
Skim off any foam on top.
Cool and put in containers.
Freeze.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: grandma phillip's banana bread
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, eggs and mashed bananas.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.

title: cherry cheese delights
directions: Put 1 vanilla wafer in each cupcake liner.
Cream the cheese. Beat the eggs and blend into the creamed cheese.
Add the remaining ingredients except the pie filling.
Spoon the cheese mixture into the cupcake liner 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Remove from cupcake tin and cool.
Spoon filling on top when cool.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Have butcher cut a pocket on the bone side of each pork chop. Combine all ingredients and mix well; stuff each chop with this mixture.
Place in greased shallow pan and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until chops are tender.

title: pecan squares
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together. Add vanilla, eggs and molasses. Mix thoroughly.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water over oatmeal and let stand.
Mix sugars, oleo and eggs.
Add oatmeal mixture, flour, cinnamon, soda, salt and vanilla.
Bake at 350° in an 8 x 8-inch pan for 45 minutes.
Double ingredients for 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except for cracker crumbs). Bake in a well buttered pan at 350° for 1 hour then put cracker crumbs on top.
Bake another 10 minutes. Serve with rice. Delicious and easy.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook one large fryer chicken.
Cool and dice meat.
Add all ingredients.
Mix well and chill.
Serve on lettuce or as sandwiches.

title: taco pie
directions: Press biscuits into 9 x 13-inch baking dish (spray dish). Brown turkey, peppers, onions and bouillon in pan.	After this is well browned, add tomato paste, water and taco seasoning*.	Put 1/2 mixture on unbaked biscuits.
Spread 1/2 cheese on top of meat.
Put remainder of meat on top of cheese and cover with remainder of cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs until frothy.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Continue beating until mixture is thick and foamy.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
In a separate bowl, stir together flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and walnuts until thoroughly blended.
Stir gently into zucchini mixture just until blended.
Spoon batter equally into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until bread begins to pull away from sides and a cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Turn out onto racks to cool completely.

title: pork b~b~q cole slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, carrot, and red cabbage.
Pour dressing over cabbage until moist and stir.
Refrigerate.
Add salt and pepper to taste just before serving.

title: refrigerator muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate at least 6 hours.
Bake muffins 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Refrigerate batter, covered, up to 6 weeks.

title: lasagna sandwiches
directions: In skillet, cook meat until brown; drain off fat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Cook ground beef; drain.
Add onion and enchilada sauce to beef mixture; set aside.
Mix cheese, mushroom soup and chilies together.
Line bottom of 2 greased 9 x 13-inch pans with enough sauce to cover.
Roll meat mixture in 25 tortilla shells and pack closely in casseroles.
Cover with remaining sauce.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Combine the onions and garlic in a large saucepan and cook, covered, over low heat until soft, stirring frequently and adding a little water if necessary to prevent scorching.
Add all other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Cook over medium heat until bubbling hot.
Serve in bowls.

title: bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter 2 loaf pans.
Chop mandarin peel and place in enough water to barely cover.
Cook over low heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add more water if necessary.
Add 1 cup sugar and boil for 10 minutes, until thick and syrupy.
Cream the butter with 1/2 cup sugar, add the egg and milk.
Mix the flour, baking powder, and salt.
Add to the batter, beat well.
Add the cooked mandarin peel and syrup.
Put in prepared pans.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on racks.
Makes 2 small loaves.

title: chicken almond casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread 1/2 chicken in bottom of 2-quart greased casserole.
Top with mushrooms, chestnuts, almonds and onions.
Arrange remaining chicken on top.
Cover with chicken sauce.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add dry mixture alternately with milk and vanilla.
Bake in a greased tube pan for 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: pickled peppers
directions: Pack raw peppers into jars.
Bring vinegar, water and sugar to a hard boil; pour the hot liquid into jars and seal.
Makes 6 pints.

title: roasted corn and black beans
directions: Cook black beans until tender; do not overcook.
Drain.
Pour olive oil in a frying pan and heat.
Place garlic, jalapeno pepper and onions in pan.
Saute until the onions are tender, translucent and start to take on some color.
Add corn, black beans, cilantro, tomatoes and lime juice.
Stir well and toss this mixture over high heat, until all ingredients are very hot.
Serve at once.
Yields 10 portions.

title: peanut butter thumbprints
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, beat butter, brown sugar and peanut butter until well blended.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Stir together flour, baking powder and baking soda. Gradually add to peanut butter mixture.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls; roll in peanuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until cookies are just set.
Press thumb gently in center of each cookie; cool slightly.
Remove from cookie sheet to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Prepare Thumbprint Filling. Spoon or pipe about 1/2 teaspoon filling into each thumbprint. Makes about 8 dozen cookies.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven 350 degrees.
Melt chocolate and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks one at a time, beating well after each. Blend in vanilla and chocolate.
Sift flour with soda and salt. Add alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture.
Beat after each addition until smooth.
Fold into beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 prepared 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Cool.
Frost tops only using Coconut-Pecan Frosting.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour the oil into a 13x9x2 inch pan.
Tilt pan until bottom is covered with oil.
Put remaining ingredients into pan and stir until well blended.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35-45 minutes until a toothpick inserted near center of cake comes out clean.

title: spicy hot tea punch
directions: Combine 1 quart water, sugar and spices.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes; strain.
Bring 1 quart water to a boil and pour over tea bags.
Steep 5 minutes.
Combine with spice mixture and juices.
Boil remaining 3 quarts water and add to mixture.
Refrigerate unused portion and reheat as needed. Serves 35 people.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Join dough pieces and spread over a jelly roll pan and bake for 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown and allow to cool.
Cream sour cream, Ranch dressing, onions and cream cheese.
Spread creamed mixture across the pastry.
Add a variety of chopped fresh vegetables to top the pastry.
Cut to appetizer size pieces and chill.

title: tofu pecan meatballs
directions: Mash tofu.
If using regular firmness, blend in blender or food processor until smooth.
Mix all ingredients together.
Let set in refrigerator to thicken before forming into balls.
After forming balls, bake on lightly oiled cookie sheet in 350° to 400° oven for 30 minutes or until browned (turn after 10 to 15 minutes).
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan and boil over medium heat until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell. Cool and serve with whipped topping.

title: sausage bread
directions: Cook sausage with seasonings.
Drain.
Roll bread dough until flat.
Add meat and cheese. Fold bread dough over to form jelly roll.
Let rise.
Bake at 325° until brown.

title: the ultimate bar cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine brownie mix, oil, water and egg in mixing bowl; stir to blend, about 50 strokes.
Spread batter in prepared pan.
Sprinkle evenly with butterscotch and chocolate morsels, coconut and pecans.
Pour condensed milk over entire mixture and spread carefully.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until coconut turns golden brown. Cool in pan on wire rack.
Cut into 2 x 1-inch bars.
Makes 48 bars.

title: laura's baked chicken
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Pour over chicken that has been placed in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place in a 325° to 350° oven for about 1 hour. Easy to burn so check as time nears end.

title: apricot jello
directions: Boil together nectar and Jell-O until Jell-O is dissolved. Add pineapple and set to jell.
Whip the whipped topping with cream cheese.
Spread over set Jell-O and sprinkle with nuts.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, walnuts and butter.
Bake in shallow pan at 350° for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Sprinkle 2/3 of crumbs into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Combine egg whites, berries, lemon juice and sugar.
Beat at high speed for 10 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip and spoon over crumbs.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs. Freeze for 6 hours.
Serve frozen.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix real good without mixer.
Drop by teaspoonfuls in small muffin tins (30). Bake at 435° for 10 minutes.

title: apricot chicken stir-fry
directions: In a small bowl, soak apricots in water; set aside (do not drain).
Combine flour, cilantro (if desired), salt and pepper. Sprinkle over the chicken and set aside.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Chop up cooked chicken breasts and spread in bottom of a 9-inch casserole dish.
Combine soup and sour cream; pour over chicken. Sprinkle dressing mix on top and pour chicken broth over dressing mix.
Cover with foil.
Cook in a 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients in order directed on box using quantities and casserole size given here.
Cover; microwave 18 to 20 minutes on "6" or until potatoes are tender and most of liquid is absorbed.

title: angel food special
directions: Break cake into pieces in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Prepare the vanilla pudding according to package directions.
Beat the vanilla ice cream into the pudding; pour over cake pieces. Combine the jello with 1 cup hot water.
Mix in the frozen strawberries; pour over top of cake and pudding.
Put in refrigerator.
Let stand until cold.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, mix meat, soup mix, eggs, catsup, bread crumbs, and water. Shape into loaf pan and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine margarine, cream cheese and sugar; blend well.
Add eggs one at a time; blend well after each.
Gradually add flour and vanilla.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Add beaten eggs, sugar and oil together.
Sift flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder; add to egg mixture and blend well.
Add vanilla, nuts and zucchini.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until tests done.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Make a well in center of meal.
Add beaten eggs, sour cream, shortening, then corn, mix well.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased skillet.
Add grated cheese and peppers.
Now cover with rest of batter.
Sprinkle with bacon bits.
Cook at 375 degrees 30 to 40 minutes until brown.

title: apple sauce cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and spice together.
Cream sugar and margarine well adding apple sauce and eggs, one at a time, then slowly add flour mixture and mix well.
Have oven preheated at 350 degrees.
Have cookie sheet ready and drop by spoon full onto sheet.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.
Bake about 15-20 minutes.

title: four layer chocolate and vanilla dessert
directions: In bowl, cut butter into flour until crumbly.
Stir in 3/4 cup of pecans.
Press mixture evenly over bottom of baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes; cool.
In small bowl, beat cream cheese on low speed until fluffy.
Beat in powdered sugar and half of the thawed Cool Whip topping.
Spread over crust; chill.
In large bowl, combine both pudding mixes with milk.
Beat with rotary beater two minutes.
Spoon over cream cheese layer.
Chill or freeze until firm (several hours or overnight).
Top with remaining chopped pecans.

title: glazed almonds
directions: Heat almonds, sugar and butter in heavy skillet over medium heat, stirring constantly until almonds are toasted and sugar is golden brown, about 15 minutes.
Sugar should be syrupy.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Spread mixture onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Allow to harden.
Break apart.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter, Crisco, sugar, milk and vanilla.
Beat until creamy at medium speed.
Add egg; beat until blended.
Add dry ingredients on low speed.
Drop by teaspoonfuls or flatten with crisscross pattern with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake in 375° oven for 7 to 8 minutes or until cookie cracks.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: creole red beans and rice
directions: Cover beans with fresh water.
Add all ingredients and meat. Cook slow and long.
Serve over cooked rice.
Garnish with green onions, serve with cornbread and salad.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients together adding the 4 eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Fold in chocolate chips.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, cardamon and salt. Combine beaten eggs and 1 cup milk.
Pour into flour mixture and stir until smooth.
If batter is too heavy, add additional milk. Batter should pour in a heavy stream.

title: chicken in wine
directions: Pour first 2 ingredients over chicken.
Cook covered at 400° for 1/2 hour.
Turn up to 450° and remove cover for another 1/2 hour.
(Turn after 45 minutes.)

title: best baked beans(serves 8)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bacon, in an oiled 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Lay bacon strips over top.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: jogging in a jug
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Drink 1/4 cup every day.
Makes you really feel good, as when you jog.

title: creamed onions with almonds
directions: Place
onions
in
buttered casserole.	Pour sauce over and combine
with cheese and sherry.
(May refrigerate at this point.) When ready	to
use, bake in 350° oven until thick and bubbly. Sprinkle
with
almonds
during
last
minutes
of baking. Goes well with fish dishes.

title: crunchy granola
directions: Mix all ingredients, except raisins, together with electric mixer.
Spread evenly on 2 baking sheets with edge.
Bake in a 250° oven until golden brown, 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Turn and stir after 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and add raisins.
Cool and stir in plastic bag.

title: beet pickles
directions: Boil beets.
Mix vinegar, sugar, cinnamon sticks, cloves and 2 cups of water beets were boiled in.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Rinse beets.
Take off skins and cut to desired size.
Pack into quart jars and pour liquid over.
Seal.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: hot fish potato salad
directions: Saute celery and onion in bacon fat until tender; combine sugar, flour, paprika, salt and celery seed.
Stir mixture into sauteed vegetables.
Add vinegar and water gradually.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add potatoes, bacon and fish; mix lightly, cover and cook over low heat for 10 minutes until fish flakes easily when tested with fork; sprinkle with parsley.

title: pizza spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti (directions on box), drain, rinse and set aside.
Mix well milk and egg together.
Pour over spaghetti; mix together well.
Put spaghetti in a greased cookie sheet.
Top, but don't mix with your favorite spaghetti sauce.
Then add cheese and whatever else you like on your pizza.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool slightly and cut in squares.

title: brownies
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour and salt.
Melt butter or Crisco and chocolate.
Add to mixture with vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in an 8 x 8-inch square pan.

title: aunt bertha's spanish burgers
directions: Make patties with onions, pepper and garlic to taste.
Fry patties until nicely browned.
Cover with Spanish rice and simmer for about 20 minutes.

title: blue cheese dip
directions: Mix well and chill.
Serve with crackers, chips or vegetables.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Stir in nuts, if desired.
Frost the cake.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Cube potatoes.
Take fried bacon, onions and pickles and mix together.
In a small kettle heat the remaining ingredients.
Pour over potatoes and stir.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine partially set gelatine to cranberries.
Chop celery and apples; add to gelatine and cranberries.
Chill to set. "Makes a good salad for heart patients."

title: coffee can ice cream
directions: Any other ingredient such as chocolate chips or fresh peaches or other fresh fruit may be added.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saut onion in butter and add hominy, jalapenos and soup.
Heat until bubbly.
Pour into 9 x 13 pan and top with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken thoroughly.
Batter chicken with flour and eggs, cooking in oil for 20 minutes.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt butter in dutch oven over low heat.
Add onions and bell pepper.
Saute till clear, then add 2 cups water.
Bring to boil. Add crawfish tails and green onions.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, uncovered.
Season to taste - a little at a time. Add cornstarch to 1/2 cup water and pour into dutch oven.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and sprinkle parsley flakes.
Let stand a few minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: chocolate refrigerator cake
directions: Melt chips with sugar in double boiler.
Remove from heat and add beaten egg yolks.
Cool 5 minutes (will be stiff).
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and whipped cream.
Break cake into bite sized pieces.
Place 1/2 cake in bottom of 8 x 12 x 2-inch greased pan.
Cover with 1/2 chocolate mixture.
Dot with remaining cake and cover with remainder of chocolate mix.
Sprinkle chopped almonds on top.
Chill overnight.

title: pancake surprise
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs and liquid together. Combine dry ingredients and liquids together.
Spoon onto preheated grill.
Turn when bubbly.
Yields 12 pancakes.

title: shepherd's pie(serves 4)
directions: Heat mince.
Fry onion until golden brown in 1 ounce butter. Add to mince, then stir in stock and seasoning.
Place in a greased pie dish.
Mash potatoes with the rest of the butter, then add beaten egg.
Beat well.
Cover mince with the potatoes and bake in a moderate oven for 15 minutes.
Dot potato with butter and brown under grill after cooking.

title: savory macaroni and beef
directions: Heat a heavy 10-inch skillet over moderate heat for 30 seconds.
Add the ground beef, salt and pepper; cook, stirring, until no longer pink, 3 to 4 minutes.
Push the meat to one side. Add the onion and garlic.
Cover and cook until the onion is soft, about 3 minutes.
Add the tomatoes, tomato paste, cinnamon and basil and stir.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, for 10 to 15 minutes, or until most of the liquid has evaporated.

title: sour cream cut out cookies
directions: Mix everything together very well.
Batter will be very thick and very hard to mix.
Use lots of flour and roll out mix.
Cut into shapes and place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: easy divinity
directions: Beat frosting mix (dry), corn syrup, vanilla and boiling water in small bowl on low speed until blended. Beat on high speed about 5 minutes or until stiff peaks form. Transfer to large bowl. Gradually beat in sugar on low speed. Stir in nuts. Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper. Let stand about 4 hours or until firm. Turn candies over. Makes 4 to 6 dozen.

title: caramel goodies
directions: Combine all ingredients for crust. Pat 1/2 of mixture into greased 9 inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Add carrots, pineapple and nuts and pour into three 9-inch tins, greased and floured, or two 9 x 13-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cake cobbler
directions: Place fruit and its juice in baking dish.
Melt butter and add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour batter over fruit and bake until topping is lightly brown, about 30 minutes.

title: mary's casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain and coat noodles with butter.
Brown meat, onion and green pepper in butter; stir in tomato sauce.
Mix cheeses and sour cream.
In greased casserole, place a layer of noodles, then a layer of meat mixture and a layer of cheese mixture.
Continue layering until used, ending with a layer of cheese mixture.
Bake in uncovered casserole at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
This casserole can be assembled a day ahead, refrigerated and baked just before serving.

title: maraschino cherry balls
directions: Combine butter, confectioners sugar, almond extract, milk and coconut (optional).
Beat well.
Wrap batter around each cherry. Roll in graham cracker crumbs.
Chill 1 hour.

title: 7-minute icing
directions: Combine ingredients in double boiler (beat at high speed) over boiling water for about 7 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread on the cake.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften	cream cheese at room temperature, while cutting up green
peppers
and
onions.
Mix
all
ingredients except pecans or parsley.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in finely chopped pecans
or chopped parsley.
Keep refrigerated until ready to use.
Set
out about 15 minutes before using to soften.
Serve with crackers.

title: swiss steak #1
directions: Brown
both
sides of beef with butter in 14-inch Dutch oven. Add
other	ingredients
and
cook covered for 2 hours. Add water if needed to keep sauce thinner.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil. Add zucchini, chocolate and vanilla. Add sifted dry ingredients.
Grease and flour a tube or Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.

title: supreme cornbread
directions: Beat eggs and oil together.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for about 35 minutes.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix in punch bowl and garnish with fruit slices.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Add
boiling water to oatmeal and cool.

title: divinity candy
directions: Place sugar, water and Karo in pan and cook until it forms a soft ball in water.
Pour over beaten egg whites and beat until mixture begins to thicken. Add nuts and continue beating until mixture is stiff. Drop small amounts on wax paper and top with a pecan half or candied fruit.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and let stand 24 hours, before serving, stirring occasionally.
About 2 hours before serving, fold in whipped cream.
Serve on lettuce leaves and garnish with a cherry.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all
ingredients.
Pour
into
a 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 375° about 45 minutes or until done.

title: polenta
directions: In 3-quart ring pan, combine corn meal, water in pan, cook uncovered at 70% power (Medium-high) for 26 to 30 minutes stirring occasionally until thick.
Set aside to cool and then refrigerate. Slice and serve or better yet, fry the slices in a little butter or olive oil.
Serve with tomato sauce, tomato sauce stew, poultry, ground beef, fried eggs; for breakfast, with maple syrup and butter.

title: chocolate velvet cake
directions: To make the cake, combine in saucepan the chocolate morsels and 1/4 cup water and stir over low heat until melted and smooth. Remove from heat. Sift together the flour, baking soda and salt. Set aside. Combine in bowl the sugar, softened butter and vanilla. Beat until blended. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Blend in melted chocolate mixture. Stir in flour mixture, alternating with 1 cup of water. Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch layer cake pans. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool. Fill and frost with the following frosting.

title: first date scampi
directions: Melt butter.
Add garlic and simmer.
Add wine.
Let boil on low for 15 minutes.
Cook pasta; drain and set aside.
Add shrimp to wine mixture.
Add parsley.
Cover; cook on low heat until shrimp are opaque.
Pour over pasta.
Toss lightly and sprinkle grated cheese.

title: mother-in-law lasagna
directions: Brown beef and onion in a skillet until all the red color is out of the meat.
Add salt, pepper, basil, oregano, tomato sauce and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes. While meat is cooking, cook lasagna noodles in a shallow pan about the size of 9 x 13-inch.
Arrange alternate layers of beef mixture, drained noodles, Parmesan cheese and cottage cheese, ending with beef.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Top with slices of Mozzarella cheese and bake another 5 minutes to melt the cheese.

title: rommegrot(norwegian cream pudding)
directions: Put cream into heavy saucepan and boil for 10 minutes.
Sift flour into cream very gradually to prevent lumps from forming, stirring hard.
Continue cooking over moderate heat, stirring to bring out butter fat.
Remove butter as soon as it forms and put into a small pan to keep warm. Add a little more flour to the grot.
When well mixed, add scalded milk gradually, stirring briskly, until mixture is smooth. Add salt and sugar. Cook 10 minutes more. Serve hot with melted butter and mixed sugar and cinnamon.
Serves 8.
Takes 1/2 hour to make.

title: crusty pizza dough(yields two 14-inch pizzas)
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water in warm bowl.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add salt, oil and 2 1/2 cups flour.
In Kitchen Aid, mix on Speed 2 for 2 minutes.
Add remaining flour 1/2 cup at a time until dough comes away from sides of bowl, kneading 2 to 5 minutes.

title: barbecue water chestnuts
directions: Wrap each water chestnut with 1/3 slice of bacon and fasten with toothpick.
Broil; turn 1 time.
Mix catsup, brown sugar and white sugar.
Heat and pour over chestnuts.
Heat in oven until bubbling or put in crock-pot.

title: carrot raisin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Combine flour, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a large mixing bowl. In another bowl, combine oil, sugar, eggs, molasses and vanilla with an electric mixer. Add shredded carrot and mix. Add raisins and walnuts and mix well by hand. Pour flour mixture into the other ingredients and stir until combined. Pour batter into two ungreased 8 inch loaf pans. Bake for 60 minutes, or until done.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until top is golden brown.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter and milk.
Boil together for 1 1/2 minutes.
Cut off heat and add peanut butter, oatmeal, nuts and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar and flour.
Scald 1-quart milk.
Add a little to egg mixture, then add eggs to rest of milk and cook until thick.
Cool and add extract.
Use 1 pint cream for 1 gallon, finish filling with milk to 1 or 2 inches from top.
A very good old recipe.

title: kaluha
directions: Simmer water, coffee and sugar for 2 hours.
Let cool.
Add vanilla bean and vodka.
Bottle in a dark bottle; let sit 3 weeks. Shake occasionally.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Bring water and butter to a boil and add flour.
Let cool. Add eggs (one at a time) and beat.
Spread in a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cool.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In medium sized casserole dish, alternate layers of asparagus, thin layer of soup and grated cheese.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used, ending with cheese on top.
Should make about 3 layers.
Bake in oven at 375° until bubbly and cheese is slightly browned, about 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients with 1/2 cup melted margarine. Mix remaining ingredients with 3 tablespoons margarine.
Spread over sweet potato mixture.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed baked potatoes(german style)
directions: Wash potatoes and parboil in their jackets 30 minutes.
Cut a slice off of top of each potato and reserve for later use.
Scoop out the potato with a spoon, leaving shells intact.
Finely chop the scooped out portion and add sour cream, egg yolks, cheese, dill, salt and pepper.
Mix well and spoon the mixture into the potato shells, mounding it over the top.
Top potatoes with the reserved slices.
Arrange potatoes in baking dish, over which pour melted butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour, basting often with butter.
Serves 6.

title: sunday dinner
directions: Wrap
each breast in bacon and dried beef.
Secure with a toothpick.	Place chicken bundles in casserole dish.
Pepper to taste.
Mix
sour
cream
and
mushroom soup and pour over chicken.
Dot
with
butter.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cut large shrimp in half.
Cook onion, green pepper and garlic in butter until tender.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add tomatoes and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add shrimp and simmer, uncovered, about 20 minutes, until shrimp are cooked. Serve over rice.

title: big john casserole
directions: Brown
bacon, onion and garlic; add hamburger and pork. Brown and
drain
off
fat.
Meanwhile,
mix in large bowl the beans, brown
sugar, vinegar and mustard.
Add meat to beans; pour in a 9
x
13-inch
pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until
bubbly. Sprinkle
corn
chips
and cheese on top.
Put back in oven until cheese melts, approximately 5 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: In mixing bowl, mix with electric mixer, cream cheese and soup, undiluted, until dip consistency.
Drain can of shrimp and mix again.
Save a few shrimp to garnish.
Refrigerate until time to serve.
Time:
5 to 10 minutes.

title: dill barbecue buns
directions: Measure flour.
Combine 2 cups flour, undissolved yeast, sugar, salt, onion and dill weed in large bowl.
Stir to blend. Add margarine and hot tap water.
Beat with mixer at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Scrape bowl occasionally.
Add 1 more cup of flour; beat with electric mixer at high speed for 1 minute or until thick and elastic.
Stir in enough remaining flour with wooden spoon to make soft dough.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and cool.
Add relish, onion, pepper, celery and pimento.
Mix well.
Combine mayonnaise, soup mix and garlic powder.
Pour over macaroni and mix.
Add chopped eggs and chill.

title: beef brisket in beer
directions: Arrange onion atop meat.
Combine next 4 ingredients.
Pour over meat.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 3 1/2 hours. Uncover; bake 30 minutes longer.
